0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: At day, a healthy and beautiful swamp. At night, the same swamp undergoes a medical history of environmental illness!

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Genesis
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Beauty in formation. Color by day, classic monochrome by night. 
2048 x 1600

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Hallowcracy
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: The artwork is dedicated to the oddities of modern life and the urgent need for change. It is inevitably "political" and "of the here and NOW", yet very metaphorical and "timeless" in its essence.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: A Vitruvian Nightmare for Mazzucchelli
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
“A painter should begin every canvas with a wash of black, because all things in nature are dark except where exposed by the light.” 
― Leonardo da Vinci

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The World is Confusing
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
While the world is made up of many different levels of perception, which intersect and overlap, it is increasingly difficult to see the big picture. 

At night you are less distracted by bright colors and it is easier to see the patterns and connections. Therefore this work of art automatically changes to day or night mode every 12 hours.

The work is part of my series of digital remasters of my old drawings. It is based on a drawing from 1990, that I digitally recreated by accurately following the lines using a graphics drawing tablet before I filled the shapes with single colors.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Artur | Somnium
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
AI Portrait of Artur Sychov. 

Painting robot's AI interpretation of photo taken inside the Virtual World of Somnium Space. The robot used Feedback Loops and Neural Networks to complete the painting in the physical world one brush stroke at a time.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Gate
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Welcome to "The Gate," an entrance to solitude, relief, and peace. Throughout the day the work's form changes, and as time flows on you may
discover its origin and purpose. The piece is created from hand-selected images of eastern and western toilets that were used to train an AI machine learning model
and creatively springs forth from the crossroads of man and machine, certainty and uncertainty, and high and low culture.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Garden of Chaos
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Garden of Chaos is an experiment in generative artwork constructed purely and completely from logic and mathematics. The seeds for the Garden are planted using logic, but the Garden that grows is born out of the natural randomness generated by code.

In every hour of the day, the Garden blooms by expanding, and then closes in rest at night only to be awakened the next morning to grow again.

This phenomenon of delicate balance is the heart of the Garden of Chaos. It lives at the intersection between natural and mechanical, order and chaos. It's a man-made space where nature can thrive.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: EthBoy
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Young Vitalik takes on the role of Picasso’s son Paulo dressed as Harlequin in this artwork but the octahedron Ethereum logo replaces the chequered pattern of the original jester outfit. Leaning against a large chair, the boy genius fiddles with his fingers in a somewhat nervous manner; nevertheless, he stares directly at the viewer with what appears to be a confident, ‘Mona Lisa-like’ smile. Vitalik has no idea what the future has in store for him, but he’s prepared to face any obstacle ahead as he begins life's adventure.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Summer Dreams 2020
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
A Vaporwave inspired digital works by Artist Franky Aguilar. The Summer Dreams Async work of art is a Starburst flavored dream of what the life of the crypto allstar. High resolution graphical imagery, popped with contrasted line work displays the technical vibrancy and lust of what happens when yo pockets is fat. 
-Frankynines

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: the Remixable King of Art
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
A programmable male portrait.

The ever-changing remix of the traits obtained from the sectioning of six portraits of famous painters from the history of art, covering a span of 4 centuries:

Andrea del Castagno (1421–1457) - Portrait of a Gentleman
Antonello da Messina (1430-1479) - Portrait of a Young Gentleman
Raffaello Sanzio  (1483–1520)- Portrait of Pietro Bembo
Ottavio  Leoni (1578–1630) - Portrait of Caravaggio
Rembrandt (1606-1669) - Self portrait
Vincent van Gogh (1853–1890) - Self portrait

5 remixable layers with 6 states each for a journey to discover expressions, unexpected looks, colors and shapes of his 7776 possible combinations, knowing that in every part of them there is the brushstroke of a master and the energy of his spirit and his time.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Neural Alchemy
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
We live in times where New Aesthetic and New Media are the rule of our visual code. My creative process appropriates the characteristic visual features of the main movements present in digital art in recent years—such as Glitch Art, 3D models, DataViz, Code Art, Vaporwave and Cyberpunk, in order to mix them with each other and reintegrate them with traditional media such as drawing and painting. As a painter by training, I conduct myself through an erratic process that seems more like a search for a personal aesthetic within the density of images and information characteristic of our era.
Compose obsessively is the key to associating these elements in an image; distribute visual weights, observe the piece at a different distance, move away and get closer. Neural Alchemy is the result of cautious curation of elements and careful observation and decision-making to solve a piece that is not meant to be static. As an artist, producing an image for the format in which Async Art works is one of the most exhilaratingly creative challenges I have ever faced.
The piece is made up of four layers based on the core elements: Mood, Material Color, Ethereal Color and Body Matter. Each one plays with references of the styles mentioned above. Hope you find hidden messages and feel inspired by this creation, you might enjoy this piece as much as I do.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Another Day In Paradise
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Just as the book speaks to intelligence, the image in all its muteness speaks to the heart.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Empty Room
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
There is nothing more mysterious than a TV set left on in an empty room. It is even stranger than a man talking to himself or a woman standing dreaming at her stove. It is as if another planet is communicating with you.                                                               
Jean Baudrillard

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Extracts from The Mystical Microzoology of Mathematics
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The expert consensus on “The Mystical Microzoology of Mathematics” is that it is a late 20th century hoax manuscript of mixed anonymous authorship, scans of which were first unveiled at a private, invitation-only America Online forum catering to Esperanto enthusiasts in 2001.

The origin story that captured the popular imagination is based on the codex’s internal claim that it is a faithful recreation of documents, themselves reproductions of earlier medieval tomes, entrusted to Zamenhof during the inaugural World Esperanto Congress of 1905.

The primary thesis of the text is that there exist an infinitude of “animalcules” on the immortal mathematical plane, and they have inscrutable sympathetic connections to the other planes of reality, allowing their arcane placement into specialized configurations to reify mystical pre-human prayers of supplication on behalf of the arranger, thus being akin to immobile prayer wheels of sorts.

Of course, the endotextual claims of the manuscript’s pre-modern origins along with its other propositions are contradicted by the very focus of their mystical enquiries, as the microbial-looking forms featured on its illustrated folios are fractal figures more commonly known as Pickover biomorphs, only discovered in the late 1980s.

Nonetheless, this programmable cryptoart work is intended to facilitate the digital reification of all possible valid patterns within the limits stated and implied by extant fragments of the codex, well in excess of the handful of surviving illustrated pages believed to be authentic.

150 billion unique combinations of the biomorph figures, spread through 5 trees, are possible, and taking all other parameters into account, there exist precisely 6.75 trillion visually unique configurations that layer owners can bring to life.

The folio number in the left corner uniquely identifies every single possible variant.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Landscape Study #1 (with Visitor)
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
In the spirit of British landscape artists - your Constables, Turners, and Wilsons - this programmable painting features studies of breathtaking parts of the UK.

Views such as these are rarely empty of modern human activity. More popular areas are likely to receive an overwhelming number of visitors, though some might see just a few each day.

From ornately-framed originals in national gallery spaces, to an unframed canvas reproduction hung in your grandparent's kitchen - romantic landscape paintings can be found in a broad range of settings, and are often regarded as timeless.

A key inspiration for this particular artwork is Anglesey Abbey - a National Trust property in Cambridge, UK - which has an entire wing seemingly dedicated to Lord Fairhaven's collection of Windsor Castle paintings.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The New Block
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
“For man to be able to live he must either not see the infinite, or have such an explanation of the meaning of life as will connect the finite with the infinite.”
― Leo Tolstoy, A Confession

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Quiet of Silence... Triptych (Wabi-Sabi)
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This Art Piece is based on the original Triptych made from the photographs I took around Lake Ashinoko (Japan, 芦ノ湖) and is the first NTF artwork that belongs to the series "WABI-SABI: Acceptance of Transience... the Beauty of things that are Imperfect, Impermanent, Incomplete".
 
I spent nearly 3 months around Japan trying to understand a very profound and rooted Japanese philosophy and way of life that goes back many centuries… that of Wabi-Sabi. Wabi-Sabi is the quintessential Japanese aesthetic. It is the beauty of things that are imperfect, impermanent, and incomplete. It is the beauty of things that are modest and humble. It is the beauty of things that are unconventional… of everyday things… man-made, natural and the union of the two. 
The series was started in 2014-2015 and is still an ongoing project.

WHY MAKE IT INTO A NFT ART PIECE?
With the possibilities offered by AsyncArt and NFTs I decided to "extend" the original Triptych by changing some elements from the 3 original photos with other elements... this gave me more possibilities, more flexibility and allowed me to complete the original concept of "WABI-SABI: Acceptance of Transience... the Beauty of things that are Imperfect, Impermanent, Incomplete".
IMPORTANT: Every element in each layer/state comes from one of the original photographs (about 1000) that I took on the same location (Lake Ashinoko, Japan). This is essential, because all the parts of this NFT artwork are relevant to the same place and not "abstract" insertions from non related images. I wanted everything to be in harmony.

This NFT piece is composed by 3 Layers. Each layer has 6 States which can be changed by the owner of the layer and will reflect on the Master. This creates a total of 216 possible combinations. You can see an animation + all the different combinations here: www.tonycorocher.com/nft-triptych/

The Cover Image of each layer (the image that the owner of the layer will see as his/her own art piece) is one of the 3 original photos that make up the original printed Triptych. 

The original Triptych does NOT come from one photograph split into 3 pieces, but from 3 different photos taken from different positions and with different perspectives. The final piece was first imagined in the head and later on put together as a composition.
The original Triptych is also available as a Fine Art Print (all my photos are printed in 1 unique copy + a Limited Edition of 12).  

WHAT DOES WABI-SABI MEAN?
WABI: Beauty in simplicity.
Wabi is the austere beauty found in simple, even stark, things. The concept emerged as part of the tea ceremony in the 15th century. Over time it moved beyond physical objects like simple tea implements to merge with Zen and become a life philosophy based on rejecting anything showy or wasteful. Wabi can also be enjoyed in observing the changing seasons while reflecting on the impermanence of things.

SABI: Beauty in decay.
Sabi is the beauty of things that are old and in a state of decay. For example, one might see Sabi in the worn grain of the polished wood of the corridors in an old Japanese house; an old statue of the Buddha, the gold lacquer peeled off to reveal the bare wood beneath; or moss covered rocks in the garden.

Wabi-Sabi (侘寂?) represents a comprehensive Japanese world view or aesthetic centered on the acceptance of transience and imperfection. It is a concept derived from the Buddhist teaching of the three marks of existence (三法印 sanbōin?), specifically impermanence (無常 mujō?), the other two being suffering (苦 ku?) and emptiness or absence of self-nature (空 kū?).

Characteristics of the Wabi-Sabi aesthetic include asperity (roughness or irregularity), simplicity, economy, austerity, modesty, intimacy, and appreciation of the ingenuous integrity of natural objects and processes.

----------------------
ABOUT ME:
International Award winning independent Documentary & Fine Art Photographer. Born in Italy, 1974. I was educated and then worked as an Art Director/Graphic Designer for many years (I still do). 
You can find a full biography, more of my work, a list of international Awards/Exhibitions/Museums on my website www.tonycorocher.com or on my LinkedIn page www.linkedin.com/in/tonycorocher/

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Art We Share
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Art usually attempts to convey a feeling or a message; it exposes the inner workings of the creator's mind. 
An art piece is a language developed by the artist to communicate alternatively to conventional language.
The Async platform gifts the collector the ability to use and to be immersed in that language; for the first time the artist is taking a step back by allowing the collector/s to have the final say in what the art piece should look like.

In "The Art We Share" I wanted to take that concept a step further. I want this piece to become a reflection of the collector's emotional state instead of reflecting mine. That being said, I hope to see the "Joy layer state" a lot, and maybe if you are feeling sad I can help you with that. :)

Cheers,

Horus

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: "Untitled #1", from "Slits in Depth" series (2020)
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This work is the first of a new series of 3D anaglyph images. It's composed of 3 layers (Black, Gray, and White) that can be arranged to display different levels of depth when observed with red/ cyan glasses. 

It was shot on my studio during The Great Lockdown of 2020, with layers made of old photographic backgrounds.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Crypto Bubble
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Realize what you really want. It stops you from chasing butterflies and puts you to work digging gold. Digital Artwork by Sandro Ieva

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Jackpot
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
“The Jackpot” is a collaboration between https://async.art/u/rutgervandertas (0x84300dCc7ca9Cf447e886fA17C11fa22557d1AF0) and Ytje Veenstra. They share a studio in Haarlem, the Netherlands,  where they found mutual artistic ground.

“The Jackpot” is loosely based on William Gibson's book “The Peripheral”. It's about two timelines, set apart 70 years, on different continents. These timelines converge and characters on both sides of  time find themselves interacting, strategizing and plotting to ward off a greater danger, called the jackpot.

Ytje Veenstra is a longtime fan of Gibson's cyberpunk and speculative fiction. Her clear-lined drawings intersect and merge with Rutger van der Tas' mind bending, psychedelic style. Like the two timelines in Gibson's story, Rutger and Ytje weave their art and vision into an organic, yet collage-like dream world, a universe where future nightmares and virtual worlds fold in around themselves.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Journey
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Journey is an artwork which shows a perspective switch from division to unity, from the other to the same, from being above/below to being at the same level. Using the metaphor of day and night as light and darkness, the artwork switches from the vertical (above-below) configuration to the horizontal (same-level) configuration as it journeys from darkness to light.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: View Program
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Control your view.

View Program is an adjustable abstraction of a high-rise building. Consisting of 6 layers, owners have the ability to select from 9 different window patterns, 4 atmospheric conditions, and over 16 billion color combinations through 4 different reflections. This artwork is optimized for display on the Async AppleTV app.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: 2.0 - Out of Concept
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
2.0 Out of Concept - A reference to the Ethereum 2.0 the new version of the Ethereum blockchain network created by Vitalik Buterin.

It takes its name because it is a piece with elements that apparently are not in the same concept, interdimensional travelers, a digital portrait of Vitalik and a strange dimensional gate! how far does your imagination go?

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Micro Grass #001
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Micro Grass #001 is a work based on the micro world.I use color to divide the graphics layout to make geometric and add natural elements .

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Who's The Controller Now?
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
An update of Diego Rivera’s famous fresco, Man at the Crossroads.  Destroyed for political reasons in 1934 by the Rockefeller family.  Repainted in Mexico City and renamed - Man, Controller of the Universe.

In a time of global economic distress, an oligarch's contracts came with the right to silence an artist, and erase an enormous physical work from one of the world's most famous locations - 30 Rockefeller Center.  Pressured by client and peers alike, Rivera found himself at that familiar crossroads - can I remain the captain of my own artistic destiny in a world of commerce?

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Async Dynamic Header #2
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Our second Dynamic Header doodle. Dynamic Headers are made to live embedded in the header slice of our homepage. By owning a layer in this piece, you'll have the ability to influence the very look of our site!

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Mixed media - acrylic with a pinch of digital

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Still Life on Niche
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Using three recurring elements from my work, I set out to develop another exercise on light and how it affects the mood of a scene, through a year of iterations. 

Given the impossibility of representing the 'light' of a specific month, I tried to capture the atmosphere through the light, with its colours, it's shadows or its vibrancy. Even though the elements remain the same, each month there's a new scene manifesting changes related to a certain month; wether by reason (the known angles of the sun on specific times for ex.) or emotion (the use of a symbolic colour to express a season), the scene is always changing in accordance to an idealized seasonal cycle (taking place in a temperate climate of the northern hemisphere.)

The images change at the 21st of each month, and during each season the camera focus will incide on one of the elements: an egg for the Winter Solstice and a skull for the Summer Solstice, while the Equinoxes are marked by a focus on the idol standing in between them. 

It's a still life, but also a meta-shrine that connects us to another form of time.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Eclipse
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Solar eclipses and their most spectacular effect - the total concealment of the Sun by the Moon - stimulate the imagination of people from the most varied cultures around the Earth.
While the scientific community is still connected to measurements and quantitative bias, art and metaverse takes us out of reality and takes us to a beautiful and charming place.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Say Ahhh...
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Say Ahh... is originally a physical traditional oil painting on canvas, 36x36’’ (91x91 cm) made between January and March 2020 in Boston, Massachusetts USA, and adapted for Async on December 2020.

This piece represents an idea that I had in a dream, it  shows my signature bear character showing his gumdrop teeth while floating in a space full of stars, eyeballs and polka dots.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Song of The Coins
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Addition to my 'Data Art' series this is my new exploration of 'Simulation + Data Art' this is a road to experiment data artworks with an intent of adding the right theme style and a simulative approach apart from being fully abstract. This is an artistic expression of datasets of 24hr high price (USD) of major coins like Bitcoin BTC, Ethereum ETH and Litecoin LTC.

Generating a sequence of notes with a pitch corresponding to the price data value of the coins. The visual representation is an audio spectrum of all 3 coins price fluctuation of 1 year (~2020). The prices make the audio beats and hence the visual spectrum. The master image consists of all data from all three coins. The idea of sonification of data came from endless datart-workshop experiments and after everyday trial and errors of finding different dimensions to visualize data beautifully. A node-based visual programming engine, image manipulation and other open-source software are combined to change dimensions of raw data and render into desired results.

Master audio: www.bit.ly/3r59ifI
Read more on portfolio: www.flatarc.io

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Playtime At Le Mans
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Playtime At Le Mans | From [The Room] series

A creation which focuses on minimalism and the beautiful characteristics of the famous Le Mans Porsche 917K.

Do you prefer the relaxed day cycle of the Gulf Blue... or the more engaging and exciting Gulf Orange. What mood are you in? Will you win over your imagination.

The cycle of time lives on...

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Sun Kachina Hours
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Kachina spirits live in Native American Hopi villages. Many years ago I was priviledged to witness the Niman (Going Home) ceremony, which concludes the Kachina season with an outdoor Kachina Dance at sunrise.  It was a magical experience. A few years later, I was able to trade a painting for a traditional Kachina doll made by a noted Hopi artisan.  It was a Clown Kachina.  Another important Kachina is the Sun Kachina, a highly abstracted version of which is reimagined in this work.  The images change on the hour throughout the 24 hour night/day cycle.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Lion Faced One - Mother of All
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
I took a dive in a world of space exploration, rebuilding humans as AI's, people uploading their minds into so called proxies and human beings bio engineering themselves to live in marine environments. I saw this world come alive while reading the Poseidon's Children book trilogy by Alastair Reynolds, while mixing in my own interests: old scifi movies and my childhood obsession with stories about space exploration. 
The matriarch, Eunice Akinya, is a space pioneer. She's named The Lion Faced One because she painted the image of a lion on her space helmet when she was younger. This character resonated with me on a personal level. She reminded me of my grandmother, who passed away in 2020. Being 98, she experienced WWII. When our country was occupied by the nazis, she smuggled weapons and and supplies past German checkpoints,. She was pretty fearless and practical to a fault, just like Eunice Akinya.
The source material reflects my own ideas. It challenged me to imagine how I would envision a future world, while anchoring it firmly to classical concepts in art, like landscapes and portraits.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: A Day Of Soft Construction
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: A Day Of Soft Construction' is a 3D painting interpretation of Salvador Dali 1936 painting 'Soft Construction with Boiled Beans'. The interpretation consists of 24 images that represent 24hours of the day. The interpretation is able to show us this painting from never seen before perspectives and  experienced in completely new light as it is 'living' through the day and night

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Timeless
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Timeless is a look into how cultural memory can be stored in digital objects. This piece consists of a single layer that represents different aspects of the intertwinement between culture and technology. The “time” layer evolves autonomously throughout a Gregorian year, gradually returning the central piece to its archaeological origin, deeper into the ground. Every 1st of the month, the sculpture will be buried a bit more until a whole year cycle, where it will emerge and begin the process once again. An endless temporal loop.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Chess and Addicts
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Chess and Addicts portrays the beauty of chess game and the love for it which isn't confined to any boundaries, be it place, age, gender, time, physical presence, life, death and many more represented in metaphorical ways. With every layer of the piece adding to the emotional factors surrounding the match, it also symbolises how a very small change can create a whole new story and perspective shown by the piece.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Path of the Monolith
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This was a magical crossroad, the air shifted as various places converged into this one space. With each turn there was a new opening, a separate path leading to a magical monolith. 

So many possibilities...

The hero felt lost, unsure where to go, knowing that each monolith provided different blessings and strengths. She took her time, examining all of the choices thoroughly- She could always use more knowledge, protection and fortune, but maybe she craved for a meaningful connection and some additional courage. This was a difficult choice, but there was no wrong choice, which gave her comfort.

In the end she let her instinct choose, what felt right for her. As she approached the Monolith, she felt the magic radiating from it washed over her. 

The backgrounds represent our past, where we come from. The cloaks symbolize the present moment, they're the insulation from the outside world. The protection and comfort, giving us the strength to keep going. Whereas, Monoliths represent the future, they can be considered more like magical charms to aid us in our pursuits. Each monolith has it's own meaning and purpose.

The symbols in the art can be transcribed into English words revealing the deeper meanings in the artwork and combinations. The symbols' key is located on the cloaks preview layer.

This painting is a part of the Adventure series, a journey about discovery, persistence and perseverance. This project is quite personal but I keep the meanings vague enough for others to find their own interpretations and connection to the art.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Dreamer
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
I believe that we can do a lot with effort, but to create something with soul and revolutionary power you must be a dreamer. Dream about your vision every day and make it the fuel to build.
It is important to build, it is important to dream!

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Fall From Grace
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"Fall From Grace" is my genesis Async Art piece. It's a play on the story of Icarus. How ambition and the pursuit of our desires can easily be convoluted or distorted by greed and lust. How it's ok to aspire and dream, but that there's a delicate line between desire and foolishness. Enjoying and being grateful for the journey itself is part of the dream, and ascending too high just means that there can ultimately be an even larger fall to the bottom.
.
.
.
DETAILS:
•Layers: 34 Background Layers, 12 Middle Layers, 20 Top Layers
•Resolution: 1620x2160 (Async), 5400x7200 (High Res)
•Medium: Multimedia, Programmable
•Software: Tilt Brush, Cinema 4D, Octane Render, Substance Painter, ProCreate, Adobe Illustrator, Adobe Photoshop
•Physical Canvas/Prints: If they so choose, the original buyer of the Master Layer can get in touch with me on social media to have a free physical 18"x24" Canvas Print or Fine Art Print sent to their address of choice.
.
.
.
PROCESS:
This piece was created with an intention to use as many of my different creative skills / software knowledge as possible, while also iterating on years and years of personal aesthetic research and design theory. The first step involved sculpting the base mesh, rigging the model, splitting out the designated sections/pieces of the body, and then resuming sculpting and detail using VR & Tilt Brush. From VR, the 3D model was taken back and cleaned up in Cinema 4D and textured externally in Substance Painter. Once the model and texturing was to my liking, I consolidated my textures and set up my render scene/lighting using Octane Render in C4D. I exported a 2D still that I could paint and embellish with the floral pattern tattooed on the model's body. The still render was then hand-painted using my iPad/Procreate. The final step included me creating alternate background layers, hair/wire layers, and skin layers using bits and pieces from the previous processes. All the variants and pieces were composited in Photoshop, tweaked, color corrected, and styled to create the final composition consisting of 34 background layers, 13 mid ground layers, and 20 foreground layers.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: the Remixable Landscape
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
A programmable landscape.
 
The ever-changing remix of the foregrounds, middlegrounds and backgrounds obtained from the sectioning of six artworks of famous painters from the history of art, covering a span of 4 centuries: 
 
Giorgione - Tramonto (1505-1508)
Pieter Bruegel the Elder - The Harvesters (1565)
Aelbert Cuyp - Travelers in Hilly Countryside (1650-1652)
Caspar David Friedrich - Frau vor untergehender Sonne (1818)
Vincent van Gogh - The Sower (1888)
Henri Rousseau - La Charmeuse de Serpents (1907)
 
3 remixable layers with 6 states each for a journey to discover lights, colors and shapes, unexpected atmospheres of the 216 possible combinations knowing that in every part of them there is the brushstroke of a master and the energy of his spirit and his time.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: GANOODLE [Async Edition]
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
GANOODLE [Async Edition] is part of a series of experimental character artworks, created by training a generative adversarial network on a data set of my own character doodles, then illustrating selected results by hand. This genesis Async Edition marks the fourth installment in the GANOODLES series and their debut to the world of programmable art. 

The GANOODLES project has always been about experimentation—learning through playing and pure curiosity, using a blend of technology and traditional drawing methods. Now, Async’s mechanism lets layer owners act as collaborators, with complete creative control to mix and match shapes and features, allowing others to experiment and play along with me! 

The Async GANOODLE incorporates five possible state changes in its body, eyes, frame and canvas layers, allowing the owners of each layer the ability to switch between those different variations. Make it as coordinated—or as chaotic—as you’d like!

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Menarche Monarch
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Menarche Monarch is an incarnation fighting against the forced transition to vulnerability and loss of identity. This piece was originally crafted with polymer clay and re-incarnated in 3 different forms including this async piece. It consists of 7 layers and the owner has the ability to select from 7 different lighting and color states and bring her to life in different ways.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Phase Space #2: Divergences
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Our heroes have made it to civilization with their boon! Ogdai and Kallah are to meet with a master spiral arm teacher, Enki, to learn the next steps of their initiatory journey. The Hierarchical Capital is a busy place however, populated with dangers and delights, and doesn’t allow our heroes anything like an easy victory!

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Rock Paper Scissors
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Rock paper scissors is a simple little game we played as kids; whether to pass time or to call dibs on the bigger slice of pie. Under the hood, it’s a rudimentary and confrontational form of communication; three words caught in a triangular relationship of domination and submission.

A closed fist represents rock: heavy, solid, and capable of crushing scissors. An extended index and middle finger resemble scissors: sharp, sophisticated, and destined to cut paper. An open palm mimics paper: candid, transparent, and clever enough to bind rock. The only moment of truce is when matching gestures are thrown; a brief release of tension and glimpse into a mirror. 

More could be said with the three expressions. A closed fist is handing a concealed gift to an open palm; the extended index and middle fingers are calling for peace. The relationship doesn’t need to be contentious.

‘Rock Paper Scissors’ frames an ongoing conversation between two strangers. Limited to three signals, the strangers may decide whether their dialog is a never-ending chase for power, a mutual armistice, or something deeper altogether.

A third participant narrates my own relationship with my hands. As an artist, my hands mean the world to me - they allow me to express my thoughts and materialize my imagination. Perhaps a cosmic joke, my hands suffer from chronic eczema. Whenever I create art, my hands become fragile, dry husks – as though I channel life from my hands into the work. Despite all this, I choose my art to be about joy and play. In the end, it’s a fun little game.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Micro Grass #003-Cloud & Grass
 Day theme / Energetic 
 Night theme / Clean

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Crypto Gothic
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: 2030. A new subculture was born in the crypto community. They live in mixed reality and use neuro implants as accessories to communicate with the world and play their games in the cyber world. The boundaries between physical and digital finally disappeared. Their physical bodies now mixed with their accounts on neuro social media and digital wearables.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Tarrying with Topiary
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Welcome, welcome to our garden! Please, take a break and stroll around. You've really been working so hard, and could take a moment to yourself. Have a chat with our topiary, but keep a close eye, they're a bit restless and change shape! And you're not alone, there are plenty of other guests to enjoy the space with! Really, just take as much time as you need, we'll leave the light on for you.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Cryptoforce
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: A surreal allegory of the concept of "force tranquille" - that could be translated as "quiet / gentle / effortless strength" - in the world of blockchain art. The Cryptowitch, the Concept Skies and the Energy Ground each comes in 3 flavours: Bitcoin, Ethereum and Ripple.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Le Visionnaire
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: The Visionary, holding his/her vision tightly, feeding from it, never giving up.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The City of Krasmere
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The city of Krasmere is the pride of the Kasai Dynamics Corp in Kepler 6. 
This beautiful city rivals the ones from the Old World, and boasts a magnificent highway where transports arrive and depart on the hour. Workers arrive every day, along with merchants, convicts, mercenaries, and priests. Powerful CORP agents coming here to check the newest hardware available. 
One never knows what they will find in Krasmere.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Old Bitcoin Art
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Old Bitcoin Art

Artist portfolio: flatarc.io/crypto-art

Addition to my quest for visualizing complexity of computational thinking and using data as my paint. With the service of AI (artificial intelligence) such as generative adversarial network (GAN) and many other to create amalgamations to analyze form by an artistic thinking with the help of machine intelligence. Not a single source from any original art is used to create these paintings. Used NASA's public collection of Hubble telescope cosmos images. The model itself ended up giving it vibes of unique historic art movement styles. Just to get philosophical, As we have not yet figured out what conscious itself is, then how can we define what art should be.
​
Also a unique opportunity when you need to think about parametric form with unusual physics which cannot exist in reality, this is where machine intelligence services you with power of exploring unusual and other-worldly forms and experiences. Refer my other 'Data Art' project pages for more about inspirations. This current piece of work was a tribute to the fascinating, daring Bitcoin-crypto-community and people who love decentralization. Unbelievable paradigm shift that will change everything that we know as norms.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Does she see's things I cannot
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: A piece about my first born. In the first 6 months of sleepless nights and constant worrying. When feeding or changing,little Nora would stare into empty space. It was almost as of she could see things I could not.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Brigitte Bardot
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: This polaroid mosaic depicting French actress and singer Brigitte Bardot is the first of my ICON series. Bardot, one of the first popular culture icons, captivated a generation with her beauty and sense of freedom. She paved the way for countless others to follow and so it made sense to begin my series with her. My piece has 24 different color variations, which change automatically on the hour, like a clock. I designed the colorways specifically for the different times of the day in which they will be active. Let this beautiful and iconic image accompany you through the different stages of your day, no matter where in the world you may be. Bardot illuminated in pink and orange hues will help you ease your way into the day, more muted tones will ensure you stay focused during working hours, and the vibrant colors that play into the night will set the vibes to party the way Bardot did in the 50s. The owner of this token will also receive the 1/1 physical framed polaroid set that I used to create this digital time-lapse. 12 original polaroids in a secret colorway not seen here on Async, framed in a beautiful white frame that measures 20’’ x 15’’ and lets the polaroids do all the talking.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Changing Aroma of the Amazon Jungle
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Amazon jungle had the smell of the rainforest. The wet soil's smell, the strong smell of tropical flowers, an explosion of fresh fragrances from an immense variety of plants combined, the pungent smell of decaying animals, wood and leaves rotting on the jungle floor. The lungs of the planet, one of the main living repository of the world's biodiversity, the home of the Indigenous Peoples, are under attack. Climate change and brutal deforestation in Amazonia are changing their aroma. With the settlers, the extreme climate and wild fires, the sky darkens and arrives the black rain with the smell of smoke and burning. Even the Brazil’s National Museum that kept one of the best collections of indigenous literature and artefacts in the world was eaten by the flames. “This is the greatest loss of indigenous writing in Latin America. Our memory has been erased.”

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Exit
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:

Gabor Molnar / Dformer

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Mount Ethereum
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Through a generative system comprising of over one hundred images, Mount Ethereum reacts to the value of ETH in $50 increments, resulting in an ever changing, flowing form.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Hash In Space
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Hash in Space is a mix of Programmable + Generative Art inspired by Ethereum and Outer Space. The idea is to create a visual representation of Ethereum Network hash rate throughout the past 5 years from 2016 to 2020.

To create this, daily Ethereum average hash rate data was collected (source: Etherscan.io) and converted to values consisting of a whole year's total, median and average.
The interaction between data and graphics was done through associating the entire year's values to pre-defined range modifiers into a graphic particles system.

A javascript math script was created to convert the hash rate year values in GH/s  to 6 particles system modifiers values: Particles Count X, Particles Count Y, Displacement, Fractal Scale, Random Swirl Y and Force Relative Position X.

The result is a mix of reality and sci-fi, present and future, precise data and visual satisfaction. Maybe this is the way we will visualize data in the future. Or maybe, by that time, the space is the place where we will be.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Crumbling Keep
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: The mystical land of Kurindar holds endless wonders. One such spectacle is known simply as the Crumbling Keep. Its true origins have been lost to history, and appears to be little more than an abandoned castle, bereft of its former glory. Residents of nearby villages claim the keep is cursed, and warn against going near the castle at night. They say the moon awakens the ancient spirits within... and they do not take kindly to visitors.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Landscape Study #2 (with Creatures)
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
A departure from the grounded tranquillity found in Study #1, this programmable painting presents far more dramatic and diverse scenes. These take inspiration from a variety of themes - often blending fiction and reality. 

The artist has challenged themselves to create a set of extraordinary creatures and exquisite frames that succeeded in complimenting, contrasting, or otherwise enhancing each unique landscape.

Each combination of layers allows plenty of room for interpretation - highlighted in part by their cryptic (or outright vague) state titles.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Red Room
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: The Red Room is an artpiece inspired by the urban legend known as "Red Rooms". Such legends are alleged to feature captured terrorists/criminals to be gruesomely tortured at the request and pleasure of a livestream chat connected to a site within the dark web. The moral implications of such a scenario are up for you to decipher.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Reclining Nude
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Reclining nude in a classic pose, rendered in three styles, capturing the beauty of South Africa. Collaboration with Daniella Attfield.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Baptism
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This is my first exclusive digital piece for Async Art. Made in January 2021.

This piece celebrates the baptism of my signature red bear, that until now, didn't have a name. Now his official name is Chico.

I created Chico in 2017 and since then I've been asked about his name by almost everybody that has seen him. Sadly I never came up with a name that I thought could suit him well. In January 2021 the artist Brian Murphy, sculptor based in Boston MA, suggested the name Chico for the bear and I thought it suited him perfectly: it means "small" in Spanish, it gives him a cool Latin-American vibe and it also sounds cute to me.

I decided to make Chico's baptism public using blockchain technology so it could be official.

The piece also contains a series of symbols I've been working with lately, like stars, sparkles and dripping clouds.

The layers can be changed to show different stages of the hearts, a regular red or a special golden version of Chico and also a colorful day or red night background (that hides an easter egg).

You can see more works here: https://www.jaime.works

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: One of these days.
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
When it comes to chasing an epiphany on a daily basis we often lose ourselves completely while encountering innumerable visions and endless ways of possible approach in fiddling with the ravishing onslaught of inspiring perspectives.

Most often we just have to pick one and go for it entirely.

Natural Warp 28012021

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: MegaCube
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: This 3D Cube is an experiment to commemorate the most ambitious multiplayer experience in Decentraland up to date. Date released 29/01/2021

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: 4EVER / Async_edit /2021
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Mood communicator.
Two (or more) persons, communicate their mood between them,
by using 3 different states of mood for each figure (colorful, neutral and dark).
Each layer is composed of two figures that create a ring.
Background is a layer as well with 2 states light and dark.
The result is a unique artistic sculpture based on the mood of the users evolving to a unique form of communication.
Based on the artwork "4EVER8" / 2018
Digital 3d

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: THE SOUL OF JAPAN: Profound Tranquility or Modern Loneliness? (WabiSabi n.4)
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
• VERY IMPORTANT:  
THIS PIECE IS SOLD AS A SINGLE ARTWORK! This means that THE LAYERS ARE NOT FOR SALE but will be delivered FREE OF CHARGE TO THE PERSON WHO COLLECTS THE MASTER. I decided to do this because the artwork was created to be in the hands of one collector and I would like him/her to have the ability to trigger changes to his/her liking.

• TEST THE ARTWORK: before you decide to purchase, you can test and play around with the Master by triggering changes to the states of the Layers (3 Layers + 18 States = 216 possible combinations) by going to this link:
https://www.tonycorocher.com/nft-digitalart/AsyncArt/testwabisabi04

• EXTRA!!! A PHYSICAL PRINT: the owner of this artwork will also be eligible to receive a Museum Quality Fine Art Giclèe Print (70x40 cm) done using carbon pigmented inks on Hahnemühle Archival Paper of the highest quality. This will be a 1of1 Fine Art Print and a collectors item (with holograms, signature, date, stamps and paper certificates) in line with my 10 years selling museum quality prints. The special feature here is that the collector will be able to select the 3 States he/she likes more (one for each layer) and I will get that selection printed and sent to him/her. 
You can find more info about my Fine Art Prints process here: https://www.tonycorocher.com/fine-art-prints/

• DESCRIPTION: 
I loved Japan and its culture since I can remember… its aesthetic principles of beauty, its sense of peace, the respect for others, its harmony and safety. 

In this artwork I want to present and describe (through a series of 18 interchangeable street photographs I took around Japan in 2 years) a feeling of detachment and kind of “self inflicted” loneliness which may seem very strange to a non Japanese or someone traveling to this beautiful country for the first time. This feeling can be encountered all over the country but is felt more strongly in the big cities, especially in the streets of Tokyo. 

A feeling that deeply entangles and mixes with a secular way of life, with a thought process and a value system based on respect, duty and obligation… all directed to achieve harmony and tranquility.
To most Japanese these are not just ideas to believe in, but almost “unmovable objects” that still linger in the further recesses of their “modern” minds.
These ideas may have changed their forms in the last century but they have also retained their influence and are frequently the main reason of misunderstanding with non Japanese people.

This NFT digital artwork is composed of 1 Master, 3 Layers and 18 states which can be triggered from the Layers to change the Master in 216 possible combinations. It is n.4 in the "WabiSabi" NFT Collection.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Enemy
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
'Enemy' is the artwork created to explore the question of 'What makes an enemy'.
It is a journey to understand the complexity of our prejudice and reasons with which one convinces themselves whilst calling someone an enemy. And as the reasons start becoming obvious, a slightest change in any of the layer presents itself with many other very different reasons contradicting or supporting the previous explanation. 
The artworks with its four characters is a play of their changing roles and positions, making their actions in the piece more and more unexpected and difficult to understand, thus blurring the lines of rights and wrongs in this fight. Many mysteries are unfolded with a closer look at the details of each layer indicating the many things happening in the moment that might not be visible immediately.    
So the work is not an answer but an attempt of creating a place to understand the question and hence the term 'Enemy'.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Exquisite Genesis
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"Exquisite Genesis" was inspired by The Exquisite Corpse. A game the surrealist used to play in which a piece of paper would be passed around and each member would draw a portion of the body.  The result was a combination of styles and ideas held together by the figurative form.  The more random each artist's interpretation was, the more interesting the result would be. 

"Exquisite Genesis" is my first exploration of this concept within the NFT space.  It includes 4 heads, 3 bodies, 3 legs and 3 objects of desire.  In total this piece has the potential to create 108 unique combinations.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Programmable "Hodl'em"
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Texas hold 'em (hold 'em or holdem) is one of the most popular variants of the card game of poker. Two cards, known as hole cards, are dealt face down to each player, and then five community cards are dealt face up. Each player seeks the best five card poker hand from any combination of the seven cards; the five community cards and their two hole cards.

This piece brings a maximum interactivity concept between the layers owners. Interact with other layers owners to compete in the most epic and endless programmable poker game in blockchain.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Into The Digital Wilderness
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The digital world, especially when setting foot in the blockchain terra incognita for the first time, feels strange, wonderful, filled with opportunities, risks and things you don't understand, with its diverse fauna and flora of bots, algorithms and human users. Hurt yourself, find some help, lose some gas for nothing when you trip, find treasures.

     And when the gas fees are too high, it's night on the blockchain, everyone takes it easy, things move slowly, and it's time to tell your stories, exchange with the community, show your findings, take a break or create.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Alien
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
There are infinite worlds in the Universe with infinite sentient beings inhabiting them.

Master autonomously updates once a day at 12am with one of 366 original artworks, showcasing some of the rarest beings, their cities, transport, technology and nature.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Water
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Water is a series of 6 watercolour artworks by Ashna Sahir, digitally scanned and enhanced. Each of the works can be revealed by switching the only layer "Today".

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: the Remixable Seascape
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
A programmable marine art.
 
The ever-changing remix of the shoreline, the sea and the sky from six artworks of famous painters from the 19th century romantic age:
 
Caspar David Friedrich - The Stages of Life (1834)
Eugène Poittevin - Les Bains de Mer, Plage d’Etretat (1864)
Gustave Courbet - The Wave (1869)
Vincent van Gogh - View of the Sea at Scheveningen (1882)
Paul Gauguin - Rocks and Sea (1886)
Winslow Homer - Saco Bay (1896)
 
3 remixable layers with 6 states each for a journey to discover lights, water's colors and shapes, unexpected atmospheres of the 216 possible combinations knowing that in every part of them there is the brushstroke and the energy of a master, with his personal view and feeling about the sea.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: / FRAGILE /
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
⛔️Watch out!
 * Delicate material. *
Do not touch with dirty hands or soul.
To keep away
of brute men,
stupid women
and vermin in general.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Portrait of Nakamoto Satoshi #10: The Bitcoin ☢️Spaceman ☢️
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
As part of the on-going series to find the true identity of Satoshi, the mysterious person or pseudonymous group who created the technological cryptocurrency Bitcoin which is fundamentally just beginning to change and challenge financial systems across the planet.  Many people have claimed to be this person or persons, but we have not yet found the actual source to be truth.  However, a few possible identities have just emerged in 2021, 20 years since the development of the technology:

Possible Identities:
#10-1 The Elontoshi Muskamoto
As we shoot into the future, behind us is the history we leave behind.  Could this technology be a double-edged sword?  On one hand--> from the league of extraordinary gentlemen comes the rise of a brilliant man who puts us into outer-space, has advanced electronic payment systems, revolutionized the electric car industry, launched the Falcon 9 Rocket to the international Space-Station with a billion-dollar contract with NASA.  The headlines read: "Tesla Acquires 1.5 billion in Bitcoin" -- (Source: CNBC, Feb 8th 2021)
".....I do at this point think Bitcoin is a good thing.  I'm late to the party, but I am a supporter of bitcoin.  .... However the comments on Dogecoin "are meant to be jokes.... The most ironic outcome would be that Dogecoin becomes the currency of Earth in the future... said Musk" (CNN)

Possible Identity #10-2
The Kimatoto Jung-toshi
  On the flip-side of the coin, a brutal dictator who will stop at nothing to grab power.  The headlines read: "Finding Financing in Unlikely Places" United Nations Experts sheds light on $316 million worth of Bitcoin amassed by North Korea (Nikkei Asian Review)
".....however, bitcoin is an effective tool for several reasons...... that is cut off from the modern financial system and has little access to hard currency, it is easy to understand why bitcoin is so appealing. It stands out as the perfect solution for the budding financial problems that are caused by years of disconnection from the global economy...... North Korea can effectively mine or steal bitcoin to support its economy and missile program." (Investpedia)

  The future that is laid before us we must seek-out, for it is part of the human condition to journey and explore where no man has gone before.  The blockchain is another battle-ground for humanity, and we must win this battle.  To-The-Moon 🚀🚀🚀 

Follow my adventures in space, as I tweet about them in real time(a living breathing and talking artwork): https://twitter.com/Muskamoto

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Cosmic Chess
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Cosmic Chess is a playable artwork that will evolve in time as the game progresses.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Unfairground monthly report
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Denizen shadow is the natural-born winner. He wasn't born in this place and nobody remembers when he appeared; seems like he has been living here his whole life. He has a special gift to convince people to believe in whatever he comes up with. Every day he has a new follower. As days are passing and more and more shadows gather around him, also the gossip starts to spread. The month is nearing its end, critical mass is growing bigger and bigger and on the last day of the month, they unmask him. Everybody leaves him and he is alone again. But not for a long. Shadows quickly forget and start to gather around him again. This cycle repeats itself month after month, till the end of the internet...  
The first twenty protagonists of this artwork are tokenized under Marko Zubak contract, using Mintbase and Arweave (https://opensea.io/collection/marko-zubak-2).
MLIBTY Shadows represent people in general but also shadows behind the curtains, invisible inhabitants you never meet, but you feel their presence. Sometimes they are watching you, sometimes they smile, black and white, no hands and no legs, shadows with faces. One day, this shadow may become a famous protagonist of one of MLIBTY Shadows art pieces. More about the artist: http://www.markozubak.com

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Screens
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Examining the concept of day and night through the AsyncArt feature.
For thousands of years, humans have adapted their lives and activities to day and night.
During the day they performed all the necessary processes for their survival and at night they slept and rested.
In modern societies, however, with the use of electricity and technology, where the night is less dark now and you always have something to do, the concept of night and day, in many cases, has been adjusted to a new form.
As an artist working in digital media, the day has ceased to be the only 24-hour period where I can work.
In fact most artworks, including this one, have been created in the still of the night.
On the globalized planet, where there is always day and night at the same time, a new society is being created that,
gives the impression that it never sleeps and always something is happening.
The artwork "Screens" is examining this concept, also, 
from the perspective of the affect that this change has to our personalities and bodies.
Digital 3d / 2021

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Happy Place
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Happy Place portrays an Indian Queen sitting in front of a painting she adores, that reminds her of the serenity she seeks. At night she dreams of visiting that place to enjoy the wind and nature. As the loop continues, the women sitting in front of window now dreams of having a life of a Queen and wants to have an artwork behind her instead of a window that doesn't appeal her much. 
So the happy place keeps changing with the changing circumstances. What once might feel as a source of true happiness might lose its value with time. And thus the artwork intends to depict that happiness is not something to be attained but something to be felt.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: self controlling hands
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: The title already says a lot. In the crypto universe it is often called: DYOR - Do Your Own Research. This work is a remake of a work of art by M.C Escher, who drew the hands that draw themselves. This artwork shows the self-controlling hands in 3d on a graphics tablet with a display. The hands are symbolic of blockchain technology because every transaction is transparent and can be verified on a block explorer. Each block content has a timestamp, which is represented by the clocks in this work.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Choose your pollution
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: This clod, despite being created in a playful way, wants to draw attention to the environment and its state of health. Too often we don't think about what our impact on the planet might be. Sometimes we are unaware, sometimes we ignore it and we do not care about what surrounds us. Here we can simply choose which environment we want to live in, but there is no solution without pollution. Is it already too late?

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: / THE MERMEID & LAMIA /
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
After a shipwreck, an exhausted survivor struggles to reach shore by clinging to an algae-covered rock to climb out of the dark waters. Exhausted, he cannot resist the undertow and treacherous currents that threaten to carry him under the waves. At this critical moment, he is struck by the beautiful vision of a young woman sitting on the rock with pearly white skin and parted lips singing a song :


“Who would be

A mermaid fair,

Singing alone,

Combing her hair…”


-----------------------------------------------------------------------


Después de un naufragio, un superviviente exhausto lucha por alcanzar la costa aferrándose a una roca cubierta de algas para salir de las aguas oscuras. Agotado, no puede resistirse a la resaca y las corrientes traicioneras que amenazan con arrastrarlo bajo las olas. En este momento crítico, le sorprende la hermosa visión de una joven sentada en la roca con la piel de un color blanco nacarado y los labios abiertos entonando una canción. Su expresión es enigmática y no sabemos si le ayudará o le hará daño, pero no hay duda de que el marinero está hechizado por su pálida belleza y su mágica melodía.


“ Who would be

A mermaid fair,

Singing alone,

Combing her hair…”

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

· Inspired in John William Waterhouse

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Defeated I
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Dormant Sentinels protected these lands for centuries. activated for the fog of war every few thousand and hundred years. Technology grows as more ancient sentinels fall. Mighty warriors of a golden era.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Catch Of The Day
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
What if, in an alternate reality, one could fish for the sun and moon to change morning into night and night into morning?

With this piece, it will alternate between the First Catch of the Day and Last Catch of the Day depending on our actual time of day in the real world.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Sean Connery
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The name’s Connery, Sean Connery. What better way to continue the ICON series than with 007 himself. The epitome of cool, Connery captivated audiences for decades with his portrayal of James Bond. He embodied the character so naturally, and in doing so set the benchmark for what it means to be a Gentleman. This film still, from the first scene of the first Bond movie ever released, sets the tone for the rest of the franchise.

The master is bundled with three layers. The owner of the master will receive ownership over all three layers and will be able to customize the chip count by altering the colors of the poker plaques. White = $1,000, Yellow = $2,000, Pink = $5,000, Blue = $10,000, Purple = $100,000, Orange = $500,000, and Red = $1,000,000. Right now Bond has $2,000 pushed in, but it’s up to you to decide how much he has at stake in the next hand. And if for some reason Lady Luck isn’t on your side, well there’s nothing a Vesper martini can’t cure. Shaken, not stirred of course. 

In addition to the master and all of the layers, the owner will receive the unique 1/1 framed polaroid set of the 12 original polaroids used to create this NFT. The frame measures 20'' x 15'' and will come with a signed certificate of authenticity.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Steve's Golden Apples
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Steve's Golden Apples reflects the charisma, anger, and brilliance of the late Steve Jobs. During the day, Steve was an incredible entrepreneur and user of trailblazing technologies. Behind closed doors, he was known for his ruthless character and polarizing attitude. This composition presents the founder's golden apples stirring in a melting pot of ideas and innovation. The piece also features the original Apple Macintosh personal computer from 1984. 

During the daytime, Steve is happy and productive. At night, anger sweeps over his mind, and the apples disappear.

"Innovation distinguishes between a leader and a follower." - Steve Jobs

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: CROM SAGE
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: CROM's last hope in battle is to wave the summoning banner of his Toad Sage and invoke an ancient arcane creature from The Nether. Crom's summoned sage crosses the portal of the Nether and goes into flaming mode vanquishing any threats.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Cyber Watch
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
CYBER WATCH

This is the first big collab The Guild has made on Async. It is based on the famous painting The Night Watch by Rembrandt (1642). This was initiated and coordinated by Rutger van der Tas.

A total of 34 layers make this Cyber Watch containing 107 different states made by 33 artists. Some of them are very well-known and some are up and coming.

We are all familiar with the famous painting and the composition of the original work by Rembrandt, therefore this digital piece is easily readable although it is a cacophony of styles and colors.

Rutger did not want to hold back the creativity by giving a set of rules. No themes, no color palette was assigned. Just the creative flow and the story every artist wanted to tell. They had to feel the freedom to do whatever they wanted.

Every artist was supplied with a figure or piece of the surroundings in the original painting. No one was able to pick a place, a spot or character on beforehand.

After dividing the canvas into separate layers and giving them a number, an online randomizer was used to divide them. This was done three times to get three different options. After this, a vote was made to choose which of the three variations was going to be used. This was done in a special Nachtwacht Telegram group.

All artists involved worked hard on their contribution even though we have all been impacted by Covid-19 directly or indirectly.

Being in a lockdown or not free to move in the way we used too, makes this online NFT art community very important. For both artists and collectors this online realm filled our lives in so many ways.

We are the Cyber Watch.

Participating artists from background to foreground:

Sparrow, Silje Thorn, Surreal Serpentine,  Moxarra Gonzalez, FtrSaroth, Loudsqueak, Lapin Mignon, Tom Abbink, Sarah Zucker, Talos, Nika Danny, Arvid Hjorth, ejthek, Benza, Legendary, Rutger van der Tas, Becca Kennedy, Shelly Soneja, Mehak Jain, Airco Caravan, pplpleasr, Fabin Rasheed, The Perfesser, Stellabelle, Matt Kane, Coldie 3D, Shinji Akhirah, Ytje Veenstra, Orabelart, Danil Pan, Jetski, Angie Taylor, SamJ Studios.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Stellar Goddesses
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Have you ever gazed up at the sky and wondered what magical mysteries lie above? Who is in control when the yellow sun that shines bright or when the blue moon appears at night, glowing, surrounded by stars? What if I told you that there are goddesses up above blessing us with their magical, stellar aura everyday? Do you believe in stellar goddesses? 

With this piece, it will alternate between Stellar Goddess and Cosmic Consciousness depending on our actual time of day in the real world.

ABOUT THE ARTIST:

My name is Shaylin Wallace or Shay the Surrealist and this is my second tokenized NFT artwork! I specializes in creating surreal, yet minimal compositions by manipulating stock images using Adobe Photoshop. In 2014, I started editing images on apps such as PicsArt and Union App and overtime, I found my passion which is manipulating images in surrealistic ways. In 2017, I saved up enough money to purchase my very first laptop and soon after got an Adobe subscription and downloaded Photoshop! Since then, I have designed hundreds of unique photo-manipulations and many amazing series as well. Welcome to my Imagination.
Warning: Your Mind May Be Blown Away!

Check out more of my artwork: https://www.smwvisuals.com/photo-manipulations 

Thank you in advance if you collect this piece!
Shaylin Wallace | https://www.smwvisuals.com/

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: I needed color. A day/night/sunrise/sunset async art piece around color gradients

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: It's Here
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
It's Here is a physical traditional oil painting on canvas, 30x40'' (76x100 cm) made between February and July 2020 in Boston, Massachusetts USA, and adapted for Async on February 2021.
This piece shows Chico the Bear lying on the grass. The original oil painting is the night state of this programmable art piece, and it shows a crane from an UFO catcher machine.
For this piece I wanted to show a more story driven image, leaving the interpretation  to the viewer, since you don't know if the crane is going to rescue or kidnap the bear, either way I wanted to show an intriguing and somehow anxiety inducing picture.
Many people have seen the original piece in my studio and I've received a wide variety of reactions, from anxiety to joy.
The buyer of this programmable art piece will get a professional giclee reproduction of the original oil painting, printed with pigment inks, lightfast and archival, signed and numbered. Comes with certificate of authenticity.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: My Lovely Cyborg - Corinna
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: The fakeness of the seductress. The long process of disassembling herself before going to bed. The girl with hollow jaws, untwisting cables and wires to finally sleep - In this art piece, by mixing layers, you’ll get different art compositions that range from full color to an entire black and white art and something in between.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
2020 saw a generation of people experience two recessions and a pandemic. We now sit at the fringe of post-humanism connected to a future of uncertainty driven by tech systems. We are indoctrinate now. There is no going back. The cyber punk fantasy is fast becoming reality.

Will the ominous depictions of the future from movies, novels and video games come to fruition? One nation under tech.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Mother
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: If you are alive, that means you have an unbroken lineage of ancestors tracing back through the millennia - back to not only the mother of all humans on our own little branch of evolution, but back to the first creature crawling out of the sea, back to the first single celled organism, back to the first instance of matter that spontaneously coagulated in the primordial soup with the ability to replicate. From here, our biological ancestry crosses over into chemical ancestry. From the matter of this earth our ancestors were formed, and from the matter of this earth we are all born. The ever-present mother is with us in life and death. Day and night. Everywhere and always.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: The sunrise starts with sun kissed banana drops, then into the daytime we are treated with chewy blossom strawberries. As our day comes to a close the cave evolves into a rich liquorice berry swizzle pop. At night the sweets all press together forming crushed fizzy bubble twirls.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Changes is the only thing that hasn’t been changed. From time to space to the thoughts of human beings are constantly changing. I transformed a Silver Gelatin Photogram (a piece of physical photograph made of alternative photographic processes) into a digital image that even can produce endless changes. This is based on the change in my way of seeing the world. It is difficult for individuals to completely isolate themselves from their own inherent culture, this ingrained imprint not only stems from families but also social and historical influences. Besides, the rapid innovation of science and technologies directly drives the world today to inevitably facing collisions and fusions in multiculturalism. Studying classical philosophical text allows me to apply the dialectical method to tease those open questions, and finally ground on my artworks. All things complement each other and balance in the collision. Changes is the key. Isn’t the development of human civilization that come to the present evolve in indistinct ways?
