0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Marilyn Monroe
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
One of the most iconic figures in American history, Marilyn Monroe was a symbol of beauty. Much like Bitcoin itself, she represented something new and exciting and swept American culture off its feet. But underneath all of her glam, Monroe was on fire - one that enveloped her day and night and ultimately led to her early demise. 

From the ashes the phoenix rises and we now find ourselves in the midst of a new cultural revolution, led by the flames of the crypto movement.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Composable Me (Part I: Spring)
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Hello, world—I just minted myself as an interface.

The avatar you see is me, about to embark on a six month creative journey that you co-lead. This is my genesis NFT.

Equip my feet, my hands, and my torso with six unlocked wearables to determine my creative tools, environment, and approach. I will check in with the Master Layer daily, and document the process and results on my socials.

Three dynamic layers each include three state-changes:

1. Hands = Tools:

- paint palette & brush - "painting"
- violin & bow - "music"
- empty hands

2. Chest = Environment:

- coder tee - "digital"
- burner tee - "analog"
- blank tee

3. Feet = Approach:

- hiking boots - "explorations"
- tightrope - "exercises"
- bare feet

How the states of these three layers interact, shapes the output. If wearables remain unchanged, then I'll dive deeper in that direction. If wearables switch often, I'll make that part of the process.

In this way, layer owners can be as hands-on or hands-off as they want. I will keep going regardless. I believe that wonderful things emerge from where chance and intention meet... Also major #fails, which are a part of this too!

# Locked Inventory

Every two months, a new NFT unlocks six new wearables, and the previous get retired. The performance moves containers in this way, and I will look to the new Master Layer for creative prompts.

At the end of six months, there will be a surprise gift sent out to the original owners of all three NFTs, as a thank you for being my first supporters and co-creators in this space.

# About Me

I've spent the better part of a decade making visual art, and now find myself circling back to my first loves: music and tech. You can get a sense of my work and career at www.wi-ch.com

This project is a blockchain-first interactive performance piece. I hope it inspires others to engage with their own creativity in strange & wonderful new ways. I am sincerely grateful to all my supporters, collaborators, and mentors, past, future, present, and in parallel timelines^^

Showing up every day to create, in relationship to this space and the greater world, is my commitment to approaching life as art—with purpose, playfulness, and a generous misting of magic.

You can find me on IG @weseeclearly, where all my other socials are linked.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Kids Aren't Alright
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
When we were young the future was so bright,
The old neighborhood was so alive
And every kid on the whole damn street,
Was going to make it big in every beat.
Now the neighborhood's cracked and torn
The kids are grown up but their lives are worn
How can one little street swallow so many lives?

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Conflate
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The human ego is both powerful and dangerous. The line between an inflated sense of self and grounded self aware is fine. Stray too far from the line either side and we leave our grounded reality. Reality is ready to knock you the fuck out when you stray too far.

We are prone to conflate trivial results with a sense of purpose and growth. We use tools to feed our ego. Drugs, money and a collective mania are a whirlwind of confirmation bias that have you thinking you are the shit. It means nothing, don’t conflate the randomness of the universe with how great you are.
In this piece, three symbols are feeding the ego.

Ethereum, symbolising how many artists are prone to conflate the value of their art to how skilled they are.

Xanax, Symbolising our constant need to use substances to step away from reality, but feel like we are partaking. Xanax has become a modern day classic for younger generations to use. Xanax makes everything feel great. The drug that makes you think there are no problems, making it one of the most dangerous drugs used.  Use this for too long and ego death is imminent.

Tulips, This is a pointer toward a time in history called ‘Tulip Mania’. See below
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tulip_mania

Are we going through a similar situation with Crypto and NFT? Have the troubles of lock down pushed society to find value elsewhere which is doomed to fail? Only time will tell. Collective thinking can be the hive minded ego inflation that destroys economies. Remember 2009 when hope destroyed peoples livelihoods. A whole system built on hope and ego.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: HOWL
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Order of the Stone Warriors
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Ancient titans appeared from mysterious portals causing havoc and destroying everything on their paths. With their monstrous Swords crushing entire towns in one blow they seemed invincible. Today their corpses decorate our land while our protectors are dormant in their stone forms. The day a titan comes back, those statues we admire will come back to life to take them down once again. Hail our saints of the Stone Warriors Order.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Ethereams
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The Ethereams is one of the code-based future civilizations. Ethereams are pieces of code deployed on the multiverse network that contains soul data from our ancestors which lived on earth thousands years ago.

This is the only species in the multiverse that has preserved characteristics from humans, the form and the emotions. They are considered the most superior species in existence due to the emotional capabilities which were implemented by the oracle when the developers found a lost capsule containing the last records from human civilization.

Video games played a strong role in shaping my creative intrigue as a child. Video games old and new help me through difficult times. They offer immersion like no other form of entertainment. Nostalgia harbours strong feelings for gamers such as myself. The epic wins, stories and worlds experienced is unique when compared to passive forms of media.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Voxorium
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Voxorium is a 3D, generative, sound-reactive and hence interactive sculpture - A peaceful art that flutters with sound.
The final interactive artwork can be experienced at: https://nurecas.github.io/voxorium 
or at: 
https://ipfs.io/ipfs/QmZJqEUoiMGhmdKWN8EZKjP2NNhXa77foTQSghSFBzTgt5

Voxorium is not only a sound-reactive work, but can also record a conversation, a music clip or an audio moment in the form of a 3D sculpture and an .ogg file. As soon as you load Voxorium, recording begins. Pressing the enter button will download the image, the audio recording and the sound sculpture model (GLTF) corresponding to the conversation. This image/sculpture will be unique and hence can be preserved as a memory/representation of that conversation/music etc. ( Maximum recording time is 1 minute, after which the file will be auto-downloaded. ) Thus, the artwork goes beyond just interaction, but also into creation - in the form of a memorabilia of a conversation/music.

The pandemic of 2020 had forced us to be inside our homes. When 2021 started I had renewed hopes, but things remained the same. I started to experience a lot of silence around me. And to my own consternation, the silence grew such that any sound around me made an indescribable impact on me. Perhaps it’s easier to say I became more sensitive to sound. With Voxorium I wanted to create generative variants, but I wanted to go beyond assigning a random number and generating with code. I wanted to give it a human touch. My heightened sensitivity drove me into listening to those subtle sounds around me which I usually comfortably ignore. I realised each of these sounds had a memory, a thought or a feeling attached to it. I decided to “visualise” these sounds. I recorded these sounds (33 in total) and played it through different unique variants of Voxorium and used the generated images as layers for this art. I also added, the memory, thought or feeling associated with the sounds in the description of each layer. Thus the artwork is also a collection of myself in parts and is such that “the whole becomes the part becomes the whole becomes the part”

A note on privacy - 
1. Voxorium is completely front-end based and does not store any sound data/recording. All recording happens in the browser only. The experience best works on Desktop. 
2. I decided to keep all recordings and 3d models corresponding to the layers to myself, but have shared the image and the story related to it in the layers.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: “Morpheus and Iris”
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Inspired in Morpheus and Iris,  painted in 1811 by Pierre-Narcisse Guérin.

This painting most probably relates to the Roman poet Ovid’s version of the tale of Alcyone and Ceyx.

Ceyx dies during a storm at sea, and so the goddess Juno decides that his wife, Alcyone, must be informed of his passing with all haste. Iris, the messenger goddess, is dispatched by Juno to Somnus, the personification of sleep, with instructions that Alcyone should be told that very night in a dream.

Somnus sends forth his son, Morpheus, god of sleep and dreams, who changes his appearance to match that of Ceyx, and enters the dream world of Alcyone.

Dripping with seawater, Morpheus, as Ceyx, tells Alcyone of his passing, and commands that funeral rites are undertaken. In her dream, Alcyone attempts to grab hold of her husband, but as she goes to touch Morpheus, so she awakens; but Morpheus has done his job, for Alcyone now knows that she is a widow.

For all Matrix fans this is how the character Morpheus’ name was chosen, in reference to the god of dreams, as the Matrix world was merely a form of dream.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: HORIZON
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
We grow by stretching ourselves and exploring the wondrous worlds that beyond our current abilities and understandings.
Words by Jim Kwick.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Bob Marley
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Bob Marley is a shining beacon of happiness for people all over the world.  Throughout his life he channeled his aura into his music and shared it with millions of people worldwide. Growing up listening to his music had a huge influence on my perspective on life and on my artwork. He encouraged people to spread love and to enjoy the little things in life, like a beautiful sun setting over the ocean or birds flying against a bright blue sky. 

For this piece, I tried to channel Bob Marley's positive energy and carefree essence, complimenting his portrait with beautiful scenes I've snapped around the world, melding his spirit with nature, where it belongs and now rests. Bob Marley lives on in so many others through his positive influence, as he said himself "My richness is life, forever".

"...and when it happens, I won't be holding on".

Inspired by the opening track of the Tame Impala album "Currents". The concept of changing and personal transformation and falling into the mindset to stop fighting for control and allowing nature to take its course. 

Made in Photoshop.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Wave
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
If we lose a loved one, are they gone forever? 

A human being is a pattern of information moving through spacetime as a wave. The matter that makes you is ever changing as you absorb and expel molecules throughout each day. Every 7-10 years almost all the cells in your body will have been replaced. You are not a physical thing. You are a pattern. 

Your pattern is not contained by your physical form. Your actions in this world will connect and intertwine your pattern with- and into the minds of others. 

When you die, some details of your pattern will be lost - but all those whose minds you’ve touched, will still hold you within them.

A memory is a physical pattern of strengthened connections between neurons in a brain. For as long as your memory is carried, your pattern will still exist in this world. Still affecting people, their actions, their dreams and their future.  

Your thoughts, values and aspirations can still propagate long after your physical form has ceased to exist. Immortality is possible, but it is up to you to set it in motion.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Dissipation
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
When you are dissipated you can't hold yourself solid. You're there, like water. Like muddy water. You can't swim and you can't see. You have to imagine a lifeboat and try to get on it, as your life depends on it.

When the boat never comes you have to sort through the spiral. 
You look into the eye.
And you sit tight, waiting for your judgment. 

This is a work about trauma. Is a work about a journey that never ends. 
Each layer depicts a state of mind, a chance for a voice to be heard.

For all the girls who don't have a name. 

"As a seashell.
They had to call and call
And pick the worms off me like sticky pearls.

Dying
Is an art, like everything else. "
excerpt from Lady Lazarus, by Sylvia Plath

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: 24 Hours in The City That Never Sleeps
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
NYC is a place filled with sensory delights any time of the day. In this work there are four different autonomous state changes representing different times of the day: shining sunrise, bright afternoon, magic hour sunset, and late night escapades. 

We live in a world that is constantly shifting every second. Let's take a minute to celebrate the humanity that bonds all of us. 24 Hours in The City That Never Sleeps is a piece about all the people that bring the big city to life. Each Frank has it's own unique story, self-expression, and energy. Each day we cross paths, form new connections, and try to leave our positive mark on the world. Frank is an extension of everyone. Helping others helps everyone. Let's be Frank.

Frank Ape is a mystical creature who lives amongst the humans but without human restrictions.  What started as a form of self-expression on the streets of NYC for artist Brandon Sines quickly turned into a movement for the people.

 Frank has special powers that he continues to discover as he is tested by the many challenges of life. Frank champions positivity and equality, and cares about all living things. He believes in using imagination and play to inspire other people and animals through thoughtful actions.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: DOMINION
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
OPUS 117 / CIRCUIT X16 /  YEAR 2396 

The city keeps growing, tons of food arrives everyday and 100% of the population have a job. Circuit’s authorities say that great things are coming for Opus 117.

The Senate gather with circuit's leaders, they tell them what they want to hear, they offer freedom, as long as citizens don’t leave Opus 117. Authorities at Encoder have released The Guardians to keep citizens in line. Riots overtake the circuit, people want to leave. 

Revolution is imminent.


-
(Modeling in Cinema 4D and rendered with Arnold.)

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: / COPYCAT /
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Some great artists spend years developing a style, technique and a subject matter that is unique. They spend a lot of time and effort to mark their own style.
And one day you wake up to see that some copycat took all your ideas as a shortcut to being successful and is making quick copies of your work, pretending that this is all his/her ideas.

 Can you imagine what style Frida Kahlo, Vincent van Gogh, Gustav Klimt and Picasso would create if they copied each other?
In this little artistic canvas is happening right now! Look at them playing like childs !!

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Art Vandal
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
When i was in Paris, i was drawn to these designated poster spaces in metros. One poster stuck on top of each other, some torn off, crumbling, thick; layers and layers of musicians, cinema, sports, commercials and some vandalised by public too, by scribbling. 

These interventions led to abstract imagery formed within those framed borders. I then methodically travelled across all the metro rail routes, stopping at all stations. Carefully observing how each poster space had evolved over time and deterioration, documenting photographically these abstracts that were formed with time, erosion and human intervention. I titled the project "Art Vandal" as i believed these actions and interventions shape up the final form that i was able to observe then. 

I was not sure of how to exhibit these images with the same effect that one could have while viewing those frames in metro station. Hence it lay dormant for years with me. When i was introduced to Async Art and programmable art I was curious to explore this project in terms of interactivity. Hence I pulled different elements from around 75 images as individual layers. With each layer the viewer/buyer has the choice to change between different elements, thus giving rise to unique set of abstracts with different backgrounds depending on the choices made.

This way of showcasing the project, I believe hold justice to the whole idea itself, not letting go off the various interactions that go in to creating a unique piece every time; just like those poster frames.

While material goods may bring you a moment of comfort. The financial freedom to do what you want, when you want, and who you want to do it with, is really the opportunity to do what your heart desires....YOUR pursuit of happiness.  

So smile and do what makes you happy.

"Money is a terrible master but an excellent servant"

Buddyart00

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Remixable Kiss
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
A programmable NFT where 12 lovers are cut out of six paintings, masterpieces of art history covering a time span of six centuries:

Giotto - Incontro alla Porta d'Oro (1303-1305)
François Gérard - Psyché et l'Amour (1798)
Francesco Hayez - il Bacio (1859)
Dante Gabriel Rossetti - Paolo and Francesca da Rimini (1867)
Jean-Léon Gérôme - Pygmalion et Galatée (1890)
Gustav Klimt - Der Kuss (1907-1908)

3 layers with 6 states each for a journey to discover the most surprising and daring kisses, where men and women are mixed for a conceptual and technical realization that is my artistic contribution to the exaltation of contemporary possibilities of programmable nfts, with a respectful eye to the historical heritage of classical art and with the privilege of knowing that in every part of this artwork there's the brushstroke of a master and the energy of his spirit and his time.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Eight Nomads
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
You are in control of this story: Eight protagonists, each facing multiple choices. 

An epic journey into ancient worlds, magical forests and eerie landscapes.

This is a programmable NFT of 4 layers with respectively 7, 8, 7, 8 choices. 

Immerse yourself into this dark and spiritual narrative, explore the wilderness and adventure through artifacts of a lost past. Mysterious creatures and characters will fill your imagination and carry you to new planes, loose your consciousness into the ethereal and celestial worlds here portrayed. 

You will choose the fate of these travelers, heroes of an unsung future that will tell their stories through the time and sing their melodies vibrating ripples throughout the universe.

Secrets are hidden within, but it's up to you to weave the harmonies you choose, and create legends that will be forever told. 

Will you help them reach their destination, if there is one?

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: "Untitled #2", from "Slits in Depth" series (2020/ 2021)
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This is the second work from the series of 3D anaglyph images “Slits in Depth”. 
“Untitled #2” was created and edited during The Great Lockdown. It has five layers: four dynamic and one static.

The background layer (“Exteriors”) presents landscapes photographed during some of my walks in the forest. The middle layer (“Resistance Band”) was shot in my studio with artificial light. And the top three layers (“Interior #1”, “#2” and “#3”) depict geometric architectural details from the place I live.

10% of the sales of the master and its layers is reserved for Acerola Fund (acerola.eth), intended for the purchase of NFTs created by other artists.

Pedro Victor Brandão
March, 2021

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Experimental No.1 #9796
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Changes is the only thing that hasn’t been changed. From time to space to the thoughts of human beings are constantly changing. I transformed a Silver Gelatin Photogram (a piece of physical photograph made of alternative photographic processes) into a digital image that even can produce endless changes. This is based on the change in my way of seeing the world. It is difficult for individuals to completely isolate themselves from their own inherent culture, this ingrained imprint not only stems from families but also social and historical influences. Besides, the rapid innovation of science and technologies directly drives the world today to inevitably facing collisions and fusions in multiculturalism. Studying classical philosophical text allows me to apply the dialectical method to tease those open questions, and finally ground on my artworks. All things complement each other and balance in the collision. Changes is the key. Isn’t the development of human civilization that come to the present evolve in indistinct ways?

Community is the fabric that unites us all. Celebrate each other and be a positive member of your neighborhood. Say hello, offer to lend a helping hand, talk to the animals, and keep an eye out for aliens. As the collector of this work of art you can customize the piece by controlling the amount of Franks, animals, and six different times of the day. How you compose the different states of each layer helps tell a story of a moment in time in the neighborhood.

We live in a world that is constantly shifting every second. Let's take a minute to celebrate the humanity that bonds all of us.  Each Frank has it's own unique story, self-expression, and energy. Each day we cross paths, form new connections, and try to leave our positive mark on the world. Frank is an extension of everyone. Helping others helps everyone. Let's be Frank.

Frank Ape is a mystical creature who lives amongst the humans but without human restrictions.  What started as a form of self-expression on the streets of NYC for artist Brandon Sines quickly turned into a movement for the people. Frank has special powers that he continues to discover as he is tested by the many challenges of life. Frank champions positivity and equality, and cares about all living things. He believes in using imagination and play to inspire other people and animals through thoughtful actions.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Old Ethereum Art
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Addition to my quest for visualising complexity of computational thinking and using data as my paint. With the service of AI (artificial intelligence) such as generative adversarial network (GAN) and many other to create amalgamations to analyse form by an artistic thinking with the help of machine intelligence. Not a single source from any original art is used to create these paintings. All images used for training are beautiful google earth satellite shots . The model itself ended up giving it vibes of unique historic art movement styles. Just to get philosophical, As we have not yet figured out what conscious itself is, then how can we define what art should be.

Ref: https://www.flatarc.io/crypto-art
​
Also a unique opportunity when you need to think about parametric form with unusual physics which cannot exist in reality, this is where machine intelligence services you with power of exploring unusual and other-worldly forms and experiences. Refer my other 'Data Art' project pages for more about inspirations. This current piece of work was a tribute to the fascinating, daring Ethereum-crypto-community and people who love decentralisation. Unbelievable paradigm shift that will change everything that we know as norms.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
High on Boba is originally a physical traditional oil painting on canvas, 30x40’’ (76x100 cm) made in January 2020 in Boston, Massachusetts USA, and adapted for Async on March 2021.
This piece is the first oil painting I ever made. It shows my character Milo drinking something that looks like green tea with boba.
In this programmable NFT version, the painting goes into Dark Mode during the night and can be seen glowing as if it were under UV light.
High on Boba was part of the ROX/SE Art Show at the Piano Craft Gallery in Boston, MA September 4, 2020 - September 27, 2020.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: RGB Geometry
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Explore the basic building blocks of The Project using geometry and colour in this programmable NFT consisting of 3 layers.

By superimposing three beams of red, green and blue light each of a given intensity, one has the ability to generate an array of different colours. We are exposed to this mixing of light throughout our lives, take a moment and appreciate these colours in their purest form. Red (255, 0, 0). Green (0, 255, 0). Blue (0, 0, 255).

But what is light and colour without shape and form? This NFT showcases 6 different geometric primitives. If you look hard enough these primitives are all around us at both a macro and micro level. Bound by points and lines and then assembled into a mesh of polygons, choose your primitive.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Lake Garda... WabiSabi in Italy.
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
• TEST THE ARTWORK: before you decide to purchase, you can test and play around with the Master by triggering changes to the States of the Layers (3 Layers + 16 States = 150 possible combinations) by going to this link:
https://www.tonycorocher.com/nft-digitalart/AsyncArt/lakeGarda

• DESCRIPTION:
This artwork is kind of a consequence of the time I spent in Japan during the previous years and of my learning about their culture and the WabiSabi aesthetic principles so dear to the Japanese way of life. 
Once I got back to Italy I decided to apply these concepts to the beauty of my country and selected Lake Garda as one of the possible options. I spent about 2 weeks going around the lake, waking up very early in the morning to try to catch the right light, the right atmosphere, the fog and the nature waking up to the new day and took about 1000 photographs.
Then, to create this NFT digital artwork I spent another 3 weeks putting together, combining and "fusing" these images into a series of possible combinations which not only had to look natural, but, most importantly, had to always reflect what I was looking at and the atmosphere of one of the most beautiful locations in Italy. 

I had a lot of fun creating this artwork, but the intricacy, clarity and smoothness of the combinations was no joke. Perspective, depth of field, main subjects, secondary subjects and backgrounds all had to be thought and imagined during the shooting, much before getting to the editing (which was no joke either). I sincerely hope this can be seen in the final artwork.

This NFT digital artwork is composed of 1 Master, 3 Layers and 16 states which can be triggered from the Layers to change the Master in 150 possible combinations. It is n.5 in the "WabiSabi" NFT Collection.

www.tonycorocher.com

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Lone Rider
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Few images are more iconic to American culture than the figure of the lone cowboy. Heading out West on horseback for the promise of a better life, this rider will trek on through sunrise, daytime, sunset and nighttime. Watch as the sky changes color and the stars come out at night. 

By peeling away the borders for this mosaic, I reveal the Polaroid's nature, rugged and true, like the cowboy himself.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Genesis
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This is my genesis NFT artwork. It is about navigating the merger of the physical and digital worlds which is being made possible by the lock and key otherwise known as an NFT. It is about the rebirth of being and the merger of man and technology. It is about a brave new space that we as a collective can shape in a way that supports and serves everyone. A celebration of continual growth, connection, dreaming big, and that a rising tide lifts all ships.

This work of art started as an abstract painting on canvas. At one point in the process imagery started to make its way into the painting. At the time I was falling in love and reaching new clarity on many things in my life. Without a doubt these things found their way into the painting, and the original painting  can be seen in the "sunrise state."

I worked on the painting for a few months and then had to travel for a while. When I got back to the studio I decided the painting was finished. This was 2017.

Fast forward to 2021 when I entered my first NFTs.tips clubhouse room in February. For a week straight I participated in amazing conversations for 8+ hours a day about the possibilities of NFT’s and the metaverse and my mind started to explode. One aspect of NFTs that I found particularly interesting was the ability to add conceptual things into the smart contract that were inherently tied to the NFT itself. This is the reason I decided to drop my first NFT on Async Art.

Overflowing with inspiration and new knowledge I took the painting from 2017 and began to paint into it with Procreate. Almost 100 hours of logged time later, and countless more conversations on clubhouse, I present to the world “Genesis.”

Day/Night feature was chosen to showcase the work in color and black and white but also an added transparency of showing important steps of the creative process in the "states" of sunrise and sunset. 

Sunrise shows the original physical painting, which turns to the digital/analog hybrid version throughout the day. At sunset the digital layer of color is shown separate, which then changes into the final digital/analog painting for the duration of the night.

As a painter the process is integral to how I reach a final image. Now with this autonomous NFT I think it’s amazing to give the collector ownership and insight into this process.

Being able to experience the same imagery in various states activates the idea of continuous change. The symbolism in the painting is open to interpretation as well as reflective of our current times of entering the metaverse. The act of seeing the painting in process is also meant to remind us that everything is a work in progress and it’s the process itself that gives meaning to existence.

Sunrise State -  Original painting on canvas
Day State – Black and White final version hybrid of digital and analog painting.
Sunset State – Layer of color digital painting.
Night State – Full color final version hybrid of digital and analog painting.

Bio: Over the last 20 years Ari Lankin has extensively developed painted languages exploring abstraction, conceptual process, and realism. His current paintings are intentionally open to interpretation and rich in visceral sensation. They encourage experienced based conversations on the universe and mankind. They hover between mystical and scientific. The physicality of paint, intuition, memory, and exploration are crucial aspects of his practice. His last solo show in New York City in 2020 completely sold out, he has two murals on public display at World Trade Center 3, and he has had major signature product collaborations with TROJAN™ Condoms and Adidas.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Magic Place
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Ever feel like you're in the center of the universe but at the same time somewhere in the far reaches of it?

Close your eyes and take a deep breath. Let the calm fill you and float in a sea of bliss. That is your Magic Place. A place that always exists inside of you.

This piece is a reminder at any time of the day, no matter where you are or how busy you may be, that you can take a break. Take as long as you need and remember the beauty of life and everything around you are all right there when you decide to open your eyes again.

I continually find myself observing how metropolises incorporate nature into their city planning and how people find unique spaces and make them their own. Finding or creating your own secret magical space is an artform everyone can practice.

Frank Ape is a mystical creature who lives amongst the humans but without human restrictions. What started as a form of self-expression on the streets of NYC for artist Brandon Sines quickly turned into a movement for the people. Frank has special powers that he continues to discover as he is tested by the many challenges of life. Frank champions positivity and equality, and cares about all living things. He believes in using imagination and play to inspire other people and animals through thoughtful actions.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: "Will I Meet You There?"
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
“Out beyond ideas of wrong and right there is a field. I'll meet you there. When the soul lies down in that grass the world is too full to talk about.” - Rumi

This piece was inspired by "The Great Wagon" by Rumi as well as the song "Julia (or, 'Holy to the LORD' on the Bells of Horses)" by mewithoutYou. Thanks to the assets provided by AsyncArt, this piece is made up of four editable layers with three of them consisting of 8 different states of color combinations that will influence the overall image. If these layers happen to have different owners, then they have the option to sync up colors to create a homogeneous piece or diverge paths to create a different blend of colors to their liking. The choice is theirs (and potentially yours!)

Thank you for viewing.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Experimental No.1 #3074
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Changes is the only thing that hasn’t been changed. From time to space to the thoughts of human beings are constantly changing. I transformed a Silver Gelatin Photogram (a piece of physical photograph made of alternative photographic processes) into a digital image that even can produce endless changes. This is based on the change in my way of seeing the world. It is difficult for individuals to completely isolate themselves from their own inherent culture, this ingrained imprint not only stems from families but also social and historical influences. Besides, the rapid innovation of science and technologies directly drives the world today to inevitably facing collisions and fusions in multiculturalism. Studying classical philosophical text allows me to apply the dialectical method to tease those open questions, and finally ground on my artworks. All things complement each other and balance in the collision. Changes is the key. Isn’t the development of human civilization that come to the present evolve in indistinct ways?

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Humachine Imaginarium
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Humachine Imaginarium was a collaboration between me, Ashna Sahir and the AI model GPT3. Through guided creation, we tried to find out what a text-only language model imagines - what does an AI imagine? It involved asking GPT3 to construct a scene from its imagination. The text was then used step by step by Ashna to draw the scene. A beautiful scene was created, and of particular interest were the last few lines where GPT3 reflects on the meaning of the creation, purpose of existence and its relation to the person collaborating.
This work is permanently exhibited at the esteemed AI Art Gallery of NeurIPS 2020.

"Perhaps it is time for sandstorms, to fly through the clouds, to paint with smoke; time to see, time to try another beat, to send everything to hell; time to collapse, to stop avoiding looks, time to make time. Perhaps it's time to change. "


This NFT shows us metaphors about time and life's choices. By changing each layer, you create a different story and a different perception of time.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Anxiety
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The piece works on the GMT time zone. The morning anxiety is soft hazy pink. Into night the colours become saturated representing a nocturnal anxiety. The colours used are to represent the time of day but in a hypnagogic setting.

Anxiety is now snowballing in our culture especially amongst younger generations.  This art piece concentrates on the most intense moment of anxiety. The feeling of helplessness mixed with a rush needing to take action. Xanax has become a popular drug to quell feelings of anxiety. The drug has been popularised in several sub cultures.

The reflective floor is a commentary on the complete loss of self awareness during our most anxious moments. Anxiety is a loss of control, our mind looses rational determination and contemplation. 

Xanax is a drug which destroys families and lives.  Many high profile suicides have been attributed to Xanax. 

Xanax also known as Alprazolam which is a Benzodiazepine. Benzodiazepines are known to ease all feelings of uncertainty and fear, offering the human psyche a feeling of being infallible. This makes the drug highly addictive due to the sense, that nothing is ever wrong. 

I grew up watching my farther completely numbed because of his Xanax addiction. It allowed him rationalise horrendous choices. It hurt and tore apart my family.  Blackouts are common on Xanax depriving Xanax users of all accountability.

At least anxiety allows you to feel, despite it being a shit feeling. I'd rather have a lifetime of feeling then numb myself to experience nothing. Learn from your anxiety, with help and support from friends and family we can learn to control our anxiety. Drugs are just a tool they don’t fix it. They can make things much worse.

No judgement for anyone struggling with addiction or anxiety, there is always a light at the end of tunnel.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: / DIANA /
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Diana, is inspired by "Diana and Her maidens", an 1898 painting by Edward Robert Hughes.

In Ovid's version of the Metamorphosis poem, a hidden lake appears in the wooded valley of Gargaphie. There, Diana, the goddess of the woods, bathed and rested after a hunt. 
Actaeon, a young hunter, accidentally witnessed the bath of the goddess. In retaliation, Diana splashed him with pool water, cursed him, and transformed into a deer.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Awakening
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: From the sky to space, time ceases to exist. Stand still and observe the multitude of events going on around you. The only certainty in life is change.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: UPrise
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The project is using the day/night feature on AsyncArt.
It is consisted of a transparent digital sculpture formation and the impact that its environment has on the substance and essence of the forms.
Humans refract (and reflect) their own enviroment in many ways and they become transparent to the influence of their personality. Humans are affected by the environment and are part of the nature of the surrundings for the others.
This artwork is also a part of a bigger project which is using traced images of famous artworks from the past as a background visual layer in a very subtle way.
In "UPrise", the day layer is using an artwork by Jean-Michel Basquiat and the night an artwork by Lewis Norman and are a reminder that the past and its products are a part of the enviroment we live in now.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Sleep Study
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Sleep is the most vulnerable state of human existence. Sleep exists in limbo between life and death. For me, portrait has been about getting the raw and vulnerable side of the person.

As a self study, I shot images of myself through a sleep cycle. Each grid shot at a specific time interval, constantly scrutinising and documenting my sleep. I move, in reality and in may be in the dreams too. Each movement flowing from one image to the next. 

The piece is a collection made from 77 images shot. 

By changing layers, would my sleep be disturbed or woken back to the strange reality. 

Could I exist in dreams and sleep alone?

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Reincarnation
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Reincarnation refers to the rebirth of consciousness, character or soul in another body after the death of an organism. This is mysterious and unknowable to ordinary people, and many people believe but cannot prove it.

In the future, technology will be used to digitally transfer the human soul code to another physical body or even a cyborg to achieve immortality. The imagination has always existed in the cyberpunk world concept, and it may even realize the ultimate fantasy of human immortality in the near future.

But whether the coded soul is the original soul is also the same as the reincarnation in the traditional concept. No one can prove its truth, only one's own experience can.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Desert Clockwork
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Genesis piece - Intended as a first programmable art experiment. 

This is my first step into "state-changing" artworks. I wanted to use my skills as a landscape crafter to create a minimal and soothing environment for the viewer to observe.

The artifact in the center represents a sun-position time device from an advanced civilization, sending nodes on remote planets to connect, observe, and learn.

Created in an unbiased graphic engine. 10/04/2021.
@cyrusjameskhan

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Arcana Crypto Tarot
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Welcome to The Arcana Crypto Tarot. This deck features the 22 cards of the traditional Major Arcana as interpreted by 22 individual artists, the product of a spontaneous collaboration between a group of cryptoartists in 2020/2021, all of them inaugural members of Women of Cryptoart (WOCA).

No one quite knows exactly how Tarot cards – the precursor to modern playing cards – were invented, or how they came to make the jump from being entertainment to occult divination tool. Generally it’s agreed that Tarot cards as we know them today evolved in medieval Europe. The symbolic archetypes of Tarot decks remained fairly consistent across the centuries, and many people will recognize the figures of the Hermit, the Fool, the Lovers, the Tower, the Hanged Man, and so on as anchors of Western psychology. 

In using this deck, you may find it useful to consult the cards’ traditional meanings. Much has already been written about these universal archetypes, so for these, we refer you to descriptions of the Rider Waite and other traditionally based Tarot decks. 

However, whenever you use divinatory tools to answer a question or get a perspective on a situation, it’s important to let one’s own associations come to the surface. In other words, the answers are not in the cards. The cards are just a tool to help you discover answers within yourself. That’s the magic.

How this deck works:

Once every 24 hours, a three-card spread is automatically generated. Anyone may visit the spread on any day with a question or concern in mind, and see what insights emerge from contemplating the cards. We invite you to follow your intuition: whenever you feel you have a question or concern, formulate your question and visit the Tarot, and reflect on the day’s reading as it pertains to your situation.

This kind of spread is generally read as follows: 

Left card: What is past, or passing.
Centre card: What is occurring now. 
Right card: What is to come.

However, you may also interpret in other ways. For example, Left card / Centre card / Right card could be: 

What you wish for / the obstacle being presented / how to overcome the obstacle
You / someone else / the relationship
What’s in your heart / what’s in your head / what’s in your spirit

... and so on. There are many more options. What’s important is how you frame the question. Look up Tarot three-card spreads for more suggestions.

Cards in the spread may also appear upside-down – or "reversed”. There are many ways to interpret this reversal. Perhaps the card means the inverse or opposite of its upright intention, or it might be describing an interior, secret or hidden state, or it's indicating a reduced or receding influence. Stay open to the possibilities as you meditate on your question.

We have also included the possibility of duplicate cards in each position. In other words, this spread encompasses three full decks’ worth of card combinations. If the same card turns up in different positions in the reading, simply integrate the message the card is giving you from the perspective of its position in the spread.


Here are a few words from each artist, giving her own particular description of the archetype she chose to depict in this deck.

0
The Fool 
Artist: y0b
A leap into the cliff, a universe of randomness and intent. Colorful hills beyond.

I
The Magician
Artist: Kristy Glas
She is pure and passionate, connected to spiritual and material realms. She seeks balance and knowledge through constant growth.

II
The High Priestess
Artist: Cristiana Vettor (combugnera)
This card indicates the search for female knowledge, clairvoyance, the search for the secret and the future; her knowledge is mostly initiatory, therefore forbidden to most people and reserved only to a few.


III
The Empress
Artist: SpaceDivers
She stands powerful and dancing, between nature and imagination, the pattern of creation and knowledge of birth are flows and breaths of reality, whether material or ethereal. 

IV
The Emperor
Artist: Lulu
Control through intelligence, the strength you need to stand straight.

V
The Hierophant
Artist: Inês Merino
A rite of passage – infinite wisdom and guidance, magic, shining the brightest light within… As we close this chapter, a new beginning unfolds.

VI
The Lovers
Artist: oculardelusion
In the sacred beech grove’s purple light, divine union of requited love, of union with the Divine. All is One.

VII
The Chariot
Artist: The Bad Lament
The Chariot brings forth the brave winged warrioress, with the moon at her back, determined and ambitious.

VIII
Strength
Artist: LUVRworldwide
The aligning of truths in mind-body-spirit, fuels our source from within, empowering a spectrum of peaceful passion and disciplined determination.


IX
The Hermit
Artist: Stina Jones
The hermit ventures forth, carving her own path through the wilderness.

X
The Wheel of Fortune
Artist: Sparrow
The Wheel of Fortune is never not a part of life. When this card appears it is a reminder: change is the only constant.

XI
Justice
Artist: Kitty Bast
“Karma’s a Bitch.”

XII
The Hanged Man
Artist: Daira
It is best to be sure to be willing to change.

XIII
Death
Artist: DaniellaDoodles
While there is death, there is also life - death allows for new growth and change.

XIV
Temperance
Artist: Vanesa Stati
Temperance tests waters with one foot on solid ground, it’s the wise step, the guide from a lower plane to a higher one that enjoys natural protection, which denotes and promove a point of balance: moderation, patience, purpose, tenacity, adaptation, acceptance, harmonization, reason, flow...

XV
The Devil
Artist: Cechk
The seduction of the devil can materialise in the physical realm as well on the mind, it has lust and obsession, it longs for power, but also lives in fear and strives for domination. The Devil is good and bad, and you’re the one that will decide who it will be. 

XVI
The Tower
Artist: Brandi Kyle
A standing reminder of the perils we face, the Tower card depicts possibilities of catastrophe, destruction, renovation, or just simply unexpected change.

XVII
The Star
Artist: Silje Thorn
She is at peace with renewed purpose and hope, nourishing her surroundings with the conscious and the subconscious in equilibrium.

XVIII
The Moon
Artist: St Heresy
As she is kind and sweet, she is also deceptive and dangerously beckoning. She is the holder of your secrets, and she holds no judgement.

XIX
The Sun
Artist: Gisel Florez
Circadian rhythms radiating the ultimate path of purpose & source.  

XX
Judgement
Artist: Marigold
The announcement of a new era is coming. A new World will be born after the Judgement.

XXI
The World
Artist: CrypticFauna

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Arcana Crypto Tarot
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Welcome to The Arcana Crypto Tarot. This deck features the 22 cards of the traditional Major Arcana as interpreted by 22 individual artists, the product of a spontaneous collaboration between a group of cryptoartists in 2020/2021, all of them inaugural members of Women of Cryptoart (WOCA).

No one quite knows exactly how Tarot cards – the precursor to modern playing cards – were invented, or how they came to make the jump from being entertainment to occult divination tool. Generally it’s agreed that Tarot cards as we know them today evolved in medieval Europe. The symbolic archetypes of Tarot decks remained fairly consistent across the centuries, and many people will recognize the figures of the Hermit, the Fool, the Lovers, the Tower, the Hanged Man, and so on as anchors of Western psychology. 

In using this deck, you may find it useful to consult the cards’ traditional meanings. Much has already been written about these universal archetypes, so for these, we refer you to descriptions of the Rider Waite and other traditionally based Tarot decks. 

However, whenever you use divinatory tools to answer a question or get a perspective on a situation, it’s important to let one’s own associations come to the surface. In other words, the answers are not in the cards. The cards are just a tool to help you discover answers within yourself. That’s the magic.

How this deck works:

Once every 24 hours, a three-card spread is automatically generated. Anyone may visit the spread on any day with a question or concern in mind, and see what insights emerge from contemplating the cards. We invite you to follow your intuition: whenever you feel you have a question or concern, formulate your question and visit the Tarot, and reflect on the day’s reading as it pertains to your situation.

This kind of spread is generally read as follows: 

Left card: What is past, or passing.
Centre card: What is occurring now. 
Right card: What is to come.

However, you may also interpret in other ways. For example, Left card / Centre card / Right card could be: 

What you wish for / the obstacle being presented / how to overcome the obstacle
You / someone else / the relationship
What’s in your heart / what’s in your head / what’s in your spirit

... and so on. There are many more options. What’s important is how you frame the question. Look up Tarot three-card spreads for more suggestions.

Cards in the spread may also appear upside-down – or "reversed”. There are many ways to interpret this reversal. Perhaps the card means the inverse or opposite of its upright intention, or it might be describing an interior, secret or hidden state, or it's indicating a reduced or receding influence. Stay open to the possibilities as you meditate on your question.

We have also included the possibility of duplicate cards in each position. In other words, this spread encompasses three full decks’ worth of card combinations. If the same card turns up in different positions in the reading, simply integrate the message the card is giving you from the perspective of its position in the spread.


Here are a few words from each artist, giving her own particular description of the archetype she chose to depict in this deck.

0
The Fool 
Artist: y0b
A leap into the cliff, a universe of randomness and intent. Colorful hills beyond.

I
The Magician
Artist: Kristy Glas
She is pure and passionate, connected to spiritual and material realms. She seeks balance and knowledge through constant growth.

II
The High Priestess
Artist: Cristiana Vettor (combugnera)
This card indicates the search for female knowledge, clairvoyance, the search for the secret and the future; her knowledge is mostly initiatory, therefore forbidden to most people and reserved only to a few.


III
The Empress
Artist: SpaceDivers
She stands powerful and dancing, between nature and imagination, the pattern of creation and knowledge of birth are flows and breaths of reality, whether material or ethereal. 

IV
The Emperor
Artist: Lulu
Control through intelligence, the strength you need to stand straight.

V
The Hierophant
Artist: Inês Merino
A rite of passage – infinite wisdom and guidance, magic, shining the brightest light within… As we close this chapter, a new beginning unfolds.

VI
The Lovers
Artist: oculardelusion
In the sacred beech grove’s purple light, divine union of requited love, of union with the Divine. All is One.

VII
The Chariot
Artist: The Bad Lament
The Chariot brings forth the brave winged warrioress, with the moon at her back, determined and ambitious.

VIII
Strength
Artist: LUVRworldwide
The aligning of truths in mind-body-spirit, fuels our source from within, empowering a spectrum of peaceful passion and disciplined determination.


IX
The Hermit
Artist: Stina Jones
The hermit ventures forth, carving her own path through the wilderness.

X
The Wheel of Fortune
Artist: Sparrow
The Wheel of Fortune is never not a part of life. When this card appears it is a reminder: change is the only constant.

XI
Justice
Artist: Kitty Bast
“Karma’s a Bitch.”

XII
The Hanged Man
Artist: Daira
It is best to be sure to be willing to change.

XIII
Death
Artist: DaniellaDoodles
While there is death, there is also life - death allows for new growth and change.

XIV
Temperance
Artist: Vanesa Stati
Temperance tests waters with one foot on solid ground, it’s the wise step, the guide from a lower plane to a higher one that enjoys natural protection, which denotes and promove a point of balance: moderation, patience, purpose, tenacity, adaptation, acceptance, harmonization, reason, flow...

XV
The Devil
Artist: Cechk
The seduction of the devil can materialise in the physical realm as well on the mind, it has lust and obsession, it longs for power, but also lives in fear and strives for domination. The Devil is good and bad, and you’re the one that will decide who it will be. 

XVI
The Tower
Artist: Brandi Kyle
A standing reminder of the perils we face, the Tower card depicts possibilities of catastrophe, destruction, renovation, or just simply unexpected change.

XVII
The Star
Artist: Silje Thorn
She is at peace with renewed purpose and hope, nourishing her surroundings with the conscious and the subconscious in equilibrium.

XVIII
The Moon
Artist: St Heresy
As she is kind and sweet, she is also deceptive and dangerously beckoning. She is the holder of your secrets, and she holds no judgement.

XIX
The Sun
Artist: Gisel Florez
Circadian rhythms radiating the ultimate path of purpose & source.  

XX
Judgement
Artist: Marigold
The announcement of a new era is coming. A new World will be born after the Judgement.

XXI
The World
Artist: CrypticFauna
She holds the past and uplifts the future, and provides all pathways into either direction.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Frank's Papaya
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This work is a very personal piece and at the same time quintessentially New York. Let me share with you the story behind "Frank's Papaya." I've decided to write this description more stream of conscious, almost like a journal entry, or a casual conversation. Sit back and take a ride in my mind.

Some of the earliest memories in my entire life are of going to Gray's Papaya on 72nd and Broadway in New York City.  I would go with my Mom and my Dad separately and don't think I was ever there with them at the same time. They were no longer together but they knew how much I enjoyed getting dogs.

The place is a visual overload with all the colors, especially the hanging paper fruits. I loved those as a kid and still do.  One thing I like is that it's pretty much remained the same for as long as I can remember it.  That entire block actually.  There's a mattress store that's been there forever and some other longtime spots. A part of New York that has managed to stay frozen in time.

The hot dogs are awesome and I learned about putting mustard and sauerkraut on "dogs" from my Dad there.  No ketchup!  But try telling my wife that lol. The papaya juice was also incredible but I am scared to think now how much sugar was in those - probably contributed to my pre-diabetic diagnosis. 

I liked that they had tons of Obama signs up when he was running for president and aren't afraid to promote whatever cause they are behind. 
Feels like a piece of old New York that I hope always stays where it is. Real New York flavor and expression.

Also, Frank serving up franks is something I've thought about for a while and what better place to pay homage to.

I learned when you order to just say the number of hotdogs you want.. for example, "Can I get two with sauerkraut?"  You put the mustard on yourself, everyone has their preference for just the right amount :)

A little bit about the layers -

The ceiling - I wanted to keep it fun and festive. Hanging Fruit, hanging sneakers, and disco balls. 
 
The TV - I thought it would be fun to offer a bunch of options on the TV, a celebration of both old and new, a sort of time machine if you will:  classic late night NYC public access shows on Channel 35 like Robin Byrd, sports, sitcoms, as well as current Crypto news and some classic Frank Ape pieces I've made over the years. 

The Customers - A little bit of choose your own adventure celebrating both young and old. 

The Employees - Always there with a smile and grace to serve up dogs in a second at any time of the day or night.

Thanks for joining me on this adventure!

Frank Ape is a mystical creature who lives amongst the humans but without human restrictions.  What started as a form of self-expression on the streets of NYC for artist Brandon Sines quickly turned into a movement for the people. Frank has special powers that he continues to discover as he is tested by the many challenges of life. Frank champions positivity and equality, and cares about all living things. He believes in using imagination and play to inspire other people and animals through thoughtful actions.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: PORTRAITS OF STRENGTH: Women in Ethnic Vietnam (Tech-Enhanced)
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
IMPORTANT: to test the artwork (and its 512 combinations) please click on the "TEST ARTWORK" button or go to this link: https://www.tonycorocher.com/nft-digitalart/asyncart/portraits-of-strength/

DESCRIPTION:
Documentary Photography meets Illustration thanks to Technology. Could this be a new way of story telling?

This NFT programmable artwork was born from the collaboration between Tony Corocher and George Boya. We decided to start from one of Tony’s award winning photo essays and to combine the "Reality" of photography with the "Surreal" of George's illustration/collage art.

We selected "PORTRAITS OF STRENGTH: Ethnic Women in North Vietnam" (original photo essay here: https://www.tonycorocher.com/portraits-of-strength-women-in-ethnic-vietnam/). We both agreed that the theme, the images, the colors and the possible combinations were ideal for programmable art and for what was boiling in our minds.
But, the main reasons why we chose this essay was the message that came with it: these women live in rural areas up in the mountains of North Vietnam, frequently in very hard conditions and with very little help. When I was there I was struck by the strength and perseveration they showed, by their collaborative efforts and by their calmness... so I decided to spend a couple of weeks in the area, meet with a few people, get to know them and listen to their stories.

With George's mesmerising illustrations we took it a step further by introducing a possible future in which technology and decentralisation will be able to help these women directly, without any middle man or government interference. 

So I got into the original 15 photos, broke each one down into 3 parts (main subject, secondary subject and background) to see what was working and what was not. I ended up with 12 States (4 in each Layer). Then George worked his magic by creating another 12 states where his illustrations overtake the original images while keeping it real and connected with the original photos.

We ended up with 1 MASTER, 3 LAYERS and 8 STATES per layer (for a total of 512 possible combinations). It was a fun, enjoyable and very interesting collaboration and it produced an artwork with a distinct and important message behind:
THE STRENGTH OF THESE WOMEN AND THE POSSIBILITIES OFFERED BY TECHNOLOGY TO IMPROVE THEIR LIVES.

The original Photo Essay won the following Awards:

- PX3 Gran Prix De La Photographie, Paris: Honorable Mention. 2015
https://www.tonycorocher.com/px3-gran-prix-de-la-photographie-paris-2015-third-place-2-honorable-mentions/

- IPA Oneshot Competition: Honorable Mention. 2016 "Family of Man” (International Photography Awards – Los Angeles).
https://www.tonycorocher.com/ipa-2016-oneshot-competition-family-of-man/

Rebeca handed you the pot filled with soup, she placed it next to you. As you had foreseen, you had no appetite.

Rebecca stared at you, an unyielding gaze.

Then, you lifted the lid. You lifted it slowly, as slow as Rebecca had placed it. You felt a strange dread as you uncovered the pot, but understood it was your nerves playing tricks on you. You fantasized of being far away, maybe in the lobby rather than the top floor, alone with her.

Rebecca stared at you, an unyielding gaze.

And when the lid was finally removed, and you looked inside, and then you looked at Rebecca, and Rebecca was staring at you with unyielding gaze, and she turned her eyes towards the inside of the pot, and she smiled, and you started moaning, and everything decided to dance in front of your eyes, everything started to blend together, and only the image of the lid remained, rising slowly, the liquid inside, and... and...

You had not expected that. You were too smart to expect that. You had the intelligence to spare, even to the point that the overflow was unable to keep on living inside your brain, and it decided to seek a way out. Now you count numbers and more numbers sitting in the bunk. No one can get a word out of you, but you used to look through the window, as if you expected to see luminous signs, and then you step forward with your right foot, you twist your hip the same way that someone who is preparing to swing a golf club would, and you bury your empty hand inside the void of your cell.

Fragment of ‘Puzzle’ by Julio Cortazar 1938.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The Mask is a physical traditional oil painting on canvas, 36x36’’ (91x91 cm) made between January and July 2020 in Boston, Massachusetts USA, and adapted for Async on April 2021.
This piece portraits a mask typical from the Diablada carnival from the Andes in South America. As a child I found these masks very scary but as I grew up I found that they were fascinating, specially because of the colors and the teatrical design.
In this programmable NFT version, the painting goes into Dark Mode during the night and can be seen glowing as if it were under UV light.
The Mask was part of the Alien Citizen Solo Art Show at the SoWa Galleries in Boston, MA September 4, 2020 - September 13, 2020.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Camping Spirit
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Camping Spirit is a collaborative artwork made by Mikko Lyytinen & PXLPET The artwork changes automatically between two images based on a day and night cycle.

A group of pxlpets have gone for an outdoors trip and set up their camp on a beautiful forest clearing near the mountains. It is a pleasant, peaceful day. You can hear the sounds of wildlife roaming around in the bushes and the whisper of a light breeze gently rattling the leaves.There is no rush anywhere, it is as if the time stood still in this enchanted landscape. 

As the sun begins to set and all the colors slowly fade away into the darkness, a sense of mystery fills the air and everyone's imagination starts to run wild. What kind of strange creatures could be hiding out there in the shadows of the forest? All the old tales of fairies, trolls and dragons even, suddenly seem to become real. Everyone is too excited to sleep and the night passes in waves of chatter, interrupted by sudden quiet when someone hears a sound and everyone is trying to figure out what kind of mythical creature it was that made it. 

In the morning everyone is surprisingly full of energy and ready for another day of leisure in their idyllic campsite.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: / ONE MORE PETAL /
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Inspired in “He Loves Me, He Loves Me Not” painted by Robert Fowler (1853-1926).

‘He/she loves me, he/she loves me not’ is a game of French origin initially called ‘effeuiller la marguerite’ (‘strip the daisy’).

In the original French version of the game, the petals do not simply indicate whether the object of the player's affection loves them, but to what extent: un peu or "a little", beaucoup or "a lot", passionnément or "passionately", à la folie or "to madness", or pas du tout or "not at all."

However the poor girl in this painting looks like her daisy needed one more petal!.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Lonely Space Journey
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
A lonely figure in a room on a spaceship, with a book as solo companion. Reading, reflecting, meditating, wondering.  Different states that this human figure has to pass the time on this journey into the unknown. A journey where the landscape changes but it seems not to affect this person that is oblivion to it. What is this journey? What are these parts in the universe that she is passing? What is written on the book? 

A lonely journey that could be also a journey to our inner self, to the stars that we are made of.

Each layers can be changed according to the mood of the owner. The Spaceship room with different colors; The Human Figure in the different positions and mindsets; and the Space Window Background to present different parts of the Universe.

Are you gonna make your Lonely Space Journey into the unknown?

All made on Ipad with Procreate.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Betty's Notebook
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
UNCOVER THE MYSTERY 
Betty's Notebook is a controversial piece of evidence in the Amelia Earhart mystery. Recorded by 15-year old Betty Klenck in 1937, the document continues the mystery of what really happened to Amelia Earhart as she was taken off her flight path. The musical adaptation by Nicholas Reeves puts audiences in Betty’s shoes: as if listeners turn a tuning knob on a short wave radio trying to hear Amelia Earhart’s distress calls that are frequently obstructed by various radio interferences.  The dynamic nature of Betty’s Notebook allows audiences to uncover chilling distress signals and key clues by toggling variants within different stems. The ever evolving music creates a holistic picture of the eternal mystery of Amelia Earhart.

  PHYSICAL RADIO
 If the Master Track NFT meets its reserve price, the owner will receive a physical life-size short wave radio with built-in speakers and screen. The radio will update in real-time to the latest audio-visual Variants. This physical radio piece is fit for private collections, museums, and galleries.   

TIME CAPSULE
 Immortalize the mystery by owning a Limited Edition Record NFT of your favorite Betty’s Notebook version. By literally taking a snapshot of the latest iteration, you get to hold onto a unique part of the mystery. 

Learn more about Betty’s Notebook and its Stems by clicking on them or at verdigrismusic.org

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: LEAVING
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
‘Leaving' is a dynamic musical artwork about the different states of a unique relationship between three people; a love triangle told from the perspective of all those involved. The three characters interweave and blur into each other, with the different primary emotional states as represented by the instrumental intermingling with unpredictable results - eventually, past present, and future; the betrayed, the betrayer and the object of the betrayal; loss, guilt and hope; all meld into one. In total, there are 6400 different songs included in the artwork - not trivially different, but radically so. Each unique composition is a snapshot of a different angle of the love triangle both in time and in perspective - the irreducible, overwhelming state of confusion that permeates all human relationships, captured musically. The accompanying cover art work, beautifully rendered by our collaborator Mike Raymond, is the visual representation of ‘Leaving'. Each possible composition, acting as each distinct moment in the relationship, has a corresponding and distinct visual representation: three lovers, 6400 different dances, spinning and looping around in eternity. 

We view the 20 tracks included as the primary colours of our composition. But relationships are not simple; therefore, the master track will dynamically reflect the intricate complexity of love and loss. The collectors can choose the timbre, intensity and sonic identity of the different instrumental layers, as well as the narrative and character behind the vocal layer, and mix the fundamentals into a unique whole, capturing the different shades and shapes love and loss can take. We believe ‘Leaving' represents a new frontier in what art and music is, and should do; both an experiment in storytelling, in sonic variations, in the value of art and in the relationship between audience, collector and artist. The stem owners can change who sings the vocal part, what the lyrics are, what the main melody is, what instrument plays the bass line, what kind of drumming style underpins the performance. All the variations seamlessly work together to form 6400 unique compositions, each of which is musically rich enough to be a standalone song - spanning everything from pianno ballads to electronic mayhem. Each layer-owner has the power to alter the whole master, without knowing what the other layer owners will do. Essentially, 'Leaving' is a collective artistic composition with randomness and agency factored in - collectors might collaboratively arrive at a state or a genre, consciously or unconsciously, by responding (or ignoring) each others’ choices. Each different state has been separately written, performed and recorded in a decentralised fashion by HMLTD and our collaborators, Tallulah Eden and Seth Evans.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: in.a.room
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: I have been quietly reflecting on my position in life. How I am, where I am, and who I am. These questions make you really take stock of how the various elements that float to and through your life influence it, and how your internal voice ultimately chooses what gets done with those elements. Like a stream swirling around you, there is a vibration in the air. If you could stop time you could see the ripples and turbulence pushing you in different directions. This piece was an attempt to stop time for a moment and take inventory of the various forces acting on me. The positive, the negative, the internal and the external, the real and the imagined. I tried to shape it and hold it in some tangible way. I tried to capture it for a moment in the hopes I could understand it more meaningfully. So I sat with myself and stopped time. This is me in a room.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Ocean Eve
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Ocean Eve

The ocean lifts.
The ocean punishes.
The ocean forgives.
The ocean heals.
The ocean connects.

Eve is the life force.

The ocean is a metaphor for the metaverse and Eve represents all of us. A collective and individual consciousness.

Ocean Eve ebbs and flows with the water, exploring and constructing an infinite immutable path. When balance and stillness is needed the leaf is there.

We are all interconnected by the same ocean.

The four works of art in this token allude to entering, exploring, admiring, and exiting the ocean. 

-

My genesis series is inspired by the entering of the metaverse. The merger of nature and technology is a topic that has inspired my art for over 20 years and will be the driving force in my genesis series. Any token holder is along for a lifelong journey of expansion and community that in itself will be a work of art.

This is a 1 of 1 autonomous token and the first appearance of Ocean Eve. There is a related video animation that is an edition of 10 called “Metaverse Eve.”

Any holder of an Async token will be rewarded with exclusive tokens in the future.
 
Bio: Over the last 20 years Ari Lankin has extensively developed painted languages exploring abstraction, conceptual process, and realism. His current paintings are intentionally open to interpretation and rich in visceral sensation. They encourage experienced based conversations on the universe and mankind. They hover between mystical and scientific. The physicality of paint, intuition, memory, and exploration are crucial aspects of his practice. His last solo show in New York City in 2020 completely sold out, he has two murals on public display at World Trade Center 3, and he has had major signature product collaborations with TROJAN™ Condoms and Adidas.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Augmented Artist Series
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The Augmented Artist is a series which consists of digital versions of 6 acrylic on textured paper hand-painted works inspired from the art created by the social media AI bot that I created in 2019 : "Auria Kathi".  Auria Kathi was exhibited at the Florence Biennale 2019 and NeurIPS AI art gallery 2019; and The Augmented Artist was exhibited at Cueva gallery and Cobalt gallery, and was featured in multiple news publications. 
This project is explained in detail here: https://nurecas.com/an-augmented-artist

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Voluttuose
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
In this artwork, my subject looks at and through the viewer in her search for light. Streams of air swirl around her just so slightly to give her enough opportunity to see things clearly.
I integrated my hand-painted and then digitalised paisley patterns to enhance the overall look of the portrait and to accentuate several details I deem important. I played a lot with skin tone varitations,  shading and the general colour scheme. As always, I tried to get rid of all that is is non-essential in my work, leaving just my conceptual triangle as a visible composition: eye - lips - art.

In myths and fairytales it is often an archetype of a deep, mysterious power. In this work, I imagine the Queen of the Forest herself. In the work she appears in a woodland glade, performing her secret rituals throughout the day, interacting with animals and the planets, and by this making the forest happen.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Lets do it a Dada - the portable museum
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
'(...) my son
let us always shuffle through the colour of the world
which looks bluer than the subway and astronomy
we are too thin
we have no mouth
our legs are stiff and knock together
our faces are formless like the stars (...)' - Tristan Tzara, 'Great Lament Of My Obscurity Three'

The portable museum is a collaborative piece between Brandi Kyle (@PlaceofMany) and Oficinas TK. 

With a friendly nod to Dada (and a heartfelt 'thank you' to Duchamp), this work presents elements from both artists' arranged inside a display case, on a hinted institutional environment, inviting the viewers to question what makes a work of art, while smiling at ideas like context, presentation, content or perception.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: the Remixable Reclining Nude
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
A programmable lying woman.
The traits of her mutable body are selectable from 6 art history masterpieces covering a span of 4 centuries: 

Giorgione - Venere dormiente (1507-1510)
Tiziano - Venere di Urbino (1538)
Francisco Goya - Maja desnuda (1797–1800)
Gustave Courbet - Femme nue couchée (1862)
Amedeo Modigliani - Nudo sdraiato (1917-1918)
Isaac Israëls - Reclining reading nude (1915-1922)

4 remixable layers with 6 states each for a journey to discover 1296 shades of sensuality, beauty and mystery, knowing that in every part of them there is the brushstroke of a master and the energy of his spirit and his time.
