0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Dark City
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
What if all the constraints of a physical world disappear, and we are left with a
database of attributes - information that determines the properties of environments. Can we envision spatial conditions that are governed by digital physics?

Nowadays, with the technology of artificial lighting, we remove the unique conditions that darkness offered to us – the ability to hide, the oblivion.

In the Dark City, there is a totally different sensual experience. Noises are suddenly amplified, the smell becomes stronger and we totally rediscover the sense of touch.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Übermensch
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Behold, Nietzsche's Übermensch (overman).

Autonomous. Changes based on time of day.

Day 
(How far we have come)
"All beings so far have created something beyond themselves; and do you want to be the ebb of this great flood, and even go back to the beasts rather than overcome man? What is ape to man? A laughing stock or painful embarrassment."

Night
(How far we have yet to go)
“And man shall be just that for the overman: a laughingstock or a painful embarrassment. You have made your way from worm to man, and much in you is still worm. Once you were apes, and even now, too, man is more ape than any ape."

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Marble faces

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Smoking Woman
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
She watches you intently as the smoke from her cigarette gently dances on the air. You're trying hard to discern her gaze in the dim light. Is it mild curiosity, mere annoyance, disgust, or is it desire?

I work both digitally and traditionally, striving to make the two indistinguishable in order to show critics the value of digital art in the world of fine art. I pick my subjects based on the emotion(s) it evokes in me and then I try to convey that same feeling in the work I create.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Money ₿adger
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: In this piece, there are 27 unique song combinations, with three music, drum and vocal track state changes. The honey badger will give a visual cue of what vocal track is selected by the positioning of its head, while the background is determined by the selected music state change. The drum machine lies beneath the badger as it bangs on the analog buttons to create the percussion for each track. The honey badger is an early mascot in the ₿itcoin world, and represents the unstoppable force that ₿itcoin and the entire ecosystem represents. ₿orn Unique and Kaimbr rap on the "Proof Of Work (Potomac Kings)" song, Willie Waze performs "Rug Pull" and Kane Mayfield drops in for "Cryptnology."

I saw a whisper,

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: F.U.S.E. Syntax [Two]
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
A new audio-visual experiment under the F.U.S.E. moniker between brothers Richie & Matthew Hawtin continuing their collaboration which started in the 1991 with the seminal electronic music album "Dimension Intrusion" on +8/WARP records.

Syntax [Two] explores the relationship between its innate components and how the re-arrangement of their layer and states create subtle but profound new iterations.

Each audio & visual layers have been designed to interplay with one another resulting in thousands of unique possiblitlies.

Syntax [Two] is part of the new F.U.S.E. Syntax release that will be available on all music streaming platforms on June 4th.

The release will also include a special version, "Syntax [Two] @username Async NFT mix" which will be determined by from the current Master Track state one week after the sale of the Master and all layers. This will give each layer owner the unique opportunity to contribute to the remix of Syntax [Two] by having their layer decisions affect the final audio & visual outcome of this special officially released version.

In addition, the current Master owners Async username will be credited in the remixes title.

What do you think?

Ebic Jo is a crypto-world explorer.

The artwork reflects day/night change of atmosphere.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Habitación SUR
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Habitación SUR es la última creación del colectivo CryptoArg donde el conjunto argentino pone en evidencia su heterogénea escencia.
La habitación se presenta como un espacio virtual donde las distintas obras se combinan entre sí generando distintos puntos de vista de la misma galería. Las obras pueden ocurrir o no ocurrir, pero solo en su conjunto ellas tienen sentido. De esta manera, Habitación Sur se configura como un punto de encuentro donde 26 artistas confluyen en una misma dirección: el Sur.


"Habitación Sur" is the latest creation of the CryptoArg collective where the Argentinean group shows its heterogeneous essence.
The room is presented as a virtual space where the different works combine with each other generating different points of view of the same gallery. The works may or may not appear due to their multiple combinations of layers, but it is only as a whole that they make sense.  In this way, this room is configured as a meeting point where 26 artists converge towards the same direction: South.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Gloomy Caw
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
On ground you could see despair and scarlet drawings. On ground there was no hope left. On ground small dreams were dead. Eyes were full of terror.
On the sky there was freedom. On the sky a bright beam was playing. On the sky we flew. Wings were full of energy.
And a caw was echoing in-between.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Regeneration #930202
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Artwork Title: Regeneration #930202
Date of Artwork: 2020-2021
Dimension: 2160 pixel x 2160 pixel
Type of Work: GANs Algorithm trained photograph
Date of Dataset: 2010-2017
Edition: Unique

The photographs in the series of Regeneration produced by using Generative Adversarial Networks. I took over three thousand photos spanned nearly a decade for a specific project and selected over a thousand photos from there as the Dataset for AI training. The photographs have been gestated by AI that integrated all the subtle emotions of the original pieces, which are the most exciting parts of this series.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Whistler
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The Master's Study

The conception of oil painting began as a statement of wealth.  Landscapes with castles overlooking their lands filled with the owner's livestock.  Tables filled with exotic foods and expensive crystal to display possessions.  Mythological scenes were stories of high society, the privileged knowledge only to the wealthy.  Pretentious portraits of royalty; it isn't their faces that glow in these compositions, but their dresses and jewelry.  

The painting of The Whistling Boy by Frank Duveneck (1848-1919) is a painting representing a blue collar worker.  The work at the time in history helps represents part of a departure of paintings representing an individual’s monetary value.  Painting began to be about the average joe, instead of the rich and wealthy.  The painting wasn't about depicting treasures, bounty's won, still lives filled with riches.  But now the painting was about being human, and the daily toils of life from the average worker.  In this context, this was a very remarkable painting of its' time.  And what for, would an artist make a painting like this?  To get paid?  Whom would ever purchase a work of this manner?....

 The artist takes the notion even further, capturing a moment where the boy is whistling. A satirical element in many respects: Has this poor boy immortalized himself through oil painting, and is he whistling to spite all of the rich nobility that came before him in this tradition of portraiture? Not to mention the haphazard way the clothing is painted, truly a disgrace to the fine art of painting.

The whistle, not only a final cat call from a disrespectful boy, but also full of such poetry. The artist captures that one moment in time, breathing life into this pile of colored mud we call paint. It’s quite a beautiful moment, and it inspired me with that same type of dynamic humor. I built upon this scene, which adds even more layers to this game that always lead us to second-guess ourselves. My work reveals these hidden elements with a twist of ironic absurdness. (Note, a recent cleaning of Duveneck’s painting revealed a cigarette in the boy’s hand. Doesn’t this change the entire meaning of this work from how it has been presented?)

As we shift from dawn/day/dusk/night we notice a hideous green monster appearing.  In remembering the Dr. Hide and Mr. Jeckyl's, Doctor Banner and his evil Hulk side.  In the new found NFT artworld, is painting remembering it's ugly pasts? Is the beast rearing its' head?  Or is it the artist with the hulking power of the beast now?  For value rests clearly inside....

Original oil on canvas created from the Master Study's series of work, 2014-2015
In creating this piece, I feel the formal attributes of the dynamic shifts on the blockchain can showcase the double-sided nature of this work, the history that it contained, and how the work has transformed even further with a digital movement and the implement meanings that continue to flow and evolve from the work.  Truly a timeless, and now (block)less artwork.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
TEAMWORK

Working together in the present helps shape a brighter future.

TEAMWORK celebrates this idea visually and functionally.

Each layer owner controls three different states of their Frank, and one owner controls the color of the light. 

Each state is an integral part in the process of working together: carrying the letter, placing the letter, and helping reach the light switch.

Layer owners collaborate to create thousands of possibilities (59,049 to be exact) all representing a facet of working together. Sometimes in perfect harmony, other times in glorious chaos, but always for the greater good of the community. 

Frank Ape is a mystical creature who lives amongst the humans but without human restrictions.  What started as a form of self-expression on the streets of NYC for artist Brandon Sines quickly turned into a movement for the people. Frank has special powers that he continues to discover as he is tested by the many challenges of life. Frank champions positivity and equality, and cares about all living things. He believes in using imagination and play to inspire other people and animals through thoughtful actions.

We are in a womb-like moment - a place of creation and chaos. Therefore, the 5 layers of Fortuna are rich in symbolism of rebirth, change, and transformation, inspired by the art of female surrealist painters. 0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: अर्धनारीश्वर (Ardhanarishvara)
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Eastern philosophy, especially Hinduism is a myriad cauldron of schools and thoughts and I get confused and confounded - mostly because it requires years of reading and understanding.

Purusha - represented in the male form represents "Pure Consciousness" 
Prakriti - represented in the female form represents "The Primary Substance" 

When you bring them together, a representation of pure consciousness within the original form is what we are in essence. The passive force (Purusha) and the active force (Prakriti) are intertwined, inseparable and represent the non-duality of the supreme being - both father and mother, both aloof and active, both fearsome and gentle, both destructive and constructive - thereby speaking to the unification of all that is opposite and contrasting to represent a whole. 

Ardhanarishvara reconciles and harmonizes the two conflicting ways of life: the spiritual way of the ascetic as represented by Shiva, and the materialistic way of the householder as symbolized by Parvati. 

It also represents the presence of both in each being. Every human within them contains Shiva and Parvati in varying degrees. There exists a spectrum between the binaries of males and females, and that spectrum is where we find balance in life.

Collaboration : Indrani Mitra imagined Parvati and Vishesh Chopra crafted Shiva

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Dark Moods
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"...The world was divided into two countries.
Every photograph taken in the first was of people.
Every photograph taken in the second showed none."
--excerpt from the poem Genesis by Mary Ruefle

Beauty is a perception. Absolutes do not hold.

That perception is not ready to be perceived. The act of perceiving is an effort and its outcome as well as its inception is probabilistic. 

Between the probabilities and the perceptions, beauty or read it as reality is elusive.

Dark Moods is my imagination playing tricks to itself. Based on public domain photography from Pixabay, each image is composed of multiple images forming a state of its own. As I've perceived each image as a totality, I did not break down to layers. Instead I've provided the four images with different levels of alterations as a continuum in itself.

Dark Moods minted June 2021 on Async Art by Hulki Okan Tabak

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: / ANDROMEDA /
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Andromeda chained to a rock as a sacrifice to sate a sea monster, before being saved from death by Perseus, her future husband.
Inspired in Edward Poynter, son of the architect Ambrose Poynter. Edward met Frederick Leighton in Rome, who made a great impression on the 17-year-old.

Boasting of being as beautiful as the Nereids, Andromeda's mother, Cassiopeia, provoked the fury of Poseidon, who decided to flood the Earth and send the sea monster Ceto to destroy men and cattle. Cepheus, Andromeda's father, knew from the oracle of Amun what the only solution was: to marry his daughter to the monster. To do this, he left her only dressed in jewels and chained to a rock.
Perseus, who after killing Medusa had received winged sandals as a gift from the Naiads, saw her chained and fell in love with her. After asking for the girl's hand in exchange for killing the monster, Perseus, with the head of Medusa - who turned whoever looked at her to stone - killed Keto and turned him into a coral.
It is a theme represented in art by artists like Giorgio Vasari and Rembrandt.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Beyond
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: We are used to looking at things only from straight angle, overlooking details that are hidden from us at first glance. This type of vision shapes our understanding of things, and drives us into the framework of the stereotypes we have created. What if we look at the world wider? What if we get used to presenting the bigger picture instead of focusing only on the details that are visible at first glance? This kind of vision would allow us to look at things more broadly, penetrating their essence and not just the outer shell. We came up with strict rules that formed the basis of life, and now, being guided by these rules, we ourselves limit our freedom of action, freedom of outlook and breadth of thought. But at the same moment, these rules and frameworks exist only in our head, and it is in our power to get rid of them. I was always inspired by the icons of Andrei Rublev, who painted his icons depicting the world in reverse perspective, as well as Pablo Picasso, who painted pictures without trying to adhere to generally accepted rules, but trying to show the very essence instead of the usual shell. The surreal spirit of such works prompted us to learn the principles of action of various optic lenses, the features of light refraction and the capabilities of various software in order to be able to push the boundaries of our usual vision, but already in the world of digital art. It took me 3 months of experiments to make this experience become possible, and this picture is the result of these experiments. It changes its appearance depending on the time of day. At night, we see the forms and strict lines we are accustomed to, in the morning and in the evening it begins to transform and freezes in an intermediate stage, in which you can see how proportions and sizes change. During the day, we have the opportunity to look beyond the usual and see what is hidden from our eyes. Forms and lines no longer lend themselves to familiar representations, but create a whole new image that allows us to look differently at the forms that have become familiar. If we treat our life in this way, we will be able to look at things with a fresh look of a child who does not yet have established conservative concepts, which means there is unlimited freedom of research and imagination. Thanks to such views of the world, we can finally look deeper, we can look beyond.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Looking for Fairies
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The work "Looking for Fairies" is about daring to love and hope in the face of prejudice and prosecution. 

The work is based on two Victorian picture genres. Most important is the photographs of "Romantic Friendships", a photographic trend where men went to a photographer to have their photo taken holding hands, embracing, sitting on each others lap, even hugging and kissing. This in a period of time when homosexuality was forbidden by law. But friendship wasn't. 

A disparaging name used on feminine men in this period was "fairies", and the other pictoral genre used in the work, is the innocent, childlike Fairy Paintings, a strange Victorian trend of painting fairies, with wings and crowns, dancing in the forest in a summerly night.

When it was forbidden for a queer man to have a partner, cruising in parks and forests was often one of the few options available to meet. In the work "Looking for Fairies", I've cut out single men from the romantic friendship photographs, and placed them as hopeful fairies in an idyllic summer forest, hunting for their future beloved friend.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This is for the people who feel like they never belong, the outsiders.
The outcasts, the exiled, the divergent thinkers. 
The ones who join groups, but never feel part of the community.

Your existence matters! 

Night State represents sadness and loneliness.
A dark veil causing blindness from the primal truth: 
Nature gave us the gift of existing. It doesn't matter who you are, your mere existence is a cause for celebration. It doesn't matter what others think about it, nature believes you have a role in this, like everybody else.

Day State represents joy and love.
The dark veil is off. The individual, while still lonely, experiences feelings of acceptance. The void created by the craved love is filled with peace. 
They discover that love has many sources, it can be given, but it can also be generated within.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: FORM FARM
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
FORM FARM yields rare architecture. The FARM has 25 collectible plots. Each plot comes with 15 form options that the owner can modify at any time. In order to successfully “farm” NFTs; plot owners must cooperate with their neighbors to align form-types (cubes, windows, staircases etc.) For example; aligning 3 windows in a row will signal the architect (untitled, xyz) to mint and airdrop a commemorative “window” themed NFT to the owner of each participating plot. Over time, FORM FARM owners are rewarded for their engagement and cooperation with one another. 

While the FARM can be used to earn NFTs, it also serves as a consensus mechanism to inform the broader artistic practice of untitled, xyz. Each form comes with a “build” or “burn” option. If a plot owner majority agrees to “burn” a window (for example); untitled, xyz will retire a window form that has been used in a previous artwork. Looking forward, that window form will never be used again. If plot owners agree to “build” a window; untitled, xyz will introduce a new style of window that has never existed before. 

Through FORM FARM, plot owners can earn NFTs while guiding the scarcity, abundance and overall evolution of xyz’s art.  

TIMING

A snapshot of the FORM FARM will take place on the 1st of every month at 12:00 AM UTC. At this time, a record of the FARM will be made and published to Twitter (@untitledxyz_) announcing how many new forms and NFTs will be airdropped to plot owners that month.

GUIDELINES

For a complete set of guidelines, visit: https://www.untitledxyz.com/formfarm

Date of Artwork: 2021
Dimension: 1688 pixel x 2160 pixel
Type of Work: Silver Gelatin Photogram, Digital Painting
Edition: Unique
Note: This artwork is a type of digital art. The hand-made photogram is one of the subjects that compose this piece, and this photogram is not for sale separately whatever in the crypto world or the real world.

Notwithstanding, the beginning of the photography is representational, it ultimately leads to the way of the abstract. Photography has nothing to do with painting, although the thinking of abstractness renders them getting closer and closer. Photography remains the interpretation of "Light", and to express the “Light” is its inescapable responsibility. I find the "Line" could be one of the forms to present the "Light". I apply the "Line", also is the "Light", to destroy a completed and finished photograph, and change it into a new form of art and have a unique way of spreading and viewing. Through this new attempt to keep looking for balance and harmony.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Portraits Sans Temps
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"...May she be granted beauty, and yet not   
Beauty to make a stranger's eye distraught,   
Or hers before a looking-glass; for such,   
Being made beautiful overmuch,   
Consider beauty a sufficient end,   
Lose natural kindness, and maybe   
The heart-revealing intimacy   
That chooses right, and never find a friend."
--- from A Prayer for My Daughter by W.B. Yeats

I have neither better, nor further words after Yeats. Let's have a look at the technicals..

...

Technical Notes:

Some of the base photographs are my photographs from the skulls in museums. Others are public domain images. In either case, each photograph has been two or three times edited since early 2000 before being considered for this final piece. Once I decided to include them, a final editing, notably in Photoshop, has been done.

While it resulted in slight imperfections and a lot of repeat work, I specifically chose 9 images and 9 states for it symbolized a grid total in my mind. Furthermore it allowed a very diverse set of visual outcomes that would range from unbearably bizarre to strikingly attractive.

Finally I spent considerable time in trying to decide on the layer images which ended up being possible alternative sets rather than layer specific line ups. Now I feel I have compressed 9 images, 9 layer images and countless possibilities in to one image. This is one of the strangest days of my life..

Portraits Sans Temps by Hulki Okan Tabak
Very exclusively, literally only for Async Art, 2021

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Dybbuk Box Diablo
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
**Disturbing Bad Vibes Vile Nasty**

The box has mysterious origins. Rumor has it that it was found in the back of a hearse with other enchanted objects.

The original box was purchased online for a music video by Dasychira called "Eternal Family", which tells the story of four YouTubers who wish to seal their fate and be together forever: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wnMKAquagdI

One day after the video shoot, the box was hidden in a secret location by one of the directors due to another crew's concern of its "dark energy".

Upon coming back to retrieve it sometime later, the director discovered the box had vanished. It has remained missing since.

Now, Dybbuk Box Diablo exists exclusively in digital (and spiritual) form as this NFT.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Hi, my name is...
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Aku is a young black kid created by Micah Johnson as a response to his nephew's question, "Can astronauts be black?". Empowered by his magical space helmet, Aku is on a mission to prove that he can be anything. Released as an NFT in February, Aku quickly inspired people across the world and became the first NFT to be optioned to become a feature film. After seeing the overwhelming responses to the inspiring message about what Aku meant to them, Micah realized the importance of collaborating directly with the community to shape the characters and stories within the Aku movie.

"Hi, my name is..." is the unveiling of the newest character in the Aku story. Created with the help of the Aku community, this collaboration concludes by giving the final control to the owner of the work. This programmable NFT enables the collector to ultimately decide if and/or when to remove the character's helmet to reveal their identity. Furthermore, because of it's programmability, this work changes every hour to reflect the rising and setting of the sun, symbolizing the determination it takes to achieve our dreams. The final element of the work is to work directly with the Aku team to name the newest member of Aku World.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: the Remixable female Selfportrait
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
A programmable nft art

The forever editable remix of hair and eyes, mouths, bodies and backgrounds from 10 self-portraits of female painters from 1500 to the end of the 1800s.

Caterina van Hemessen (1548)
Sofonisba Anguissola (1556)
Lavinia Fontana (1577)
Artemisia Gentileschi (1615-1617)
Rosalba Carriera (1715)
Angelika Kauffmann (1770-1775)
Elisabeth Vigée Lebrun (1781-1782)
Marie Gabrielle Capet (1783)
Mary Stevenson Cassatt (1880)
Berthe Morisot (1885)

4 remixable layers with 10 states each for a journey through the 10,000 possible portraits generated by the fusion of 10 masterpieces: unexpected faces, changing complexions under different lights and perspectives, different hairstyles and dresses through 4 centuries.
In each part of them there is the brushstroke of the artist while she mirrors in her Art.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:

"The collection of paintings portrays a landscape of color and intuition. I hope to capture the essence of modern life as we see it unfold in front of our very own eyes. The works are inspired by a struggle to make sense out of life and reflect a need for something more meaningful, something that brings out the JOY in our daily routine."

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Path to Nirvana
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This is a puzzle that is the human's "sense of self".

Each of us has 3 parts of "self".  The Ego, Super Ego, and Id.
Ego is mostly the one representing us.  It's what we show to the world.  But it alone is not the true "self".  How can we be complete when we are only in touch with 1/3 of ourself?

Nirvana frees us from the effects of karma and the cycles of death and birth.  In order to get there, we must explore deep into our inner truth. 

When you accept, forgive, and love all 3 parts of you, you can be at peace with each and learn to let go.  The moment you truly becomes **"SELFLESS"**, Nirvana is here!

In this thought provoking artwork, watch how the 3 versions of "self" work with each other, or NOT, on this journey to Nirvana!  Who will show up today?  Tomorrow night?  Will the Ego let others come out to play?  Will the Super Ego finally let its hair down and free the Id?  Will they ever reach Nirvana?  It's all up to the Layer Owners...

The puzzle is simple, the meaning, complex. 

**OWNERS BEWARE, this is a piece of art as well as a piece of puzzle, each Layer acts as a gateway to the ones underneath.  When you own one of the Layers, you will decide how the identity on that Layer behaves.  It's meant to bring awareness to us, reflecting on our actions.  The reveals of the inner selves and Nirvana may be very quick, or take a very very long time.  It's all meant to mimic the real struggles we have with our "inner selves".**

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Mind Sketch I
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"Almost happy now, he looked at his estate.
An exile making watches glanced up as he passed,
And went on working; where a hospital was rising fast
A joiner touched his cap; an agent came to tell
Some of the trees he'd planted were progressing well.
The white alps glittered. It was summer. He was very great."
--from the poem Voltaire at Ferney by W.H. Auden

Mind Sketch I is the first part of the mind sketches. Cerebral looking emotionally involved pieces of personal expression bullshit confusion love lost thoughts and experimentation. Purposefully quoting Auden whom I admire, specifically focusing on Voltaire for some reason or another.

Mind Sketch I consists of two pieces to be displayed half and half during the day and the night.

Minted on Async Art on June 2021 by Hulki Okan Tabak

Earthquakes and executions. Soon he would be dead,
And still all over Europe stood the horrible nurses
Itching to boil their children. Only his verses
Perhaps could stop them: He must go on working: Overhead
The uncomplaining stars composed their lucid song."
--from the poem Voltaire at Ferney by W.H. Auden

Mind Sketch II is the second of the mind sketches. Cerebral looking emotionally involved pieces of personal expression bullshit confusion love lost thoughts and experimentation. Purposefully quoting Auden whom I admire, specifically focusing on Voltaire for some reason or another.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Exquisite Frank
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Have you ever heard of the game exquisite corpse? 

I really miss just sitting around with friends and drawing which is maybe why this game popped into my head recently and inspired this collaborative piece.

It's one of the only games I can think of where everyone wins, is purely creative, and has a surrealist twist. The rules of the game are changeable but it's usually played by folding a paper in thirds. The first person draws a head and folds the paper so the next person can't see what they drew. The next person draws a body and then folds the paper again before passing it to the last person to draw the legs. Each section of the drawing is usually done in a few minutes and are fun, strange, silly, and unexpected. 

After all three sections are drawn the paper is unfolded and the reveal is made for the first time, it's like magic! 

With "Exquisite Frank" you and the other layer owners collaborate by changing each section of Frank. The collectors are forever linked in a never ending game of exquisite corpse. With this exquisite corpse, because it is digital, you can even change the background and foreground separately in two different layers, mixing the elements of each to create an entirely unique landscape.

Hope everyone has fun playing with Exquisite Frank, especially the token holders.  And for anyone who knows the game, I hope this brings back some fond memories, and all of you playing it for the first time I hope it leads to creative play with your friends next time you are hanging out.

Stay creative and keep playing :)

About the structure of the piece - 

There are five layers:
-Background Layer
-Head Section 
-Body Section
-Legs Section
-Foreground Layer

There are 25 unique Franks divided in thirds by the head, body, and legs. 

There are also 5 black and white backgrounds and foregrounds that can be mixed and matched. Not only do the Franks change, but so does the environment. 

There are a total of 390,625 possible combinations.

An increase in 'resolution' has allowed for more detail in this particular painting, but it is also heavily inspired by third and fourth generation video games - meaning bright, pixelated nostalgia was either meticulously planned or simply inevitable! 

Layers vary in impact and interactivity. A new sky or horizon can change the entire mood of the piece, but some might prefer to choose their own mode of transportation, the actions it undertakes, and whether or not it follows the rules of the road...

Meditation has the ability to reveal that which unifies all things... a shared existence. "Our Meditation" is a reflection of our Oneness. When you change, we change together, This singular work changes for us the moment you change it for you. Your moment is our moment, in time and outside of it. 

As a Collector of this work, you are invited to be a Collaborator. 
As a Collaborator in this work, you are invited to change its Vision, Body, Awareness, Energy, and Setting to reflect what you are experiencing moment to moment.
As a Viewer of this work, you are invited to reflect on what has changed... in it, in you, in us.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Space Opera V2: Descent to Hades.
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Persephone is returning to planet Hades after 6000 standard years with a final mission, to defeat the Lord of the Underdark and give an end to the Long Winter. It will be a difficult adventure and first she must face the four terrible Guardians, but she is ready and well equipped. With the right weapons and knowledge of the enemies weak spots she will manage to take them out.   


Descent to Hades is a game where the players (layer owners) must cooperate and find the right combination of blade/rifle/armour/trap/guardian in order to defeat the enemy. To celebrate the defeat of each Guardian, a new artwork will be minted and airdropped to the winners. The players can find clues at the description of each layer, or can use the Explore tool to check different visual combinations before changing the states. Have fun!

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Of Masks and Memories
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
We are made of memories, and with time, as our memories change, we change. 

When one think of 'memories', most people think of recordings, stored somehow, ready to be played back at any time, but they are so much more. They are states of mind caused by experience that are in constant flux, and which transform us. Neither our memories, nor how we feel about them, are static. They change over time and cause a process of unending transformation through which we are constantly creating and destroying ourselves.

Through all this, there are countless possible "selves" behind a mask, and the mask is the self that, finally, is presented to the world. Sometimes it is easy to forget that the mask is not who we are... Our "true self" is actually those multiple selves whom we sometimes hide, sometimes briefly reveal, sometimes try to forget...

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Watcher

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Cryptosculptures are digitally created contemporary sculptures.
With these works I develop and deepen artistic understanding of how industrial design approach might be used for creation the unique pieces of art. This practice aims to merge design with art, thus erasing the line between them. I think in the future there will be no readable difference between these two disciplines whereas any functional object or device will look as a piece of art the same way as in art we’ll see a design elements used as a normal practice.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Ineffable

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:

Psychedelic digital painting combined with generative art is my new favorite tool to create something truly unique and rare .

Shaman too uses one of these techniques . 
Shaman (Day) reflects the time of shaman when he is deep meditation inside Deep jungle.

Shaman (Night) reflects the time when shaman is under DMT trip and is able to see his distorted face in water.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Parasite Family Portrait #1
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Parasite Family is a series of work made from an archive of film negatives I discovered in an out-of-business film lab. When I was a child, individuals would come to this community film lab to get a photograph taken for business purposes. In digital era, however, these film labs were shut down. In a way, these negatives are like a memory of my society.

In this project, I experimented with the film negatives through various techniques – collage, color-grading, re-printing, and re-mixing.  For the piece minted at Async, I created a 'living' family portrait which changes from daytime to nighttime.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Making Memories
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"...I could leave these shores,
I could sail home, I could
take something with me,
I could leave something in
return, and at that word
it came back, alive."
---from Vapor Wake by Mary Ruefle

This is a 2 x 2 x 2 series. 2 states, 2 photographs, 2 artworks. Making Memories and Taking Memories are  out of town fun on the road. Photographs are from 1997. 

As I've read or heard somewhere not that long ago, possibly by Slavoj Zizek or my mind plays with me -- he was saying that memories are meaningful only if photographed. It would not mean much to have memories if there was no way store them. 

He of whoever it was meant to say that memory making, memory taking and memory recalling are interlinked. Logically, emotionally, socially and economically.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Allegory Of Bitcoin

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Butterfly #1
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: According to one theory, the creative process is the organizing of the imagination. Judging by the colors, I have a wild imagination. Organizing it, I added wings. I got the Butterfly, but you might see something different. My butterflies turned out to be somewhat ominous. I experience this state from time to time. However, I want to learn how to control this and I am working on it. The theme of this series is self-improvement, since the butterfly is the main symbol of the transformation from crawling-ugly to soaring-sublime. This topic will be close to those who aspire to become the best version of themselves. As for the controversial black-red tandem; these have been my favorite colors for a long time. However, due to their aggressiveness, I was ashamed of this. In the Butterflies series, I gave freedom to my feelings. After that my art began to shine with a new, infinitely varied range of colors.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Artwork Title: Experimental No.3 #8816
Date of Artwork: 2021
Dimension: 1666 pixel x 2160 pixel
Type of Work: Silver Gelatin Photogram, Digital Painting
Edition: Unique
Note: This artwork is a type of digital art. The hand-made photogram is one of the subjects that compose this piece, and this photogram is not for sale separately whatever in the crypto world or the real world.

Notwithstanding, the beginning of the photography is representational, it ultimately leads to the way of the abstract. Photography has nothing to do with painting, although the thinking of abstractness renders them getting closer and closer. Photography remains the interpretation of "Light", and to express the “Light” is its inescapable responsibility. I find the "Line" could be one of the forms to present the "Light". I apply the "Line", also is the "Light", to destroy a completed and finished photograph, and change it into a new form of art and have a unique way of spreading and viewing. Through this new attempt to keep looking for balance and harmony.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Say It's Possible
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
15 years ago I wrote a song called “Say It’s Possible,” and the song changed my life. 

I went from an unknown artist to the most subscribed musician on YouTube at the time. Thousands of people around the world created their own cover videos of my song. I won the inaugural YouTube Award for Best Music Video, signed deals with Universal Music Publishing and Island Records, played solo at Wembley Stadium, toured all over Europe and the UK. My experience in the major label music industry was a whirlwind ride that ultimately did not serve my best interests, and it took years of dismantling, reprogramming, and letting go of painful experiences and toxic relationships in order to find my way back to my pure love of music and the joy that comes from sharing it. 

This year I reclaimed the rights to my earliest songs from Universal Music, with the intention of recording new versions and giving these songs a life they never had. I am starting with my Async Music project: an interactive, collaborative version of my song "Say It's Possible." There are 460 possible configurations of the song and corresponding visual art, ranging from pure acoustic guitar and vocals to a lush arrangement with 13 different layers of sound.

I wrote, played, and recorded all of the music in my home studio, creating the parts in a modular way, like a puzzle, knowing the track would have to make sense in any configuration. My dear friend MG O’Shea helped with the mix, carving out frequencies to ensure all the parts would sound excellent together, in any combination. Every mix begins in the same way, like the song itself began, with acoustic guitar and vocals, evolving into something more after the first verse. Some of the changes can be subtle and some can be striking. 

The visual art is a series of self-portraits I created in the process of freeing myself from the expectations and demands placed on me by an industry that did not support me as the innovative and individualistic artist that I am.

One collector can own the Master. Up to five collectors of the individual stems (vocals, guitar, drums + percussion, bass + strings, bells + synths) will control the master mix and album cover art. A limited number of “blank records”(2,000 silver, 10 gold, 3 platinum) are also available. You can collect a blank record in advance and mint your version as soon as you hear something you love. And if you do hear something you love, mint it at that time, because we might never stumble upon that particular mix again! 

These song versions and cover art will not be released anywhere outside of this project, and the NFT you collect will be a rare and unique piece of my history and evolution as a self-actualized, independent artist.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Ride or Die
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
“Ride or Die” is PLS&TY’s newest single release in collaboration with Barbados-born soul singer, Bobby Saint. 

Tommy Leas, a Florida native - better known as PLS&TY - is burgeoning into the electronic dance music scene with his unique sound: languid bass, captivating vocals and enough upbeat melodies to make anybody feel good. After a collection of chart topping singles including "Good Vibes" (#1 on iTunes US Electronic Charts), "Down For Me", "Rebel Love (#1 on iTunes US Electronic Charts), and "Motives" (#1 on iTunes US Electronic Charts / Top 25 Billboard Electronic Charts), PLS&TY would see his productions Remixed by Grammy nominated Morgan Page, Rusko, Cazzette, Bondax, YehMe2 (Josh from Flosstradamus latest venture), and more. 

His music has amassed over 100 million listens across streaming platforms, and has been placed in nationally airing television commercials, including a Hershey's Chocolate campaign which has been viewed over 1 BILLION times. Prior to “Ride or Die”, PLS&TY kept busy with a 2019 touring season that included A-List electronic festivals Shaky Beats, Breakaway, Electric Forest, EDC Vegas, & more, along with the release of his “Very Special” EP, which included pop records with artists like Sean Kingston, Wifisfuneral, & Alex Aiono (of Netflix’s “Finding Ohana”).

“Ride or Die” is a summertime, feel-good single that encompasses love & romance. Saint’s vocals lead listeners to imagine time spent in tropical paradise with their partner. Now in programmable format on Async Music, users can select alternate variations of the stems that comprise the master track. In this way, the master track dynamically shifts and promotes adventure, like the upbeat tune itself that is “Ride or Die”.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: LayerBreaker
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This is a collaboration born out of community. The idea being what can we do with a global economy and technology which enables trustless relationships. 

62 artists were involved from over 20 countries. None of whom ever met in person, yet one of the largest collaboration to date took place. 

There are 61 layers, 284 states for this project. 

The gradient was made by color expert Jeff Davis. Each artist was assigned a HEX code and then given total freedom to create. This creates a gradient look for the master while allowing the artists to dream and share their creative expression with few restrictions. 

There are some hidden features within this project and the purpose is to enable the community of collectors to continue on with the creative process. 

We hope you enjoy exploring LayerBreaker. We certainly enjoyed creating it!

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"...I could leave these shores,
I could sail home, I could
take something with me,
I could leave something in
return, and at that word
it came back, alive."
---from Vapor Wake by Mary Ruefle

This is a 2 x 2 x 2 series. 2 states, 2 photographs, 2 artworks. Making Memories and Taking Memories are  out of town fun on the road. Photographs are  from 1997. 

As I've read or heard somewhere not that long ago, possibly by Slavoj Zizek or my mind plays with me -- he was saying that memories are meaningful only if photographed. It would not mean much to have memories if there was no way store them. 

He of whoever it was meant to say that memory making, memory taking and memory recalling are interlinked. Logically, emotionally, socially and economically.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Cryptosculptures are digitally created contemporary sculptures.
With these works I develop and deepen artistic understanding of how industrial design approach might be used for creation the unique pieces of art. This practice aims to merge design with art, thus erasing the line between them. I think in the future there will be no readable difference between these two disciplines whereas any functional object or device will look as a piece of art the same way as in art we’ll see a design elements used as a normal practice.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Tenement
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
'Tenement' is simple concept that invites users to control the illumination of an urban building facade.

It is for anyone who has ever gazed out of a high-rise at night and wondered what the myriad of other inhabitants may be doing, and is meant to invoke the natural human curiosity that occurs when we see a light on in a building. 

In the real world, within every apartment lies the day-to-day hopes, dreams, failures and successes of other people. Who are they? What could they be doing? If the lights are off, where might they be? Viewers are thus given the opportunity to suggest and imagine the stories contained behind each of the windows. 

Apartment locations are assigned by grid running from A-G on rows and 1-6 on each column, with the position indicated on each thumbnail.

Each apartment can be lit with warm light, cool light, red/rose light or switched off, allowing layer owners to play or communicate through the various light states.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Julia
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: In this piece, I applied the ideas and stylistics of such art movements in painting as pointillism, suprematism and color field painting to art photography. While developing the color field light painting, I added to it the geometric micro-shapes. As a result, I got a technique, which I called a suprematist color field (I will publish artwork in this technique later). Continuing to experiment, I combined the suprematist color field with the classic nude. As a result, I got another technique - suprematist pointillism. This artwork is done in this technique.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Sucofi #155381
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: While developing the color field light painting, I added to it the geometric micro-shapes. As a result, I got a technique, which I called a suprematist color field. This artwork is done in this technique.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Experimental No.3 #1998
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Artwork Title: Experimental No.3 #1998
Date of Artwork: 2021
Dimension: 1738 pixel x 2160 pixel
Type of Work: Silver Gelatin Photogram, Digital Painting
Edition: Unique
Note: This artwork is a type of digital art. The hand-made photogram is one of the subjects that compose this piece, and this photogram is not for sale separately whatever in the crypto world or the real world.

Notwithstanding, the beginning of the photography is representational, it ultimately leads to the way of the abstract. Photography has nothing to do with painting, although the thinking of abstractness renders them getting closer and closer. Photography remains the interpretation of "Light", and to express the “Light” is its inescapable responsibility. I find the "Line" could be one of the forms to present the "Light". I apply the "Line", also is the "Light", to destroy a completed and finished photograph, and change it into a new form of art and have a unique way of spreading and viewing. Through this new attempt to keep looking for balance and harmony.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Scenes from the Show
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Scenes from the Show is from a show about three women who have been hurt, reacted and consequently suffered. Their efforts were not in vain but not all were able to survive the ordeal. I should, with the blockchain as my witness, thank my daughter for being a part of this show and facilitating my presence as a photographer on site.

The photographs have been taken during the rehearsals in 2019. I had the opportunity to take a wide variety of shots out of which I have handpicked a few for Scenes from the Show. The photographs were edited multiple times during the period leading up to this artwork.

The show is about their courage. It is about their will not to be broken under adverse conditions of parents, lovers and all forms of authority that  prevent them to be with no hesitation to resort to use of brute force. All these women have broken the boundary and turned the tables on the assaulters of various kinds. The  effort was extraordinary yet human. The cost.. The cost was momentous however way you look at it.

Technically, I wished to push the bar higher with Scenes from the Show and introduced 9 layers (+1 static layer) with 16 states in each of them. I've done the whole work twice over as I tested a 16 x 16 alternative that I gave up due to screen being divided more than how I envisaged. Purely mathematically speaking the current probability outcome of different images is (9 layers with 16 states) 9 to the power of 16. The math comes out as 1,853,020,188,851,841 that is 1.8 quadrillion combinations. A 70 year life with no sleep and 1 click at every second yields 2,207,520,000 images for the life time. That is it would take 800,000 lifetimes to go through all the combinations. All the more reason to get couple of layers and decide at-will to manage the odds.

"Through dirt and over street. The dancer falls Then rises like an oriole over walls." -from Dancer: Four Poems by Paul Engle (4-2). Like this one each layer is referred by a small selection from a poem by Paul Engle. Incredibly lovely words, I am in admiration of this gentle petite work speaking soft meaning a lot. Each of the 16 states are named after female dancers that have made a mark in history. With them I took the liberty to select and the naming convention was quite random as I used first names, stage names and surnames with different dancers depending on how it sounded and looked. Last under the naming convention are the layer names which are my titles for the photographs I built this work upon.

There are at least 9 beautiful images in this vast set. I have clicked through and have come across a lot of inspiring visuals. However more than that, this work is a study in chance. The collector(s) holding this artwork will only see a fraction of possible outcomes. It sort of reminds me of the stories from The Book of Sand by Jorge Luis Borges. The same page or the same story will not be found again. Something similar will come up perhaps. Each story will take a lifetime. The book will merge with life. 

I wished this work to be outrageous. Visually artistic but numerically absurd. It gives two options to the Collector and/or the Viewer. One is to accept life aka the image as it is. Let the randomness speak and take it. The other is to make a choice, to change  the odds by the force of will - wherever and to whatever it may lead. The second is done by the choices on the collection of layers and about which states will prevail at the time.

This creation will live on the blockchain. I hope many years from now on, it will still cause some interest and a lonely only girl or boy would click a few buttons with the mind, look at it  and smile at the futility of life and the incessant desire to shape it by some of us.

June - August 2021
Hulki Okan Tabak

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Cuddle
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Humankind seeks affection. I have wondered many a time whether it is to love or to be loved that matters. There is a profound rabbit hole on that topic but Cuddle is more basic, more innocent, gullible even, modestly carnal, mostly emotional.

Cuddle's front layer is an abstraction from a segment of a project. That piece has been re-created in my imaginary depiction of two people hugging, holding, cuddling each other in the most basic confines of line-art abstraction.

Behind the Cuddle runs a gamut of photographs for different times of the day as Async Art's engine throttles through the incessant 24 hour interval of our lives. Sunrise hits with a garden shot of flowers in the morning from 2020. Day invigorated with an image from 25 years ago of a sun casting shadows through shutters. Sunset is a stylization of a female figure from a 1990 photograph that went through an extensive 2021 Photoshop session. Night uses a public domain photo in a subtle abstract yet attractive manner.

All through the cuddle remains the constant. Our need to express and to be heard and to be cared and to care. For most of the healthy ones at least..

Idea and execution and minting and the rest by HoT, sometime during the summer of 2021 on Aysnc Art as a Day/Night template project.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Zombie
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Zombie highlights on all the man made activities that have made our human mankind predator on earth for other organisms. Humans have ecologically disturbed even the mightiest whales to tiny rats and crabs.

We all love after-the-bomb stories. If we didn't, why would there be so many of them? There's something attractive about all those people being gone, about wandering in a depopulated world, scrounging cans of Campbell's pork and beans, defending one's family from marauders.

When you expect the world to end at any moment, you know there is no need to hurry. The biggest lies we save for ourselves. We play a game in which we are gods, in which we make choices, and the current follows in our wake. We pretend a separation from the wild. Forgetting we too are from this wild and don't think about giving something back good to nature.

Gan A.I generated base layer hand touched digitally inside Procreate and Adobe After Effects for Post Effects.
Four paintings , Four Generative art result and yes four times the fun.

She will make you laugh and she knows what scares you. Everything she is now, is a role she was designed for. She has never known anything else. She does not understand guilt or despair. She does not make mistakes. Her Story. Her Rules.

To her Enemies:	
“I am the insect that just flew right into your skull!”

To her Collector:
“You will be my crypto-master, and I will protect you.”

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Garden of One
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"Garden of One" from creator and photographer Jeremy Cowart is an abstract, passing-of-time, Lightograph NFT powered by Async Art. 

Multiple pictures of the single rose were photographed, while Cowart intentionally moved light through the space. 24 images were selected, then collaged together, in order to create a dawn to dusk sort of feel. Async Art's signature time-synchronized approach emphasizes this evolution of light through the course of a day, based upon the creator's timezone. 

If the collector so desires, a physical print of one selected stage of the "Garden of One" can be provided. 

A "Lightograph" is the patent-pending photography innovation invented by Cowart that evolves light through a still image. No 3D software is used in the process. Learn more at Lightograph.com and JeremyCowart.com.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Is That  a Whale?
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Staring at an alien landscape, you wonder if the actual alien is the place or you yourself. Looking outward because you can't look the other way, you spot a figure familiar from books of some other childhood. There in the distance to your right, or whatever direction this strange place permits, swims a big figure of folk and lore alike. You can't contain the excitement. You can ignore the people supposedly serious stern sharp shipshape indeed around you. You can not ignore yourself. You shout. You shout inadvertently. IS THAT A WHALE?

Minted 2021 on Async Art by Hulki Okan Tabak

Based on photographs of things and places. Edited to abstraction through age and tear. Refigured reconfigured reimagined as a story of whales and alienation.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Burnt Out
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Overworking is not something estranged to doctors;
burnout is something quite common. This work desires
to convey this state of emotional exhaustion, physical
fatigue, and loss of connection to purpose. Before the
state of burnout fully manifests, the professional
undergoes a gradual process where they end up
feeling drained, trapped, or defeated and maywithdraw from responsibilities, isolate, skip work or
assume the use of drugs.
These often result from the prolonged stress of work
pressure, which may often develop into an attitude of
cynicism towards daily work, a detachment towards
patients, or may doubt if at all they're making a
difference. Some may be worried that their own issues
go unresolved while they're busy worrying about those
of others.
So much can condescend one into this course state of
mental and emotional dryness.
This work cracks open the misery lying behind our
uninformed surficial conceptions about the life of
doctors.

"I photographed a boy running away from me down the street. He reminded me of my childhood going further and further into the past from me. Childhood is a wonderful time when the foundations of our psyche and our attitude to the world are formed. However, according to Eric Berne, our psyche includes three different states: child, parent and adult. It turns out that our inner child does not disappear anywhere, but lives in us to the end. This work is dedicated to him and all of our inner children"

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Revenge of Kim (2012-2021)
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Presenting to the viewer a dramatically charged scene of a killer robot. Based off of a painting of Rubens with the theme of the legend of a Saint, this painting becomes more than a critic of art history. Influenced also by the Artist's recent tours of Japan and China, multiple meanings can be extracted from the contemporary work originally titled,  "The Revenge of Asia"
The viewer is confronted with an armed robot and a fire breathing dragon, both reminiscent of mythology and legend that combine story elements from the west and east. This work of art also becomes part of a larger critique on current issues revolving around the relationship between these two powers. Combining also the past and present, the modern technologically advanced robot rides waves that remind the viewer of ancient Asian scroll paintings. Today, these waves could symbolize rising ocean levels. The horizon which is made gold, reminds us not only of the commerce of art history but also becomes a reflection of Asia's current pollution problems as it obscures the sun in its haze. The ruthless dictator and human rights violator Kim Jong-un placed alongside new and amazing technological advancements give rise to questions about the true purpose of this new technology and also which political leaders that could control them.

Set to Tokyo time, in observance of the Olympic Games of 2021.
This artwork, which was originally created in 2012, and added to the blockchain a decade later, represents a shift from the immortal history of great painting as we move to a digital creator's economy.
Ironically, this artwork was conceived before the pandemic and the great rising tides that plague our earth and human condition.  Will the block-chain give rise to a larger awareness of the pressing issues of man-kind?

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Draconian
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The Draconian sculpture transforms over the course of 24 hours, evolving from molten, to gold, and finally lunar form. 

This sculpture aims to bring about a sense of growth and progress regardless of external factors, only determined by time as a constant. The dark, chiaroscuro aesthetic evokes a sense of mystery, representing my philosophy of improving and evolving in self shrouded mystery.

The autonomous art piece is synced to the time-zone of Singapore, the artist's and art piece's country of origin.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Nihtegale. Stranger and Friend.
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
You are what it is to be a song, and here I am to be a stranger, that identifies with you. They do not see although they do. some green perhaps, and your sweet air. They are looking at you now, and they are looking at me.

This is the portrait of a bird and the imagined stranger that tells of it at different times of the day. The imagination as a storytelling self makes this a portrait of the bird, the stranger, and also of me.
This work is based on my readings related to avian aurality and lore in England from the 7th to the 10th century, with particular interest in Riddle 8 of the Exeter Book, which is seemingly the only surviving instance of the nightingale in Old English text.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: She VII for the Day
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
She is a series I mint occasionally and She VII 's base image was minted on Foundation at https://foundation.app/@athenanovo/she-vii-58818. It is an image I've re-imagined from public domain source and I thought a variation piece with Async Art's 24 piece 24 hour template would be a perfect piece to use for variations on the image. I believe the result turned out to be beautiful, interesting and somewhat striking while not being overtly loud. I hope you enjoy the creation as much as I do.

She VII for the Day minted by Athena Novo on Async Art, 2021

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Experimental No.3 #1068
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Artwork Title: Experimental No.3 #1068
Date of Artwork: 2021
Dimension: 2160 pixel x 1676 pixel
Type of Work: Silver Gelatin Photogram, Digital Painting
Edition: Unique
Note: This artwork is a type of digital art. The hand-made photogram is one of the subjects that compose this piece, and this photogram is not for sale separately whatever in the crypto world or the real world.

Notwithstanding, the beginning of the photography is representational, it ultimately leads to the way of the abstract. Photography has nothing to do with painting, although the thinking of abstractness renders them getting closer and closer. Photography remains the interpretation of "Light", and to express the “Light” is its inescapable responsibility. I find the "Line" could be one of the forms to present the "Light". I apply the "Line", also is the "Light", to destroy a completed and finished photograph, and change it into a new form of art and have a unique way of spreading and viewing. Through this new attempt to keep looking for balance and harmony.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: La Passion
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This work has a backstory that I would like to share, as it has struck a chord with me. A couple of years ago, I was strolling along an embankment with my artist friend, while we discussed art and its creators. One question in particular drove a wedge between us - what is more important for the creator, passion or patience? After a long discussion, we parted, each with his own opinion. A month later, I made this piece and sent it to him. Unfortunately, our communication has come to naught, however this discussion remains important to me.

In 2021, I completely reworked this piece, changing the shades and shapes, while only the essence remained the same. I also created a black & white version especially to show the detail and volume, as colour distracts attention from them.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Day begins with Fluid Prophecy where the dancer is enjoying a solo spot under the spotlights. Daylight follows Together under the Spotlights where two lead dancers are in a duet of colorful lights.

Night commences with Pull which is taken from the third act and the protagonist is being wound up metaphorically and physically. Rest of the night is the disturbing image of To Break Free with scant hope of escape for the leading woman of the third act.

Photography by Hulki Okan Tabak from 2019. Photoshoot from dress rehearsals of a dance project about three women and the hardships they endured. Edited various times with final edit on June 2021 to be minted on Async Art.

This has been a very intense photoshoot and gorgeous performance by the whole group. Further chapters in the series may be released depending on collector interest.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Crimson Awaiting
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Working with an A.I. can create some beautiful and chaotic pieces. A single tweak to a gene can drastically change the art that is produced. Crimson Awaiting was conceived after the G.A.N. I use gave me the first image of this piece. I enjoyed it but decided to change a few elements here and there. That gave me the second image. From there I kept up this process. The changes are meant to be subtle so that the core of the first image is always present but each image is still distinct from the one that came before it. Initially Crimson Awaiting was a project I worked on for fun but it feels like the ideal piece to list on Async using their 24 hour template.

Type of Work: Silver Gelatin Photogram, Digital Darkroom
Edition: Unique
Note: This artwork is a type of digital art. The hand-made photogram is one of the subjects that compose this piece, and this photogram is not for sale separately whatever in the crypto world or the real world.

The photograph on 00:00 is the original photogram, and the image on 23:00 is the digital-inverted version of the original piece. I am concerned about are the rest of the twenty-two images in this piece. They can be deemed as the procedures of the chemical reaction in the darkroom. I reversed the habitual way of seeing the photograph and applied an unexpected, counterintuitive but logical method based on the new techs to view a photogram and its Contact Print.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Ever since I trolled the walls of Abbey Road Studios for graffiti to photograph, I am telling that such work was tokenized graffiti. I have taken the photographs that make up this artwork first as a broad representation of the poster work and then selectively chosen where to focus before the final visual edits and choices. These underlying photographs have led to the Day and Night cycles of this AsyncArt piece.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Divided
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This artwork is composed of two cycles day and night.
The day represents a happy setting while the dark a more gloomy abstract place.
A surrealism setting formed around this skeleton of our inner helper reaching for the divided.

Sometimes all is divided. The struggle happens in day and night. A man wants to speak but is afraid. He thinks, sinking into his thoughts, imagining scenarios in which they are in love... The women believes she is at fault, as the man does not speak to her, but struggles to engage herself to break to the root. Love deteriorates, and the push becomes greater. Help then. This artwork stems from the society that we today live in. Should the women make the move first and accept to get rejected, or should the man do so accepting that he might get rejected? Both should be seen as signs of encouragement.  Maybe there is a third hand helping.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: To be, is to feel
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
During the lockdown, I stumbled upon the use of AI and the generation of visuals using GANs. I began getting intrigued by questions like how does a machine think up visuals? What goes through its “mind/consciousness” while doing so? Does it possess a mind or a consciousness like humans do? If these machines could think, could they feel too?

This last question stuck in my head and became something I constantly found myself returning to. I began thinking more; could I create an NFT piece that could emote and feel? 

I researched how emotions work in humans to see if I could replicate the same as an interactive Async piece. Human emotions are due to a few chemical components; to break it down, it is predominantly controlled by neurotransmitters. The most common ones are Adrenaline, Dopamine, Serotonin and the rest being Noradrenaline, GABA, Acetylcholine, Glutamine. Each neurotransmitter controls different emotions in a human being. 

This piece tries to emulate the functioning of the human brain. The emotional mess/bliss that every human lands up with is due to different compositions and combinations of these chemical concoctions. Buyers could purchase each of these “neurotransmitters” as individual layers, therefore giving them a chance to interact with the piece and decide how it "feels”, what it feels. 

With each layer owned by different human identities, they interact and their own emotions at that point of time could reflect in the changes they make to the piece. This gives rise to unique and infinite possibilities, just like the human mind.  

After all, what is existence if one cannot feel?

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
As the hours tick away… remember who you are and where you are today.

You ARE liquid electric stardust with heart of gold and a sparkling diamond mind swimming with billions hopes, dreams, fears, loves, and tears.

You are a living, breathing, and completely unique human being dancing on the edge of a galaxy flying through the Universe.

Why not look at life through rose colored lenses?

About This Space: Messier 107 is one of more than 150 globular star clusters found around the disc of the Milky Way galaxy. These spherical collections each contain hundreds of thousands of extremely old stars and are among the oldest objects in the Milky Way.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Idea of Saving Aesthetics - Time Edition
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Historically, carpets play a significant role in forming Azerbaijan & Middle East’s heritage and aesthetics. Different carpet schools share the same ornamental forms, such as geometric patterns, floral motifs, and calligraphic shapes, but some of the combinations are specific to certain regions. Today, the word ‘pattern’ is often associated with machine algorithms that recognize regularities in data. Orkhan designed an AI algorithm to analyze carpet designs and traditional ornaments. After processing the collected data, the neural network system is producing imaginary patterns that could have been Azerbaijani or similar, but all of them never really existed. The installation The Idea of Saving Aesthetics explores data as a fruitful and yet thoroughly problematic resource for artistic inspiration in the turbulent epoch of global nomadism, uneven cultural diffusion, and rising nationalist movements.

According to historic data and memo records of European researchers and travelers, Mediaeval Azerbaijan was one of the major carpet hubs of the Orient, and after the Islamic Golden age, most of the middle eastern carpet patterns and ornaments became popularized by the western countries. While in Azerbaijan, carpet weaving was primarily a dominating form of art, with the traditions and skills carefully passed over from one generation to another, through developing and improving methods of making and spreading crafted symbols. By approaching these representations of our nation’s cultural history, with the help of AI, we get a dialogue between the future and the past, dystopian and utopian.

In this exhibition, the artist highlights the source and meaning of ornaments with the background history and regional source of them. During the exhibition experience, visitors will be able to witness current locations and uses of the embroideries all over the world.

Premiered at Moscow contemporary art Biennale 2019. Moscow, Russia.
This art installation has been in the collection of Russian Federation The State Tretyakov Gallery since 2020.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Expected Behavior
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
What if we had a place to send our perceived bugs in this messed up simulation we call life?

'Expected Behavior' is a dark comedy collaboration between paleh0rs3 and GPT-3 AI. It imagines a disillusioned entity responsible for our simulation using a Kafkaesque task management tool to track the terribleness all around us.

The layers in this project were designed to take full advantage of the tool's UI: on the board there are 15 cards containing bugs submitted by humans to our simulation overlords. These bugs were co-written by paleh0rs3 and GPT-3 based on extensive prompting and refining. Each ticket slot contains the title of two bugs, changeable by each owner.

There's also a right hand pane to display the expected resolution for 20 of the bugs, a left hand 'Feedback' mechanism to unleash 25 mass punishments on the simulation's inhabitants, and an upper right push notification to give swift punishment to 10 individuals confessing their darkest sins.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Looking Deeper
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: This piece is based on a photographic chemigram, an image created using a camera-less approach to recording marks on photographic paper.  My work is centered in a sense of wonder and curiosity, and takes its cues from forces of nature - in this case, life at a cellular level.  The cellular metaphor encourages me to think of hidden mysteries that can only be seen and appreciated by looking deeper, past the surface, into the depths of a thing.   Careful attention and thoughtful consideration so often seems a discarded thing of the past, and I find it impoverishing.  In my images, I hope to speak to the heart, reminding us all to stop and see, slow down and appreciate.  I hope to capture an ephemeral wisp of the intangible and share it, as two children might press their heads together to gaze in awe at something captured in a cupped hand.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Experimental No.1 #5642
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Artwork Title: Experimental No.1 #5642
Date of Artwork: 2021
Dimension: 3840 pixel x 3020 pixel
Type of Work: Silver Gelatin Photogram, Digital Darkroom
Edition: Unique
Note: This artwork is a type of digital art. The hand-made photogram is one of the subjects that compose this piece, and this photogram is not for sale separately whatever in the crypto world or the real world.

Changes is the only thing that hasn’t been changed. From time to space to the thoughts of human beings are constantly changing. I transformed a Silver Gelatin Photogram (a piece of physical photograph made of alternative photographic processes) into a digital image that even can produce endless changes. This is based on the change in my way of seeing the world. It is difficult for individuals to completely isolate themselves from their own inherent culture, this ingrained imprint not only stems from families but also social and historical influences. Besides, the rapid innovation of science and technologies directly drives the world today to inevitably facing collisions and fusions in multiculturalism. Studying classical philosophical text allows me to apply the dialectical method to tease those open questions, and finally ground on my artworks. All things complement each other and balance in the collision. Changes is the key. Isn’t the development of human civilization that come to the present evolve in indistinct ways?

Contents included #5642 Master Layer (Day), #5642 Master Invert Layer (Night), #5642 the invert version of the Master Solarize Layer (Sunrise), #5642 Master Solarize Layer (Sunset).
