0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The 25th message
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
24 women. 24 messages. Every hour you get a message from time zones covering the entire planet. They use characters from their own languages to write the universal word: peace. A multicultural, multiethnic, and multilingual planetary request: PEACE.

But seems there is an error: UTC +05:00 is the Universal Standard Time for Kazakhstan, Tajikistan, Pakistan, Turkmenistan, Uzbekistan… but not Afghanistan, which is the only country in the world UTC+04:30. 
…
The Sharia law started half an hour ago. 
Once again, we were late. Again system error. 
This “undercover” message from Kabul is the 25th message.
Details here: 
https://www.theneimus.com/neimu-ludovico/the-25th-message

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This artwork changes four times a day. 
This project is based on my daily observations and how I interpret them using surrealism.

Day:
"A man drinks and drinks and eats and eats... In the end we see ourselves out paced by women. Our heart is given to them and so is our brain and so on... To be honest its all in their hand."
A surrealistic place representing man's quick daily food consumption, and drinking and others and others, in like a day.
Night:
"Is that thing watching me? .... Bodies decay. A form of rust takes our bodies and honestly its inevitable. Our hearts disappear slowly, disintegrating. But look the fat man, I thought he was big boned. He is just like the others."
A surrealistic place where rusting represents a decaying body. and we are being watched by the big brother, which always could be at night.
Sunrise:
"Heaven was kinda a ... disappointing place."
A surrealistic place describing, well, heaven. 
Sunset:
" I win a chess game but I lost the real game... the life one."
In this I don't know exactly. I imagined this while I was playing chess, and while feeling really bad for the horse. Anyway decided to compose it in a surrealistic place representing the revenge of the horse.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Gates of Delerium - Battle Scene
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
1976: Battle Scene – Confrontation, Attack, Impact (My View)

Each man, each side
Is fighting for a cause,
A cause they believe is right.
They believe so much
That their cause is right
That their deaths become righteous
And in their own eyes – 
Pure.
But the whiteness –
Of their fighting bodies –
Is pallid;
Of their pure, righteous acts – 
Is tinged with blackness;
Of their souls –
Is stained with blood.


The inspiration for the original 1976 painting was the song, “The Gates of Delerium” by Yes, off the album “Relayer”. The specific lyrics which relate to the painting are:

“Choose and renounce throwing chains to the floor
Kill or be killing faster sins correct the flow
Casting giant shadows off vast penetrating force
To alter via the war that’s seen
As friction spans the spirit’s wrath ascending (slowly) to redeem…

…The fist will run
Grasp metal to gun
The spirit sings in rushing tones we gain the battle drum
Our cries will shrill, the air will moan and crash into the dawn
The pen won’t stay the demon’s wings, the hour approaches
Pounding out the devil’s sermon”

Day:
We all are stuck inside a glass box. We need to break it and not be afraid of it. 3D artwork composed of a women stuck inside a glass box struggling.

Night:
She broke out. Now she enjoys life but searching for something she cannot find. Maybe she needs to go inside the box again? 3D artwork composed of a SEARCH.

I find the idea somewhat nostalgic, as if the action is based on the relationship between people, whether the conversation or questioning has taken place or not.

Colours chosen are bright pink and purple with white text, all words have been hand written with an oversized brush size to make them less legible. The shapes form a kind of comic book thought bubble where the pronouns used are changed every hour over a twenty four hour period.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Sketches from a Time of Conflict
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This piece is about finding solace and leaning on a bit of escapism in time of stress and conflict that one can not overcome by herself / himself.

Sketches from a Time of Conflict finds its inspiration from the works of the Jewish surrealist painter Felix Nussbaum.  Loosely based on his imagery and more firmly based on the sense of foreboding creeping in to his work, the digital sketches here are an extension of Nussbaum inspired characters I have created and minted from 2020 to 2021.

The original names I had given to the underlying artworks for this final collective piece were:
Sunrise - That Which is in Limbo
Day - Limbo One Sketch
Sunset - One of the Elders
Night - Dreaming of Another One

As they are integrated in to this Async Art piece, their identity becomes a collective now as part of Sketches from a Time of Conflict. They will not appear as individual mints so I provided the names to the prospective Collector as part of the artwork's history.

I've terribly enjoyed working on this material and I hope you shall enjoy hosting for a future generation and passing on the word of peace, understanding and constructive affirmation of diversity even in times of duress.

Sketches from a Time of Conflict
Minted 2021 on Async Art by Hulki Okan Tabak

Garhwali Language is spoken in Uttarakhand,  it is nonetheless designated as "vulnerable" in UNESCO's Atlas of the World's Languages in Danger, which indicates that the language requires consistent conservation efforts.
 
People who live in Garhwal Himalayas have long since learned humility, patience and a quiet resignation. Deep in the crouching mist lie their villages.

I have spent a lifetime in the mountains. And if I had to do it all over again, I would still choose to spend my life here. Most Garhwali cultivators are poor, some are very poor. And yet these are cheerful people, sturdy and with wonderful powers of endurance.

This 4 series of artwork readily focus on theme of Garhwal processed in Generative art and digitally distorted manner with a vision from my eyes. Eyes that still have a vision to do something for its culture, its soil. Eyes that won't rest until Myaru Garhwal (My Garhwal) becomes a key point for attraction of entire world in terms of tourism and economy towards its culture.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Samurai of the Warring States
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The Samurai of the Warring State I 

The Sengoku period (戦国時代, Sengoku Jidai, "Warring States period") is a period in Japanese history of near-constant civil war, social upheaval, and political intrigue from 1467 to 1615. An anonymous poem captured the mood of the times. "A bird with one body but two beaks, pecking itself to death." However, it was also a time of significant cultural and economic growth. This was when legendary samurai like Saito Dosan, Takeda Shingen, Uesugi Kenshin, Tokugawa Ieyasu and Oda Nobunaga emerged as major players, consolidating the territories of their respective domains while encouraging the practice of arts like classical painting, architecture and the tea ceremony.

This is the first in a series of artworks that explore the Samurai of the Sengoku Period. A place of beauty and serenity and despair, torment and violence. Each layer has between 30 to 37 states that allow you to change the feel of the work. Change the background, the clouds, the birds, the insects, the fog, the skull, the helmet or the mask. There are over 416,965,528 non-repetitive combinations available in this work.  Change how you see each legendary samurai.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: all the beings that inhabit this body
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Tossing and turning as you plan tomorrow, there's so much that you'll leave out. You will wake up as a different being in this body. Your day will not go accordingly. Your plans will unfurl to their own liking. By night, you will have transformed once again. It did not go as planned, but you manifested all of it. All of your collected assumptions have hardened into reality. You will toss and turn some more, tempering your body to house a new set of fleeting thoughts tomorrow.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
It was the summer of 2019, I took a set of macro photographs over the course of two days in a beautiful small island garden. It was my intention to photograph beyond what I see and to do this I deep dived in to the macro world. The resulting outputs were then processed with filters I developed for the project on Photoshop. Afterwards I used some of the photographs in a Google Books project and minted couple of items on the ETH blockchain. One Day in the Mind Garden is the most significant artwork idea undertaken using these photographs. I have used 24 separate photographs for the project. 

One Day in the Mind Garden by Hulki Okan Tabak
Minted in the middle of the 2021 summer on Async Art

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Mind Mirror
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
We, humans, are social beings - we can instantly match with the emotions of the people around us. This is due to the fact that we have a particular type of brain cell called - mirror neuron. We emit our emotions and mirror the emotions of others around us. 

As organisms who emit and absorb emotions - it is important for us to be aware of the emotional rhythms and mental health of people around us - as we tend to cause them while also changing ourselves to it. 

Project Mind Mirror is a portal that would represent the collective emotions of our peers. 

Depending on the results of the poll from the dedicated Twitter page @theMindMirror we change the theme of a portal reflecting the emotion of the participants. A new poll would be put out every day and the results would be presented live in form of an abstract art in the mind mirror portal. 

The themes of the mind mirror portal would be one of the following,
 - The rejoice 
The portal would change its theme to green - the colour of prosperity and happiness. 

 - The content
The portal would change its theme to blue - the colour of calm and peace. 

 - The bothered 
The portal would change its theme to red - the colour of disturbance and anger. 

 - The depressed
The portal would turn into total darkness and black themed bypassing the rest of the votes if at least 30% of the participants have mentioned 'depressed'. Even a single depressed person is an alarm to the rest of us to watch out for the ones around us and empathise more.

—
Links:
1. Link to Mind Mirror portal: https://mind-mirror.000webhostapp.com/
2. Link to Twitter poll: https://twitter.com/theMindMirror

Acknowledgment: 
1. https://www.nature.com/articles/ncpneuro0990 [An article from nature on mirror neurons]

Privacy:
1. We don’t get to know the individual person who has replied to the poll. We have made use of the Twitter API to obtain the results. Only the population results are given to our disposal by Twitter.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Timepiece of Thades
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
In 2152 the first new world mission arrived on a planet located within it's sun's habitable zone that had become known to all as 'Thades'. Virtually the same distance from its own sun as our Earth is to its sun, the landing team hoped to discover a new society. Instead, what they found were the archaeological remains of a long dead technologically advanced civilization.

However, one of the alien artefacts discovered and still in working order within many of the crumbling structures on the planet, was a cycling projection of 24 images that have come to be known collectively as, 'The Timepiece of Thades'.

Much conjecture has been made over the true meaning of the symbols, but most most experts agree that each image was an individual visual representation of an hour on the planet, with the possibility of a further division of each of these hours by 5, as represented by the 5 glyphs that visually interact with one another. It has been also suggested that the Thadeans further divided their day into six 4 hour periods – as represented by the 6 changing backgrounds.

The Timepiece of Thades remains as the only working piece of technology ever to be found on the planet...

Artist's notes: 

The project started with the creation of 5 separate glyphs as clearly seen in the 12pm piece, I then rearranged and combined 5 glyph layers with each other, with a view to creating new forms and dynamic angles/juxtapositions that draw the viewer into each piece's composition.

The aim was to create a set of works that looked and felt as if they were alien artefact art that had simplistic roots based in a primitive time, yet that had also developed along with a technologically advanced society. The concept was that the pieces were used as a form of visual communication, in this case symbolizing the time of day on an alien civilization.

Features:

*Aspect Ratio of the artwork is created at 16:9, suitable for full-screen display on Apple TVs/Widescreen monitors/Smart TVs & Smart phones
*Lossless PNG format utilized means no matter displayed large or small, the quality will be flawless
*Timezone set to PST
*Autonomously changes 24 times in a day, on the hour, every hour (forever)
*Background also changes every 4 hours, a total of 6 times in 24 hours
*Each hour's image is a 1 of 1 abstract piece of artwork within its own right
*The first time I've used the landscape orientation for an NFT work
*My particular CMYK Hexadecimal values used throughout
*My first AsyncArt solo piece

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: LICHTKUGEL
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This work results from a series with 18 light drawings from 2004 long exposures, digitally processed, and the implementation in a light ball in 3D. However, the work "lichtkugel_schwarz" was never published.
As of 2010, due to cancer, I hardly had any more opportunities to work artistically because I was tired and had to worry about livelihood, so there is a big gap in my résumé. However, I continued to follow the developments of the Internet / digital media art without making my own contribution.
In May/July 2021 I started to be interested in NFT, so I completely reworked this piece. I started to remove the Pixels and did experiments. 

I was never looking for a specific style, I am more interested in individual social and cultural topics, these are then processed selectively and then lead to a result: the image and the text. (Conceptual Art/image experiments). But I do love this work and all works with light.

Async Art shows Art, that changes over time, so this will be my first artpiece at Async Art: Master; Day + Sunrise + Sunset + Night
3 Ownable Layers > not transparent (full JPG 3840x2160px;
computer monitors, display panels, mobiles) display best on landscape screens

BALL OF LIGHT by pjArtbasel 2021
Day/Night Timezone (GMT-06:00) Central America; 
Day is shown from 6am to 7pm and Night is shown from 7pm to 6am. 
Dimensions 3840x2160px HQ JPG

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: HIKIKOMORI
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
A Hikikomori is the Japanese word for a Shut-In, a person who does not leave his house at all, sometimes for decades. This is a growing problem, with about 2 Million people only in Japan being isolated in their homes away from society, and increasing all over the planet. This piece tries to bring awareness and convey the asphyxiating feeling of not being able to leave your room, it talks about depression and difficult times, it is a mirror of your comfort zone. It´s also a celebration of the good old times and childhood memories and a realization that things get better.

This artwork consists of two layers, Day and Night, that help reinforce the feeling of being a Hikikomori. I started making this piece during this year´s lockdown, in the span of 5 months and hundreds of hours I designed, 3d modelled and textured each one of the hundreds of elements in the scene which have been meticulously curated to fit the same 90s aesthetic.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Khôra's Monolith
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Jacques Derrida uses khôra to name a radical otherness that "gives place" for being. Khôra is the place where everything passes but in which nothing remains. The monolith exists in the center of the frame and its powers lift the space. It's a character that holds the space together and uplifts the whole world around it. The algorithmically generated terrain is here to represent the liminality of a space. Where is this place ? Does it have an essence ? It is a space without being a space. It is the other. The Monolith is the hero of this sensible realm.

A generated world, which is perceptible by sight and all the senses, by the name of earth or air or fire or water, or any aggregates or constituents there of: rather, if we describe her as a Kind invisible and unshaped, all-receptive, and in some most perplexing and most baffling way partaking of the intelligible, we shall describe her truly.
— Plato, Timaeus, 51a

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Homo Zombie Zombiens_Bernard
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
I set myself the task to portray the zombification of mankind.
The result is Homo Zombie Zombiens, a series of zombie portraits of the new man.
Homo Sapiens is no more, Homo Zombie Zombiens is here. You can see them
all around you or just by looking in your mirror.
We are all wounded. I hear a lot of talk about healing, but if you don’t see the wounds,
what can you heal?

I would like to investigate these wounds, cuts and holes. The decaying matter and the trident noses! 
Where are we heading? Is it into the zombie apocalypse?
If so, let’s go with some irony.
–
Homo Zombie Zombiens is going to showcase several portraits in a rich collection of designs.
The first HZZ is Bernard.
Bernard is mad about the rise of A.I.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Oneiric Ripples
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: A generative art piece where each layer has been created using the same algorithm with a slight variation of the base parameters. The layers change automatically each hour and the intensity of the pattern in the image varies from softer during the evening/night to more intense during daylight. For this creation I chose two set of colours: blue/violet and red. The contrast between cold and warm colours, their continuously changing position and the wavy pattern tend to create the same sensory experience I get when I’m dreaming or in deep sleep.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Collective Instinct
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This piece echoes the utter essentialness of collective instinct and teamwork for doctors and their teams in the healthcare setting. The trust built and the cohesion cemented reduces the chances of medical errors and develops a greater appreciation of each other's work. This phenomenal approach enables these professionals to better meet patient needs as a collective, and through shared responsibility, their tasks are smoothed and procedures timely executed. Observations and decisions made together guarantee them enhanced efficiency and effectiveness.
Exemplified is a classic case of workplace teamwork, something they execute so well that demands a heightened sense of social and relationship awareness.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The TV Of Tomorrow
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
In a series of animated short films from 1949, Tex Avery imagines a world that exists one hundred years in the future. Showcasing his predictions for the advancement of humanity, The TV Of Tomorrow's charmingly surreal visuals appear in stark contrast to an inadvertently out-of-date sense of humour, that by today’s standards, feels culturally obsolete.

Featuring two collages created from a single source of imagery (Zeit Online - August 21, 2021), this autonomous nft alternates its humorous predictions on the hour. Fated to become The TV Of Tomorrow, this artwork is intended to be viewed from the year 2050 onwards.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Metaverse
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: A depiction of a journey into the metaverse, where the collective consciousness operates as a unifying creative force. All for one and one for all.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: A Circadian Rhythm
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Time moves differently when you go for a walk. It is simultaneously fast and slow, both seamless and stuttering.

No matter how time decides to move around you, it will always cycle - even if that takes all day.


In this piece, 24 digital paintings make up a dynamic, looping animation that changes frame every hour. Copies of each painting at their original 3200x6400 resolution are available to the owner on request.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: "Vision of Persistence"
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"Vision of Persistence"
Continuing on my 40 year celebration, and as a marker for this place in time, I wanted to make something very special and have some personal meaning to me and those who can appreciate how long I have persisted with this vision.

So much has changed in digital art since I started in 1981. We were only just beginning to digitize real world objects and storing images in digital format. Back then I had the good fortune to become friends with some heavy hitters in the pioneering stages of our beloved industry. Fractals, computer generated art, virtual reality, even 3d rendering were known only to the supernerds and geek club guys like me.  Even then for those with vision we saw that eventually we would be where we are now. Thanks to my contacts and their constant inspiration and moral support I spent 35+ years making cgi and everything digital media my career. Retired from professional life I am now focusing completely on my art. I can never forget a few things said to me by my mentors.

"Never worry about the technology to achieve your artistic vision. Concentrate on your art and the tech will be there whenever you are ready for it." - Cliff Johnson "The Great OZ"

"Pay no attention to what is popular or trendy. Find a style and own it. Always be willing to adapt when new tools come along but stay true to yourself and your vision." - Ken Musgrave "Doc Mojo 

"The best stuff can be found at the boundary between order and chaos. It is in this zone where the real action is." - Benoit Mandelbrot "Uncle Benny"

This dynamic 24 hour autonomous piece "Vision of Persistence" is dedicated to all the "old guys" that encouraged and mentored me all along the way. Next stop? 50 yr. anniversary and fully immersive art experiences!

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: "Wild Compassion"
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This piece ushers in the call for stepping up to the challenge of passion and compassion. Doctors are called to more than mere technical proficiency, but to presence and engagement that suffuses an entire conversation; compassion, a quality paramount to patient welfare. It discards the notion that doctors need to maintain a professional distance from their patients.
Combing through scientific literature reveals that doctor compassion does more than just calm the nerves; it boosts the survival chance of cancer patients , reduces post-surgery pain, and can boost the immune system, to name a few.
Compassion binds together the doctor-patient relationship, a necessary kinship in managing and seeing through one's good chance of recovery.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: "Selfless"
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The thought of handling the span and fate of people's lives can often be very overwhelming and intimidating. The hefty task is not alone in dealing with the intense pressure; it also lies in gradually cultivating the in-grown patience necessary to withstand one from stepping away from the many health catastrophes of people's lives. The instinct impels many to try one last time, to continue probing the solution. Here, the cause is greater than the burden of duty. Loads of empathy are requisites to rightly attuning mind and body for
work. It calls for perspective as to how life can easily pun out difficult for anyone, for our dear friend or loved, for anyone, ourselves included.
I respect the courage and the character it takes to uphold this personal value; this art piece extends my recognition and lauds their commendable spirit of humanity.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Her
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This artwork changes twice a day, day and night. 

Associated with love, beauty, fertility, gold, war and death is a the mother. She is also the most beautiful of all.  She loves her children, music, spring, flowers and all the world. She is the daughter of the of the gods and gives us life. This inspired me to create this artwork.

“It was her chaos that made her beautiful. ”
― Atticus Poetry, Love Her Wild

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Koi
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
'Koi' is an artwork made to invoke the calming feeling of koi carp pond watching. The fish are positioned on three depth levels, with a pond reflection layer that can also be modified. 

The paths and formations of the koi fish have been carefully designed to appear organic, yet structured enough so that users in control of various depths of the pond can discover and create harmonious shapes, paths and compositions between them.

Similar to tending a zen stone garden, the intention is for users to find a sense of simple joy in the aesthetics and forms created through collaboration with fellow users and through the koi themselves.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Vampire words
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
When language immerses itself in the unknown. 
At dawn, the words wake up, put on make-up with nice colors, and come to life with striking costumes to play together and keep us entertained. 
At dusk, it is time to remove your makeup. Dreams, fantasies, and nightmares explore other meanings. Vampire hour. Language without limits, world without limits. 

Details here: 
https://www.theneimus.com/neimu-ludovico/vampire-words

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Kylo Ren + the Divine Feminine
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"Kylo Ren + the Divine Feminine" is a story in verse that unfolds hour by hour. It’s an intimate peak inside one woman’s sleepless, disheveled mind as she attempts to cope with overwhelming feelings of neglect, desire, and failure.

Each hour is in dialogue with time past and time future—both textually and visually—underlining the cyclical, convoluted nature of our thoughts. We often feel we are trapped inside a single day that repeats itself without end. But, by confining itself to the timeframe of day, my work reveals that is not time but our thoughts that entrap us. 

“Kylo Ren + the Divine Feminine” purposefully alternates between the mundane and the transcendental to reveal how the inescapable rhythm of dawn, noon, dusk, and night governs our physical and emotional hunger. 

Though any section could be the first, readers might consider starting at 6:00 am.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Jewel Face Day and Night
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: These collages were inspired by the proliferation of stories in the mass media of women’s sexual harassment in the workplace. A creative collage response to #MeToo and #TimesUp where our social media newsfeeds are proliferated with various Men in Suits denying the traumatic narratives of women. In these pieces, the Men in Suits are surrounded by a feminine visual language. Their identities are erased with globs of paint and jewels in bright fun colours that signify positive change and transformation in our society.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Contagion'''
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Exposure to pestilent infestants without sufficient personal protective equipment occasioned a vital challenge for medical workers in the early months of the Coronavirus. Several dedicated staff lost their lives in service after contracting and succumbing to the deadly microbes while in line of duty committed to saving as many as they possibly could.
The art piece revels in their selfless altruism and unfeigned compassion during a time of crisis in contemporary history.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: '''''Last Shot
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Last Shot presents us with an imagery of a moment when, as a medical professional, one is running out of options to treat their patients and is on the verge of losing them. Several thoughts race through the mind, but none is good enough; they scramble for whatever they can to try and hinder loss.
During this race against time, the patient slowly fizzles away as they yet watch their confounded source of hope darting up and down, across the room in a futile search for answers. The frustration of unavailing evaluation and unfortunate patient outcomes can precede one's second-guessing of their abilities, a moment of trial for the practitioner.
The complication extends to challenge more than just their skill but to question who they are as a person.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: ''Wand of Serenity
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The human soul whines at the threat of a pained unhealthful existence. For the elderly and the symptomatic, a slight pinch of pain can land one contemplating something worse, an imminent ghastly swoop into death's gluttonous catacombs. Growing up as a Ndebele kid, there was a popular Grandma joke which went like, "Dokotela, uGogo uyagula, mhlabe ngejekiseni elilamanzi kayi kukwazi umehluko", a joking statement which translates as, "Doc, Granny is sick, inject her with water, she won't know the difference." The joke funnily alluded to the fact that, Granny’s being diagnosed and administered to by the doctor gave her a strong belief that had her thinking and believing that she was already healing. It was magical; the volumes of trust and the extent of willful vulnerability were astounding for our young minds.
This much confidence invested in doctors exists in no other profession.The pressure to deliver well on this much faith invested requires expert containment and the humane skill of radiating positive energy to the patients during their healing process.
Perhaps this saying is true; a caring, present, and devoted doctor has the job done half-done.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: '''Loathed Sensations '''
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The piece commits to extol the big heart it takes to gracefully wield some of the medical field's duties. It calls for something extraordinary to shock medical personnel, moreover to gross them out. It is only a unique few experiences that climb over that tall wall of expert settledness into the scum slush of squeamishness.
While the ER's trauma-infusing encounters bolden resolve and foster courage in place of fear, procedures like manual disimpaction have served to harden these servicemen from being easily stirred into queasyreflexes when confronted with awful cases in the line of duty. Nonetheless, no amount of experience can desensitize one to every disturbing experience.
It is stout commitment that can guarantee one enough thick skin to maneuver at a level of their invaluable experiences.
Loathed Sensations are daily phenomena in the premises of these Life Savers; I dedicate this piece to applaud their care, humility, and patience.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Pahadi Farmer Portrait
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Most Garhwali cultivators are poor, some are very poor. And yet these are very cheerful people. Somehow they manage to wrest a precarious living from the unhelpful soil.

Mountains and these people have stood the test of time like no other. And I have been always grateful to them. I have put together some of my best creativity to work that the mountains have inspired me to think. For if you cannot come up here, I hope these artworks will at least give you a glimpse into lives of Garhwal. 
With this artwork I hope to create a charming little portrait of our life in the hills, where we live in a quiet, unhurried manner at our own pace. And I hope that it would inspire you to come visit us too someday.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Year of the 0x
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The Guild began this project as a tribute to the Lunar Ox Year that coincides with the Ethereum bull run and astronomical explosion of NFTs as a medium. It is a work of struggle, of celebration, of premonition and of jubilation. 

An initial composition of color was created by Shinji Akhirah which helped to inform the delegation of sections via a randomizer. Each artist was randomly assigned an area on the canvas to complete their part. This collaboration captures original artwork by 38 different artists - infusing each part of the piece with their own unique style to complete the 12 different animals and setting with the central focus being placed on the Ox ("0x" or "ZeroX" as he's occasionally referred to). 

We present you with the "Year of The 0x" - a celebration of creativity, Chinese astrology and the globally collaborative CryptoArt movement.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: '''Karmic Wait ...
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Any worthwhile lifework in the universe fulfills an existing need, serves a purpose, and generates personal satisfaction. The commitment satiates and rewards outside the promise of money. Our world has seen a growing belief in Karmic energy, a belief that the universe rewards with either a tangible blessing or a strong sense of fulfillment when you do good. The same phenomenon strongly identifies with the lives of some medical workers who heartily embrace the heaven-vested duty assigned to them by the universe.
Post any successful yet complex surgery, a sense of fulfillment floods the surgical team, and for once, life feels intimate, and its possibilities are sensed with greater intensity. This band darted into plains of positivity where consistent hope is cultivated and courage to expect the good is adopted.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: ""Still-Still"'
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Still-still — still composed, still unfazed, still warring for the incalculable high value of optimal health, this piece damn well features in many physician stories. Beamed in this composition is the trying task of keeping calm and collected amidst the loathed pressure-pressed high-stress hour.
Expressed is the art of mastered composure, drilled over years of professional training, and primed by several invaluable experiences of workday practice. Still-still is a state of being exhibited by seasoned clinicians in their firm steadiness during a difficult time. The internally sourced quietness is planted in their unreserved embrace and concrete understanding mission, cognizance that keeps the mind undistracted from duty.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Nothing New
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This creation changes every hour in a 24-hour cycle. It depicts the building and burying of a structure. The creature rebuilds the dome every day, and each day it is reclaimed by the sands. The work portrays the inherent meaninglessness of our toil, which eventually passes with time. It poses the question: knowing this, why do we continue to build what we build?

The creature was crafted from pipe cleaners, felt, yarn, clothes pins, and a large bead. It was photographed in the physical world in front of a green screen and inserted into a virtual environment. This environment, including the house, props, and lighting, were rendered in real-time out of a game engine. The process combines physical and digital worlds as a reflection of our own way of existing in both spaces.

“What has been will be again, what has been done will be done again. There is nothing new under the sun.”

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Eternity
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"Eternity is in love with the productions of time."

Night layer: "For man has closed himself up, till he sees all things thro' narrow chinks of his cavern"

Sunrise layer:
"He who binds to himself a joy
Does the wingèd life destroy;
But he who kisses the joy as it flies
Lives in eternity's sunrise."

Day layer: "If the doors of perception were cleansed every thing would appear to man as it is, infinite."

Sunset layer: 
"The moon like a flower
In heaven's high bower,
With silent delight,
Sits and smiles on the night."

All quotes from William Blake, who has taught me much about The Self, identity, and being in the world.  I turned to Blake to get inspiration for what it means to be in these new virtual worlds we are creating.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Covid Collage Project
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Our former eyes have been replaced, and the curtain pulled back on the inequities that we didn’t quite FULLY see before; rampant ableism, deep racism, vitriolic sexism and complex classism. 

News and news feeds are full of surreal death stories and devastating condolences, read and consumed through these new eyes of truth; all laid bare by Covid19. 

We look with different eyes that are metallic and shiny. Eyes that haven’t yet been formed; new eyes that no longer know how to ‘look to our future” for hope and possibilities. Eyes swimming in pools of uncertainties brought by Covid19.

Our Instagram lives and our materialistic obsessions are now unimportant and breaking apart at the seams. Nails unpainted, unkempt hair with new natural roots growing out of our scalps. spring fashion lines left the rack, are locked up in retail stores collecting dust. All were deemed unimportant by Covid19. 

We are left to self reflect, face ourselves, slow down, and toss and turn at night with vivid crackling dreams alive with messages screaming from our subconscious. A newly formed focus on symbols and images, not yet fully understood, brought to you by Covid19. 

Our connection to nature and the world around us is only now beginning to be understood. We thought we were separate, but now we know we are one. We were never masters of this universe because nature was never ours to master. Fractured plants, roaming animals, the unpolluted sky, the contaminated dirt, seeping in and out of our bodies. Sequestered in our homes, our minds begin to change, open up, and fracture with confusion; scattered with former motivations that are no longer valuable. We float in a sea of unknowns, covering our faces with psychological and real masks. Covid19 is a virus that makes reliability and safety unknown. In a sparkly shiny isolated dreamy space —  how will we prophesize our new future and manifest in an uncertain one?

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Weeping Rose
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: My heart, along with this rose, weeps for the people of Afghanistan, particularly the women and girls thrust into the medieval darkness of totalitarian dictatorship and gender apartheid.  As an adolescent I first read, in a novel of 19th century romance, the term, Hindu Kush.  The phrase washed over me like a strong perfume and my imagination was fired.  Afghanistan became a kind of Eden - a lush and exotic garden inhabited by beautiful and heroic people - for beyond my reach but enriching my world.  Would that I could today enrich the real world of my unknown, but beloved sisters there.  I weep, and pray that Afghanistan may see a new dawn.  Artist proceeds from the sale of this artwork will be donated to the Malala Fund: https://malala.org.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Questgiver
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Questgiver is a satirical app developed by paleh0rs3 to ask the question:

"What if mid-conversation we could pull up an Uber-style app to break free from the imposed limits on acceptable thoughts?"

In almost any social situation we're implicitly forced to choose from a set of response options as if we're non-playable characters, or quest givers, in a video game. And often this is for good reason: the human mind harbors darkness and despair that our fellow citizens are usually best left unaware of.

We often joke about living in a simulation to conjure apprehension, but on some axes, we're most comfortable when the options are limited and predictable.

Questgiver's UI was handcrafted for the 16:9 aspect ratio optimal for displaying Async pieces on televisions and digital frames. The concept for a "Questgiver Terminal" was inspired by the "expected waiting time" screens for public transport / ridesharing apps in high-end lobbies. It gives a publicly observable screen on which passersby can view nearby Questgivers engaging in uncomfortable conversations.

Each conversation features completely fake yet convincing human portraits generated via AI on ThisPersonDoesNotExist.com. In addition, the conversations utilize a stylized "dialog tree," which is actually a method employed to model NPC interactions in video games. Each dialog tree is spawned by a remark from the non-Questgiver. The first column of the tree contains two "socially acceptable" responses that have been greyed out in favor of the transgressive response. The app then generates a predicted counter-response to the Questgiver's unacceptably choice words, which prompts three more even worse options to become available.

Since it was designed to be shown on a public display in a well-trafficked area, the concept was a natural fit for the 24H Async template. At each hour of the day, a new Questgiver is highlighted to emulate the dynamic nature of conversations occurring 24/7.

So go find your nearest Questgiver Terminal today.

Maybe you'll even strike up a conversation over what you both witness...

MAP ATTRIBUTION
Questgiver utilizes a static snapshot of a map from Mapbox
To learn more, visit https://www.mapbox.com/about/maps/ and http://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:

The artwork “The Eye” intends to criticize the changes made by humans to the environment and how it does not recognize himself as the offender. The moment he looks in the mirror, he never sees exactly what he is.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: BITCOIN.
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The Ultimate Store of Value. 

The next time someone says "Bitcoin uses too much energy", proceed to ask them very simple questions. 

Question 1: How much energy does it use? Beatboxing will begin. 
Question 2: Too much energy in comparison to what? Further beatboxing. 
Question 3: Have you read the Bitcoin white paper? Inevitable facepalm. 

This piece showcases the evolution of my understanding of the nature of money. 

Andreas Antonopoulos was instrumental in that understanding. Ironically, Peter Schiff may have kickstarted this journey with his video, "I am the 1%. Let's Talk". 

With my recent discovery of Michael Saylor, the excitement has been revived. 

Here's to the future.

...

Part of a series of Marylebone, London based artworks. All of these works consist of photographs taken by me in January 2020. It is the time of Lunar New Year, Wuhan lockdowns, and the very first signs of the virus in Europe.

Marylebone was originally an Ancient Parish formed to serve the manors (landholdings) of Lileston (in the west - which gives its name to modern Lisson Grove) and Tyburn in the east. The parish is likely to have been in place since at least the twelfth century and will have used the boundaries of the pre-existing manors. The boundaries of the parish were consistent from the late twelfth century to the creation of the Metropolitan Borough which succeeded it. (Wikipedia)

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Mystical Harbor
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Watched by deities older than men, populated in ancient times by the Ptolemaic to the Roman, hosting the brilliant Trireme laden with oils to the fishing dingies of today; the port of Knidos, the mystical harbor that is welcomes human and non-human creatures all alike into its embrace cold and warm at the same time.

Photographs from the Summer of 2021 by Hulki Okan Tabak. Conceptualized, edited and minted during September 2021. With a loving heart and a bunch of well intentioned blood sweat and laughter, it is hereby presented in its 24 piece form on Async Art.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: ''Collective Instinct ""
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This piece echoes the utter essentialness of collective instinct and teamwork for doctors and their teams in the healthcare setting. The trust built and the cohesion cemented reduces the chances of medical errors and develops a greater appreciation of each other's work. This phenomenal approach enables these professionals to better meet patient needs as a collective, and through shared responsibility, their tasks are smoothed and procedures timely executed. Observations and decisions made together guarantee them enhanced efficiency and effectiveness.
Exemplified is a classic case of workplace teamwork, something they execute so well that demands a heightened sense of social and relationship awareness.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Seven Chakras
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: The Sanskrit word “Chakra” means “Disk” or “Wheels” and refers to the 7 points of energy in the human body. The 7 Chakras of spinning energy, each corresponds to certain nerves and major organs of the body. The Chakras are an ancient energy systems dating back to 1000 BC. With the passage of time and increased significance of alignment of mind and body the Chakras have gained a lot of importance in modern day fitness and health programs. It is believed there are around 114 Chakras in the human body, but the major influence is through the 7 chakras. The Chakras in our body defined our personality, health and lifestyle in general. By choosing your individual personality traits you can design a unique NFT that aligns with your persona & energy. The 7 Chakra NFT isn’t merely a digital art form but a unique representation of your personality.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: "'Broken''
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Life is a bubbling barrel of events incessantly shooting up and about, consummating each individual's respective life experience. "Broken" funnels luminance into the darker patches of physician life, unsealing a people suffering a far greater risk of enduring the ordeal of broken home life. Perpetual absence from home alienates them from the affairs at home and deprives them of valuable family time. This chips away precious moments they could have shared with their families and creates a massive imbalance that robs them of happiness.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: History’s Monsters
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
At the Acropolis Museum in Athens lie the fragments of dozens of carcasses, cast in stone and marble. Heads without bodies, hands without arms, horses without their riders. These ghostly splinters are a stark reminder of the legacy of colonial history; their missing parts scattered around the museums of the world, from London to The Louvre. 

‘History’s Monsters’ is an attempt to glue history back together, collecting broken fragments of ancient Greek sculptures, statues and grotesques from across the world and reconstructing them in a horrifying game of Exquisite Corpse. The Frankensteins that are created in turn recall the many gods and hybrids that populate ancient Greek mythology, from Medusa to the Minotaur, and from Cerberus to the Cyclops. These are history’s monsters. 

The piece consists of twelve monsters. Each monster changes colour and texture depending on whether it’s night or day in Athens, Greece (where the Acropolis Museum stands), to create twenty-four unique images, metamorphosing every hour - a macabre clock. The first visual creation of London-based band HMLTD, and following their Async Music genesis piece 'LEAVING', 'History's Monsters' will play an integral role in their upcoming second album campaign.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This is a 3d piece comprised of  surrealistic landscapes,  fractal geometric patterns, and strange attractor textures. It is an exploration of form, colour, and texture.


The process I used was  RTX  path tracing in Nvidia Omniverse, and unreal landscape engine to make the terrain. For the geometric patterns, and strange attractors I worked with Jwildfire. It was then colour graded in Davinci Resolve. Finally  I whittled down the best combinations which made a significant diverse difference to the master layer. All the layers are meant to be mixed and matched. Enjoy playing with it!

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Moon Aloof
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
As the hours pass the moon will slowly reveal itself becoming a bright light in the nights sky before eventually shrouding itself in darkness again!


A little about how I  created this:
Started with images taken from the Lunar Reconnaissance Orbiter (LRO) and modeled them in After Effects from there I added points of light that gradually come towards the camera. After I was happy with the look here I edited it further on my phone using an app called Glitch Studio to bring out some of the blues and reds. This was also where I layered in some noise, dithering, and got the overall aesthetic down. For this piece I imported the finished video which was almost 2 minutes long  back into AE and sped it up to be 24 secs long and exported a frame every 60 frames which ended out working out to a complete loop!

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Crypto Mundi
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This is Crypto Mundi from The Most Expensive Artworks Project collaboration by Athena Novo and Mad Monk.

It is a remix of Leonardo Da Vinci's Salvator Mundi. It is No 1 in the project in parallel with its place on the list. Accordingly it has been last sold November 2017 in Christie's New York for USD 450 million. The seller was Dmitry Rybolovlev and the buyer was Badr bin Abdullah Al Saud. 

...

The Most Expensive Artworks Project started with an idea and a web page on Wikipedia: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_most_expensive_paintings.

Athena Novo and Mad Monk collaborated on "doing something" with the list. First idea was to make a common "burn" GIF. Step by step the original or an alternative version would be burned i.e. like a GIF. However the idea of destructing artworks did not appeal. Then glitching was cast off as the main tool for something more appealing was under consideration. It was the idea of remixing the artwork more freely - sometimes with itself and sometimes with others on the list (as a pre-condition to narrow the universe).

Consequently AN and MM started to work on from the top of the list. Several results were obtained and from them, the story modes with multiple artworks will be minted on Async Art by Athena Novo while the single items (in GIF or JPG) will be minted on KnownOrigin by Mad Monk as a part of the collaboration.

...

Salvator Mundi (Latin for ''Savior of the World'') is a painting attributed in whole or in part to the Italian High Renaissance artist Leonardo da Vinci, dated to c. 1499–1510. Long thought to be a copy of a lost original veiled with overpainting, it was rediscovered, restored, and included in Luke Syson's major Leonardo exhibition at the National Gallery, London, in 2011–12. Christie's claimed just after selling the work that most leading scholars consider it to be an original work by Leonardo, but this attribution has been disputed by other specialists, some of whom posit that he only contributed certain elements.

The painting depicts Jesus in an anachronistic blue Renaissance dress, making the sign of the cross with his right hand, while holding a transparent, non-refracting crystal orb in his left, signaling his role as Salvator Mundi and representing the 'celestial sphere' of the heavens. Approximately thirty copies and variations of the work by students and followers of Leonardo have been identified. Preparatory chalk and ink drawings of the drapery by Leonardo are held in the British Royal Collection.

The painting was sold at auction for US$450.3 million on 15 November 2017 by Christie's in New York to Prince Badr bin Abdullah, setting a new record for most expensive painting ever sold at public auction. Prince Badr allegedly made the purchase on behalf of Abu Dhabi's Department of Culture and Tourism but it has since been posited that he may have been a stand-in bidder for his close ally and Saudi Arabian crown prince Mohammed bin Salman. This follows late-2017 reports that the painting would be put on display at the Louvre Abu Dhabi and the unexplained cancellation of its scheduled September 2018 unveiling. The current location of the painting has been reported as unknown but a June 2019 report stated that it was being stored on bin Salman's yacht, pending completion of a cultural center in Al-`Ula and an October 2019 report indicated it may be in storage in Switzerland. (Wikipedia) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salvator_Mundi_(Leonardo)

The Most Expensive Artworks Project started with an idea and a web page on Wikipedia: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_most_expensive_paintings.

Athena Novo and Mad Monk collaborated on "doing something" with the list. First idea was to make a common "burn" GIF. Step by step the original or an alternative version would be burned i.e. like a GIF. However the idea of destructing artworks did not appeal. Then glitching was cast off as the main tool for something more appealing was under consideration. It was the idea of remixing the artwork more freely - sometimes with itself and sometimes with others on the list (as a pre-condition to narrow the universe).

Consequently AN and MM started to work on from the top of the list. Several results were obtained and from them, the story modes with multiple artworks will be minted on Async Art by Athena Novo while the single items (in GIF or JPG) will be minted on KnownOrigin by Mad Monk as a part of the collaboration.

The Card Players is a series of oil paintings by the French Post-Impressionist artist Paul Cézanne. Painted during Cézanne's final period in the early 1890s, there are five paintings in the series. The versions vary in size, the number of players, and the setting in which the game takes place. Cézanne also completed numerous drawings and studies in preparation for The Card Players series.

The series is considered by critics to be a cornerstone of Cézanne's art during the early-to-mid 1890s period, as well as a "prelude" to his final years, when he painted some of his most acclaimed work.

Each painting depicts Provençal peasants immersed in their pipes and playing cards. The subjects, all male, are displayed as studious within their card playing, eyes cast downward, intent on the game at hand. Cézanne adapted a motif from 17th-century Dutch and French genre painting which often depicted card games with rowdy, drunken gamblers in taverns, replacing them instead with stone-faced tradesmen in a more simplified setting. Whereas previous paintings of the genre had illustrated heightened moments of drama, Cézanne's portraits have been noted for their lack of drama, narrative, and conventional characterization. Other than an unused wine bottle in the two-player versions, there is an absence of drink and money, which were prominent fixtures of the 17th-century genre. 

The models for the paintings were local farmhands, some of whom worked on the Cézanne family estate, the Jas de Bouffan. Each scene is depicted as one of quiet, still concentration; the men look down at their cards rather than at each other, with the cards being perhaps their sole means of communication outside of work. One critic described the scenes as "human still life", while another speculated that the men's intense focus on their game mirrors that of the painter's absorption in his art. (Wikipedia) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Card_Players

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Farfalle One
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
'Farfalle One', named after the Italian word for 'butterflies', is an interactive, co-operable inkblot. 

Its two layers can be combined and interpreted in a large number of ways that always produce unpredictable results for viewers to contemplate on what they see before them. 

When experiencing the piece, viewers are encouraged to consider one simple question :

"What do you see now?"

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Day for Night (001)
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This is a dream.  The Washago experiment. A nautical disaster.  
He said, "It's out there most days and nights.  Those fingernails scratching on the hull between a Green River and a Cognashene." 

Day for night. 

As cinematic as our conversation is as faint a sound in my memory.  
Then the dream ends when the phone rings. 

Day: 44.92459,-79.9268445
Night: 44.7598753,-79.3307357

Day for Night (001) is a 1/1 edition genesis NFT artwork by Nolan Dubeau consisting of four images exploring the creation of hybrid landscapes from disparate locations.

Sunrise is shown from 6am to 7am.
Day is shown from 6am to 7pm.
Sunset is shown from 6pm to 7pm. 
Night is shown from 7pm to 6am.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Farfalle Two
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
'Farfalle Two', named after the Italian word for 'butterflies', is an interactive, co-operated tri-chromatic inkblot.

It is comprised of three, individually selectable layers of prints in cyan, magenta and yellow, which overlap to form a vibrant composite image.

Each layer contains twelve inkblot designs. By selecting two identical designs, tertiary colors can also be created.

Its three layers can be combined and interpreted in a large number of ways that always produce unpredictable results for viewers to contemplate on what they see before them. 

When experiencing the piece, viewers are encouraged to consider one simple question :

"What do you see now?"

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Nu Day in Her Own Way
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This is Nu Day in Her Own Way from The Most Expensive Artworks Project collaboration by Athena Novo and Mad Monk.

It is a remix of Modigliani's Nu Couche with a dose of some more Modigliani . It is No 10 (skipping a lot in between at will) in the project in parallel with its place on the list. Accordingly it has been last sold November 2015 in Christie's New York for USD 170 million. The seller was Laura Mattioli Rossi and the buyer was Liu Yiqian. 

...

The Most Expensive Artworks Project started with an idea and a web page on Wikipedia: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_most_expensive_paintings.

Athena Novo and Mad Monk collaborated on "doing something" with the list. First idea was to make a common "burn" GIF. Step by step the original or an alternative version would be burned i.e. like a GIF. However the idea of destructing artworks did not appeal. Then glitching was cast off as the main tool for something more appealing was under consideration. It was the idea of remixing the artwork more freely - sometimes with itself and sometimes with others on the list (as a pre-condition to narrow the universe).

Consequently AN and MM started to work on from the top of the list. Several results were obtained and from them, the story modes with multiple artworks will be minted on Async Art by Athena Novo while the single items (in GIF or JPG) will be minted on KnownOrigin by Mad Monk as a part of the collaboration.

...

Nu couché (also known in English as Red Nude or Reclining Nude is a 1917 oil on canvas painting by the Italian artist Amedeo Modigliani. It is one of his most widely reproduced and exhibited paintings. (Wikipedia)

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: metaphysics of life
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: It's like we're all walking on an old swaying wooden bridge in the world. If we can't find anything to hold on to, we roll over. And we continue to fight with ourselves while looking for a subject, thing, person, ideology to which we can connect. Centuries have not changed its ordinary style in human psychology. One day we will realize that the only thing we can hold on to in the world is love. Until that happens, we will integrate with things. We will greet the insects. We will mix colors. And we will become alienated from those closest to us. We'll get lost in untidy dirty walls. After a while, the days become the same as the other days. Then hours are like days. Let's Think Now. Are our emotions a closet that we can open into the dark and show? Or how are we different from an insect trying to escape between things?

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Being truthful to one's self.
Going to pleasure island is in no way the solution. Escaping the roots of our problems only escalades the situation. Fear is the enemy itself. Fear of being prosecuted for our mistakes. Living in fear creates the misery one will suffer. Creating a problem is never a solution. Admitting mistakes is a process one has to go through and it comes with honesty.

This artwork is inspired by the pleasure island. Coming back from it. Accepting the monster it created and killing it for my own good.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Huexixua means ‘’head’’ in Chontaquiro, which is an Arawak language.
This 24-hour dynamic artwork is a tribute to indigenous people from South America, their tradition of creating ‘’colossal heads’’ sculptures and Native American Indian colourful totem poles. The word ‘’totem’’ meant ‘’to be related to someone’’ - totem poles represent both the written history and Native American family lineage.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Thing With Feathers
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Inspired by Emily Dickinson's poem "Hope is the Thing With Feathers" this plays around with the juxtaposition of coins and feathers. Parrots, considered an auspicious bird in the lucky colour yellow are associated with hope, as they turn they become a side growing tree made up of different currencies. It explores ideas of luck, money and what is means to hope.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Trixel CryptoAngels Genesis
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Collab between Domacollective (ig domacollective) and marcsparkss (ig msparkss_art) on the birth of the Trixel CryptoAngel movement.

The artists are going befond the pfp pixel craze and exploring new forms of digitally inspired respresentations.  We got tired of pixels and went for triangles, hence "the Trixel"
Day : based on 180x130 acrylic painting 
Night: Mixed media 

The angels in Raphael's Sisitine Madonna have long time represented youth, innocence, a promise for a better world.  They are superstars, known to so many around the world, but  we feel their global fame outgrew the physical aspect of how they were initially conceived. So, we took them out of their original version and suggested a new representation of diversity, fluidity, creativity, as in new form of hope. 

Proceeds of the sale towards research & building a smart-contract platform bringing further transparency of ngos accepting eth donations.

I made the first portrait (day) in 2013. It is a digital imitation of ink on paper, also called light drawing.
The second portrait (night) was made using the light painting technique in 2019.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Yorick's Box
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Merging self-portraiture with Shakespeare this is Yorick's Box. The work explores the ideas of the multi-faceted self via self-portraiture, depicting the spiritual self as a 100 handed triplet. The skulls each have their own unique temperament and story, as Yorick's in Shakespeare's 'Hamlet'. Just as Hamlet contemplated his own fate as melancholic Prince of Denmark, pondering the life of former court jester Yorick, so each head encourages introspection. As the day moves from morning to night the image rotates to reveal new aspects and intricate detailing.
 "Alas, poor Yorick! I knew him, Horatio, a fellow of infinite jest, of most excellent fancy." William Shakespeare, Hamlet, V:I.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: LIMBO
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Here we find, amidst lamentations of pain and anger, the "people who lived without glory and infamy", mixed with the angels who did not rebel against God, but not out of loyalty, but to avoid the consequences of taking sides in the struggle between good and evil. Heaven rejects them because they did nothing good and hell also, because they did nothing evil. Their torment is that no one remembers them, they have no hope of dying and have nothing to do in their poor life, spurned by both justice and compassion.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Influence of Surroundings
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Beauty is subjective, based partially by the surrounding elements of the observed object. In this artwork, the background is composed of two different layers, each with three different possible choices (layer A: white, burgundy or yellow layer B: white, blue or green) interacting together (the color of Layer B multiplies with the color of layer A) resulting in 9 potential background colors. Watch how the main element is perceived differently each time, depending on the underlying background. Even though, in reality the paint stays exactly the same no matter the background, it looks different based on its surroundings. Which relates to what we see in the "real" world, the truth being greatly influenced by its surrounding.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Do Not Step Into Your Place
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Do Not Step Into Your Place
by Hulki Okan Tabak
minted 2021 on Async Art

24 artworks based on World War I propaganda posters including a poster for the Third United States Official War Picture called Under Four Flags.  

One hidden surprise image embedded alongside for thinking outside the box.

...

The Great War, history, politics, art, posters and propaganda are topics of interest for me. It was kind of natural that I wanted to incorporate that in my cryptoart creations. The desire led to a selection of public domain pieces out of copyright from the Library of Congress archives. I created all sorts of derivative pacifist and tongue-in-cheek works. So far I have only minted a handful on KnownOrigin. Starting September 2021, I will mint a more comprehensive set on Async Art and KO depending on the nature of the final artwork. The artwork presented here is part of that World War I Posters set.

Culture in a vice versa city has been changing the mood of people not in it. Like a culture you're not a part of and you feel it, quote everyday.
Some people would love to wake up with their perception of Paris soo vibrant and yet so it's their dream to live there. Some people just day dream about vacay in there, their perception is what they chose to see, maybe just visit have great croissant with coffee buy some balenciaga and go home. The true dreamers are the sunset ones , they care about the city deeply, thinking they and the city can co-live together creating harmony for creativity and love. The night in Paris is for homies of Paris from start to the finish, the true leaders of their city, who just stick with it till the end. It takes all their energy but they have some life changing steps to only what they know where.

Parisiano consist thus of 4 pieces based on the day time. 
Morning
Day
Sunset
Night

Each belong to part of the story.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: 24h CATastrophe Averted
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
BRIEF: Abstract techno magical surrealist self-portrait with artist’s still-quite-feral kitty for Kitty Bungalow & Async Art.

BACKGROUND: In a world governed by straight lines and rigid thought, a gentle curve can be disruptive. A soft bit of fur & flesh can make an awful mess out of a clean but heartless machine. 

INQUIRY: Proverbial wayward women (& kitties), hexes, vexes, and societal complexes: visually explore the symbolism, stigma, myth, and magic of feline &  feminine forms as repressed elements within a rigid societal infrastructure through abstract techno magical surrealism. Further probe the unconscious with 24 unique variations of color & detail; ranging from subtle to drastic differences. (programmed to change every hour throughout a 24 hour period). 

The juxtaposition of organic & digital shapes creates contrast and highlights the intrinsically awesome power of conscious endogenous life forms in the Universe — opening up room for broader meditation on the extant tension & interplay between the permanence of chaos & the impermanence of order — and how grounding our bodies IRL through physical connection & affection can anchor us, support us, and offer love when we are at our most vulnerable; fostering curiosity, play, resilience, and space for hearts to open, shift, and heal. 

When viewed through different lenses, filters, or contexts, things, people, places, images, symbols, and ideas, can take on new meaning, depth, and texture. 24h CATastrophe AveRTed is a call to reflect, observe, witness, to be present with the unknown, with growth, change, and evolution under the sun. May this piece serve as reminder to pause & look deeper, to be slow to judgment; and above all, to be kind; to one another and, of course, to be kind to kitties — especially the wayward ones. <3

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Everything I Own
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Outside my art gallery is a doorbell cam. It captures not only people who ring the bell but also everyone that walks by. I occasionally review the days recording and am amazed by the passers by. This is the first in a series that will explore the contrasts and similarities that I discover as I try to imagine the stories of the blurry people who I glimpse.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Uttarakhand
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Located on the shivalik range of Himalayas. Uttarakhand is a state in northern part of India. It is often referred to as the "Devbhumi" (literally "Land of the Gods").
Uttarakhand's name is derived from the Sanskrit words uttara (उत्तर) meaning 'north', and khaṇḍa (खण्ड) meaning 'land', altogether simply meaning 'Northern Land'.

The native people of Uttarakhand are generally called Uttarakhandi and sometimes specifically either Garhwali or Kumaoni depending on their place of origin in either the Garhwal or Kumaon region. Regional languages of Uttarakhand are Garhwali, which is spoken by 23% of the population mostly in the western half of the state, Kumaoni, spoken in the eastern half and native to 20%, both closely related languages of the Central Pahari languages, and the Jaunsari of the Western Pahari family, whose speakers are concentrated in Dehradun district in the southwest and make up 1.3% of the state's population. 

There are many ancient temples, forest reserves, national parks, hill stations, and mountain peaks that draw large number of tourists. There are 44 nationally protected monuments in the state.
Also many regional festivals are celebrated here, Harela is one of them. Harela has a great significance in Kumaon. This symbolizes a new harvest and the rainy season. It has become common practice to attribute a slogan of – "Save The Environment" to Harela. Schools in Uttarakhand often encourage their students to plant saplings, either at home, in the school or with the support of local officials. In Kumaun, the two celebrations during Navratri – first during Chaitra Navratri in the month of Chaitra, and second during Sharad Navratri in the month of Ashwin, is also considered to be connected to Harela.

The scarcity of water is still a major problem in Uttarakhand. Agricultural land remains barren because of a lack of irrigation facilities in the state, while water is not even available for everyday household chores. In villages, women have to walk for miles every day to fetch water.
The need for responsible tourism and construction in the mountains has long been overlooked. Besides unemployment and migration, lack of power and other infrastructures like road constitute major electoral issues in the state. 

Out-migration in Uttarakhand can primarily be attributed to a combination of push and pull factors like the lack of employment, low income, subsistence agriculture, better opportunities for employment and children's education, etc.
I sometimes feel these hills of Uttarakhand wants to speak something to me.
They want me to tell their story . They want me to describe the condition of Uttarakhand and hope I can bring a change in its developing community.

To the cruel world who only thinks about themselves, I wanted to be something else.
To change lifestyle of people of my Uttarakhand by improving economy through Crypto.
Because when you realize art is not just in canvas but if your art can change/improve someone lifestyle that is the real art and I am continuously striking myself to achieve that level of perfection.

Artists - 1. Shivansh Rawat
2. Shubham Bisht (https://www.behance.net/bhishtibis975b)
3. Avi Bisht (https://makersplace.com/psybot/)
4. Dipika Negi (https://www.instagram.com/unrealshot_/?hl=en)

minted 2021 on Async Art

So far I have only minted a handful on KnownOrigin. Starting September 2021, I will mint a more comprehensive set on Async Art and KO depending on the nature of the final artwork. The artwork presented here is part of that World War I Posters set.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Duchess Theatre Variety Show of Kittywood
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
When Duchess retired from Kittywood, she bought an old prop house from a friend. Even though she made the decision not to take another acting job, she wanted to remain in the Business in some way. It had been her life since she was a kitten! 

One morning at sunrise, Duchess was loading some furniture into her van at the back of the building, when she noticed 5 sleepy kittens huddled in the cold. She knew that homelessness was a problem in Kittywood (having experienced it firsthand herself) and decided to build a shelter at the prop house. 

Kitty Tent City facilitates the adoptions and ensures that the kittens are neutered or spayed and receive their vaccines. Over the years, many of Duchess' clients have adopted her kittens. Many of the kittens have stayed on to work in the prop house, help her run the shelter or have gone into the Business themselves.

Once a year, Duchess hosts and emcees the Duchess Theatre Variety Show featuring all the kittens-in-residence. It is a fundraiser for all the homeless kittens in Kittywood. You can usually find agents and managers in the audience, scouting for an up-and-coming starlet. Sometimes Duchess even performs!

The 24 hour images are a rotation of The Duchess Theatre Variety Show in two 12 hour cycles. It is always night in Kittywood, so no matter what time it is where you are, you are part of the party. 

1   Sunset Boulevard
2   House Party
3   By the Light of the Silvery Moon
4   Into the Night
5   Midnight Express
6   The Dark Side of the Moon
7   LA Confidential
8   Through the Glass Darkly
9   Eyes Wide Shut
10 Sunrise: A Song of Two Humans
11 The World's a Little Blurry
12 I gotta go to bed, it's too bright out

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Loop
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: In this piece, I tried to raise awareness to the global warming by showing the three major indicators of it by using these circular charts which represent the CO2 emissions (top), sea level rise (middle) and temperature (bottom) changes through years. Each slice can be thought as timeframes and the occupancy of the slices represent the units of them. Each day/night these charts start from the past when everything is sweetness and light and end with the current level of the global warming, which create a loop of awareness reminding us each day that we can't change the past and motivates us to take action for a better future.
