0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Day Cat, Night Cat
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"Day Cat, Night Cat" is my contribution for the Kitty Bungalow Charity event. With this piece I wanted to tell about the complex different personalities that cats can have.

The Day Cat is my parents cat called Peukku. It means thumb in Finnish and she got that name because she has one extra toe on all paws. She's lives in the countryside and has been outdoors cat for all of his life. Shes very cautious as outdoors cats need to be and runs away from most people, but shes known me from a small kitty and I can still nowadays approach her and give her some pats but she usually wants to keep a distance and is definitely not a cat to hold! Sometimes when its quiet and safe, she might go on my parents lap when they watch tv. In summertime she loves to just sleep somewhere in the meadows or in the barn. Her nails are sharp as needles and shes pretty good at catching prey.. although she has gained quite a lot of weight recently.

The night cat is my cat called Kelmi (hard to translate, something like criminal/mischievous in Finnish). He is few years old Bengal cat. Bengals are domesticated from the wild Asian leopard cats and behave like one! Like all Bengals, he is very energetic and playful and needs quite a lot of entertainment to keep him satisfied. His favorite game is to play fetch and has already learned to come literally poke me with his paws to start playing with him when my girlfriend takes our dog out for a walk (that's the time to play or otherwise the doggo steals the toy). He has also no problem keeping up wresting with our dog that's 4 times of his weight. Other fun traits: he loves going outdoors (with harness) to climb trees and he knows his feeding times well enough that before it he will come on my desk to poke me with his head, purrs and acts very lovable until he gets his food. Sometimes though during nighttime his Bengal dna can start to show up and he can get bit aggressive and attack us hoomans. That's the time when you just have to keep the cool and move him to another room to cool down. Overall Bengals are really intelligent and fun cats that can be very lovable but sometimes also bit pain in the ass so a good amount of patience is required with them! Good news, next month we are getting another Bengal kitty!

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Shanghai/上海

Do you really think that you can recognize a woman by her looks? How deceptive are appearances? She can be a housewife in the morning, a friend at lunch, and turn into a lioness in the evening. A woman is an amazing creature of nature. 
 
你真的认为你能从一个女孩的外表认出她吗？她的外表是多么具有欺骗性？她早上可能是一个家庭主妇，中午是一个朋友，晚上是一头母狮。女人是自然界的一种神奇生物。

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Magic Man on the Loose
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Magic Man lived a long time ago in a place far far away.

Magic Man wore a hat that housed his powers. Never took it off for fear of losing it.

When he got too old to perform magic, Magic Man left his home in search of an apprentice.

During his travels, Magic Man encountered a world unknown to him. He loved and loathed what he saw. He desired and cried incessantly. His emotions were mixed, his magic wat patchy, his hat was ragged.

I've met him during his travels. It was by the inn on the High Steppes that he was so tired that he fell asleep on foot when he stumbled in. I helped the keep carry him to a room that was to be his last. 

The stories I heard from him changed my life. The brief encounter was so brief and deep at the same time that I lack words to describe it. His last words I shall take to my grave. His wishes are my wishes now. His travels were not in vain.

...

Magic Man on the Loose
by Hulki Okan Tabak

Photography by Hulki Okan Tabak, January - February 2020
Digital Painting variations and Photoshop editing by Hulki Okan Tabak, January - September 2021
Concept and the story by Hulki Okan Tabak, September 2021

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Visions of the Past
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
She knew she couldn't ever truly experience the beauty of Mao Mao City, the stories were very clear that the city had fallen during the last great war, when the Kung Paw were finally defeated, albeit at great cost.  She couldn't stop thinking what that old tabby had said though... he seemed so certain of his beliefs. Could it be that she was truly the grandaughter of the exile? The legends never mentioned anything more of Captain Aditi after his exile, and the rumor that he had been found by the most loyal soldiers of the Kung Paw; deep in the belly of Shao Mountain, dabbling with dark powers not meant for kitty kind. But then, there were conflicting theories about how kitties learned to change their form by light of day to one resembling that of the hoomans of ancient times. Not even the great royal mages could say with any certainty why kitties gained this ability, nor did they know for sure why it was only possible in daylight; most kitties simply accepted the common belief that it was a gift offered them by the Kitty God, whose gaze strays to the west when night falls. The uncertianty was too much to bear. She had overheard the royal mages speaking of a spell they'd discovered that may let them witness events of the past, If she WAS a descendant of Aditi, and assuming the rumors of his involvement with dark magics were true, then maybe, just maybe, she could harness the ancient captains power, now possibly flowing through her veins, and could succeed where the royal mages had failed. 

Protect her Kitty God, she is young and has too important a destiny...

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Dark Tourism - Chernobyl (24 Photo Editions in 1 NFT)
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Dark tourism is a concept where you visit the worlds most darkest places ever historically associated with death, tragedy and suffering.
In 2017, I've visited Chernobyl. Took the tour to visit Kiev, Pripyat, and Chernobyl Nuclear Reactor Site.

The ghost city of Pripyat was amazing. When the government back then declared an evacuation, people didn't have any time to take their belongings with them.
All they packed was their clothes in small bags.

Pripyat was one of the richest cities in the whole world back then as the wages of the workers of Nuclear site was enough for them to become wealthy.
But money didn't solve anything when, in 26th of April, 1986, the reactor exploded.

The abandoned Pripyat elementary school was also evacuated when the children were actually in classes.
And the tour guide says that none of the items in there were ever touched or re-placed.

This 24 photos are all taken by @koklucinar and generated by eNFThusiast.
It's a portrait design. Hope you enjoy it with your Meurals or Apple TV's.

All original 24 photos, without the background frame details, will be provided upon request by the owner of this NFT.

Important Note: This is a programmable NFT. It contains 24 photos and it updates automatically every hour.
Come back in about an hour later to see the next photo or view all photos with the Async Art's explorer.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Cosmic Entanglement
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
53 6f 6d 65 20 77 61 73 74 65 20 74 68 65 69 72 20 65 6e 74 69 72 65 20 6c 69 76 65 73 20 77 6f 72 72 79 69 6e 67 20 61 62 6f 75 74 20 74 68 65 20 65 6e 74 61 6e 67 6c 65 6d 65 6e 74 2e 20 53 6f 6d 65 20 65 6d 62 72 61 63 65 20 69 74 20 6c 69 6b 65 20 61 6e 20 6f 6c 64 20 66 72 69 65 6e 64 2e 20 54 68 65 72 65 20 69 73 20 6e 6f 20 65 73 63 61 70 69 6e 67 20 74 68 65 20 65 66 66 65 63 74 20 6f 66 20 74 68 65 6d 2e 20 54 68 65 72 65 20 69 73 20 6e 6f 20 54 69 6d 65 2e

When the lines of time intersect there is an entanglement of a different kind where the past present and future co-exist at the same time.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: MozartBeats
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart’s masterpiece *Eine kleine Nachtmusik* ("a little night music") was completed in Vienna on 10 August 1787 while he worked on the opera Don Giovanni, but the work was not published until about 1827, long after his death. The occasion and the patron for Mozart’s composition remains unknown today and it was probably never performed within the span of his lifetime.

Almost 200 years later and in the same city of Vienna, the world’s musical capital, Mozart’s masterpiece has been remoulded to reflect society’s evolution into today’s postmodern artistic landscape, with the incorporation of bold and futuristic cutting-edge technologies.

The structure of the Mastertrack consists of four stems: Violin 1, Violin 2, Viola and Cello, with a total of five variations per stem. Layering different stem variations over one another leads to the creation of personally crafted, magical and unique tapestries of sound, closely related to Mozart’s original.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: My Lifetime

Your ways determine some emotions, others by your environment. 
The fact we reach for answers gives the feeling of being lost, only to end up filling up our own lives to be as they are supposed to be.

Surf was the backdoor to the emptiness I had found in my youth. Having problems for finding myself in the middle of the chaos everyone called life. A labyrinth of emotions and challenges that made me what I am today. I wouldn't get rid of anything. It's part of my life. It's part of me. I wouldn't be the person I am today if I hadn't had those experiences, and I'm grateful for that.

aka Christmas Collection
by Hulki Okan Tabak
minted 2021 on Async Art

4 artworks based on World War I propaganda posters from Germany. In this case Bavarian Red Cross' efforts to raise some money for army.

...

The Great War, history, politics, art, posters and propaganda are topics of interest for me. It was kind of natural that I wanted to incorporate that in my cryptoart creations. The desire led to a selection of public domain pieces out of copyright from the Library of Congress archives. I created all sorts of derivative pacifist and tongue-in-cheek works. So far I have only minted a handful on KnownOrigin. Starting September 2021, I will mint a more comprehensive set on Async Art and KO depending on the nature of the final artwork. The artwork presented here is part of that World War I Posters set.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Colour, as a Measure of Time.
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Working with a grid and a Hex colour wheel, I wanted to use colour as a measurement of time. In this piece, each hour is represented by the clockwise movement around the colour wheel, fading from one colour to the next as the day progresses and we transition through the hours, from morning to afternoon to night. The colour’s of each hour are offset next their complementary colours, suggesting the notion that time zones have their own complementary times. The piece progresses inwards, around the clock, measured in hours, to the moment this day ends and a new one begins and it's time to say GM again.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: DraCColumbus
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
BRIEF: A meme about monsters, culture as propaganda, 500+ years of appropriation of the wealth of nations through genocide, slavery, and colonialism. 

BACKGROUND: 

On a small island, called Guanahani by the Indigenous Taíno People (in present day Bahamas), Christopher Columbus accidentally made landfall on the 12th of October 1492.

Conceived & realized as a single animation during October 2020, DraCColumbus is inspired by the gothic horror novel “Dracula” by Bram Stoker and the disturbingly persistent hero worship of Christopher Columbus in the form of U.S. monuments, urban & institutional nomenclature. Using four different lights I explore the archetypal vampire as it relates to cultural propaganda of European colonialism broadly and the fetishization of its legacy of entrenched power structures; including but not limited to the control of water, land, natural resources, human beings, language, monopoly on violence, infrastructure, and currency. 

INQUIRY:

In 1492 Columbus sailed the ocean blue,
The Niña, the Pinta, and the Santa Maria too.
Carried by the wind across the open sea,
Bringing death, destruction, and disease.
500+ years of genocide — it’s true.
I see a vampire’s legacy.
What about you?

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: From The Plain People
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
From The Plain People
by Hulki Okan Tabak
minted 2021 on Async Art

4 artworks based on World War I propaganda posters from the US depicting the war time aid to Belgium. The core propaganda was to show the aid as humanitarian and from the plain people of the US to the ordinary Belgians. 

...

The Great War, history, politics, art, posters and propaganda are topics of interest for me. It was kind of natural that I wanted to incorporate that in my cryptoart creations. The desire led to a selection of public domain pieces out of copyright from the Library of Congress archives. I created all sorts of derivative pacifist and tongue-in-cheek works. So far I have only minted a handful on KnownOrigin. Starting September 2021, I will mint a more comprehensive set on Async Art and KO depending on the nature of the final artwork. The artwork presented here is part of that World War I Posters set.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Relief with Purpose
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Relief with Purpose
by Hulki Okan Tabak
minted 2021 on Async Art

2 artworks based on World War I propaganda posters from the US. Relief is the sister piece to From The Plain People on Async Art. It is a piece derived from the same working material I've used in the KnownOrigin mints titled Belgian Relief Uncle Sam Arrives and Belgian Relief On the Ground. Relief with Purpose takes the same material and further glitches and complicates the situation on one larger canvas. It is the darker starker and also more experimental offshoot of this sub-heading in the greater World War I posters series.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: 24h Spiral Dance
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
BRIEF: This minimalist digitally hand-drawn stipple exploration of spiral formation grows an hour at a time; reaching its fullest coiled shape at midnight. 

BACKGROUND:

Since the human story began, upon every continent & island inhabited by human beings there were people carving spirals into wood, metal, stone, and bone. From galaxies to our DNA, spirals are repeated endlessly throughout our Universe at macro & micro scales. These deceptively simple motions reveal the principle of parsimony — energy conservation — at play in the Cosmos. Derived from Latin parsimonia meaning "sparingness, frugality, thrift," from pars-, the past-participle stem of parcere "to spare, save, refrain from, use moderately" and -monia, suffix signifying action, state, or condition. (Etymonline) 

INQUIRY:

Art did not begin as an institutional construct; and it will not end with the (at times, seemingly inevitable) decline of modern technological human civilizations on Earth through waste & war. Can we learn something from the silent movements of our world? Does our technological cosmology accurately place us within an infinite garden? Can we put aside finite games of centralization & domination to humbly rebalance? Will we mirror our infinite nature and collectively embody simplicity before our time runs out? No matter our fate, the vast & dazzling patterns in which we reside and find our being will remain long after the last pixel blinks out of existence.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: 24 Hours of Skulls
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
---This NFT represents the sale of 24 physical ink paintings of animal skulls and skeletons created by Skeenee. These paintings were first featured on Makersplace (https://makersplace.com/skeenee/). Skeenee will personally deliver this physical collection to the winner of this auction on first sale---

Spend a day in the company of Skeenee’s Skull and Skeleton creations in your own space in the metaverse. Venture inside CryptoVoxels to your very own parcel where “24 hours of Skulls” awaits.  With each hour spent there, an exciting new artwork is displayed, revealing 24 unique creations. Understand the creation process behind each piece as it is brought to life through video.
Finally come back to reality as you take ownership of each of the 24 physical artworks, delivered in person by Skeenee. (Buyers in the International Space Station may need to wait to take delivery).

Buy this and you’ll receive:
* The NFT, "24 hours of Skulls"
* 24 ink paintings created by Skeenee with fountain pen and ink on Arches paper
* A central CryptoVoxels Parcel featuring the NFT, the paintings and process videos. (https://www.cryptovoxels.com/parcels/281)
* A mural of the artwork

Each artwork comes from the Skull & Skeleton ink painting series which was started by Skeenee in 2018 to study anatomy & contrast and was inspired by renaissance drawings; a demonstration of a time where art and science were seen as one. The paintings are drawn with fountain pens on Arches paper, painted & shaded with Sumi ink and watercolors.

Remember, the clock is ticking…

Powers That Be
by Hulki Okan Tabak
minted 2021 on Async Art

4 artworks based on World War I propaganda posters from Germany. Powers That Be is based on the same source material as its companion piece Der Letzte Hier on Async Art and Helft! Powers Beyond Us minted nearly a year ago on KnownOrigin. Powers That Be combines elements used in all three in a different manner for a Day/Night cycle programmable artwork experience with Async Art.

...

The Great War, history, politics, art, posters and propaganda are topics of interest for me. It was kind of natural that I wanted to incorporate that in my cryptoart creations. The desire led to a selection of public domain pieces out of copyright from the Library of Congress archives. I created all sorts of derivative pacifist and tongue-in-cheek works. So far I have only minted a handful on KnownOrigin. Starting September 2021, I will mint a more comprehensive set on Async Art and KO depending on the nature of the final artwork. The artwork presented here is part of that World War I Posters set.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Exquisite Being
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Exquisite Being is an artwork inspired by the drawing exercise “exquisite corpse.” In this piece, the body parts of the figure, and its background, can be changed to build new combinations. The three options for each body part and background represent distinct ideological forces that influence the development of society: they were inspired by the archetypes of The Industrialist, The Artist, and The Scientist.  Each archetype views the world and the development of their species through a different lens and set of values. 

These archetypes were referenced in an essay written by a nineteenth-century French economic, political, and socialist thinker, Henri de Saint-Simon, in 1825. Henri de Saint-Simon coined one of the first uses of the French phrase “Avant Garde” to describe the role of artists in driving social change through their work. “We artists will serve you as an avant-garde, the power of the arts is most immediate: when we want to spread new ideas we inscribe them on marble or canvas.” In addition to artists, Henri de Saint-Simon saw scientists and industrialists (i.e., the businessman, the capitalist) as the three forerunners and shapers of society. 

This artwork is a collaborative piece between the artist and the different owners. Together, the owners of each part of the creature contribute to one character that represents a whole group of beings in the early stages of development on a new planet. As they evolve, they will need to make many choices of what to build their new society around. Therefore, the owners will not only determine the creature’s look but their evolutionary trajectory, the future of their society, and by extension, the health of their planet. The effects of these choices will be explored in future artworks.

“Exquisite Being” is a mixed media piece that combines physical hand-crafted characters with digital environments. Pipe cleaners, felt, yarn, clothes pins, and wooden beads were used to build each creature and their body parts. They were photographed in the physical world in front of a green screen and inserted into virtual environments. These environments, including the structures, props, and lighting, were rendered in real-time out of a game engine.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Lex Be Don
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
I have often wondered how parts make up a whole. I have written about it. I have actually written a mini poem about it and published it on Medium. I've minted another such into a different sort of NFT here on Async Art. This piece is another divide and don't conquer one. Loosely based on my grafitti photographs from Abbey Road Studios' walls, I focus taking bits out of the original photo and re-creating the linked pieces for this work. I sincerely wonder that if I live and it's years later that the art market boom of NFT would have happened to the extent that experimental works on Async Art have also been sweeped. I really would hope to see the day and  f*** talk about it for fun over coffee.

I call it a photograph.

I call it text.

I call it glitch.

I call it pseduo painting.

I even call it photo painting.

I may call it pseduo photo painting of selective text.

Lex Be Don by Hulki Okan Tabak
Minted on Async Art as 2021 ages further

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Asteroid
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Asteroid

AsyncArt Genesis
Consists of two 1 of 1 unique panoramic views of a digitally hand carved metamorphic architectural space, that represent day and night cycles.

Gentle lines hide among intense meshes, flowing freely they create a fabric of space or maybe a landscape of a distant asteroid from an outer space? In this art work we invite your imagination to travel outside of human perception or maybe even outside of this world. We invite you on a journey that explores the idea of architectural space. Follow the day and night cycles to become a space explorer and make new discoveries. 

Coming from years of architectural research in depth, each digital painting is a carefully crafted abstract architectural landscape, that explores spatial qualities of landscape, surface and texture.
Each art work comes from a process that involves hand sculpting in different mediums, starting from physical sculpting and into a 3D digital hand sculpting.
The art work comes from the project Interface, that took more than 7500 hours to develop the project and methodology plus more than 250 hrs to finish one digitally hand sculpted landscape.

2021
MABLAB

Spend a day in the company of Skeenee’s Skull and Skeleton creations in your own space in the metaverse. Venture inside CryptoVoxels to your very own parcel where “24 hours of Skulls” awaits. Buy this and you’ll receive:

-The NFT, "24 hours of Skulls"

Each artwork comes from the Skull & Skeleton ink painting series which was started by Skeenee in 2018 to study anatomy & contrast and was inspired by renaissance drawings; a demonstration of a time where art and science were seen as one. The paintings are drawn with fountain pens on Arches paper, painted & shaded with Sumi ink and watercolors.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Blockchain Rakuchu Rakugai-zu
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This piece was created in the likeness of the streets of Kyoto on a folding screen that’s the abstraction of the blockchain, created in the early days of blockchain technology.

Blockchain’s true nature is a new system that is decentralized. It’s created from a combination including irreversible hash functions, miners, nodes, and chains for a trustworthy system.

The creator believed that the power of the system “is like a bunch of new, invisible hands of gods that were born from the common consciousness based on the trust between humans.”  The gods that keep the blockchain system intact isn’t a single god, but the many blockchain tokens, making it similar to the millions of spirits in Shinto. The basis of blockchain was created by people, but ideally, blockchain itself cannot be directly controlled by humans. (Though it might be possible if the system is imperfect.) The girl who is depicted on a large scale in this art is not a god, but rather a being like a future shrine maiden that can be used by god.

Humanity can’t access the system directly, but they can connect to the system through the shrine maiden. Because of the maiden, the system is governed throughout the city, but there are also places outside that are not under the system. In order to make it obvious that this space is stateless, the buildings in the art are from all around the world. The shrine maiden’s appearance suggests that she is Japanese, just like the founder of blockchain, but her hair is pink, a color not found in nature, as well to imply statelessness. The general idea (god) of the ideal blockchain is firm, but its history is still quite short, so the shrine maiden is still a young, immature teenager doing this as a part-time job. She may make mistakes when the processes can’t be dealt with on the chain. Miners use cranes to maintain the basic structure of the system. They’re not working because of the orders to do that; instead they are private general contractors doing it for profit. The various cryptocurrencies and tokens are concealed in the system’s space like clouds, but that’s just all they are, and they represent the essence of the system itself. Exchanges in shops are transactions. At the time, on the web, the systems were different for the regular web and the blockchain web even though it was the same web. The blockchain web had practical use for cryptocurrency through the reliable demand, but after that the system was put in use in a wide variety of fields like entertainment and art, so the soul of the system was created within the virtual space of the web just like the Milky Way runs through the galaxy.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Generic Landscape, Lofoten, A Snow Storm Passing
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The artist Trygve Skogrand has lived for several years in the arctic Lofoten islands in the North of Norway, documenting the changing of the seasons, the drifting weather over the dramatic polar landscape. In this work, he has trained an ai-algorithm on a large series of photographs of the wintery mountains surrounding his house. The algorithm learns from statistics on colours, angles, shapes and textures in the photographs to generate new, virtual views of something not quite unlike the Lofoten mountains. 

The artist calls these generated, synthetic landscapes for "Generic Landscapes". In the work "Generic Landscape, Lofoten, A Snow Storm Passing", a snowstorm drifts over the mountains, obscuring and revealing them as it passes. The work changes each hour of the day, to reveal a different aspect of the winterly storm.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Satoshi Legacy
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Satoshi's legacy inspired by Sandro Botticelli's painting "Portrait of a Stranger", in these four facets of Satoshi, I show you the legacy of cryptocurrencies that in my perception are the footprint that Satoshi Nakamoto left us 13 years ago: A sunrise , a day, a sunset and a night that reflects that he came to change the digital world and the global economy.

1-Sunrise: Bitcoin
The Sunrise belongs to Bitcoin and this is the birth of a revolution of the exchange of monetary value in a decentralized way, thanks to the fact that Satoshi shows us a resistance to censorship now no intermediary could stand in the way of P2P exchanges and this is the dawn that every society wanted one day.


2-Day: Ethereum
The day belongs to Ethereum, as this is the light, as it has shown us how much fun a cryptocurrency ecosystem can be filled with many types of applications, such as smart contracts, NFTs, games, and decentralized finances.


3-Sunset: Raini
The sunset belongs to $Raini, because this cryptocurrency is a reflection of the good results that the day gave us, and how a community with a lot of value can be generated, and how a project can grow thanks to everyone's enthusiasm.


4-night: Monero
The night or the dark belongs to Monero because it will be our refuge to have a greater resistance to censorship and absolute anonymity, it will not only be a cryptocurrency that hackers will use, but an entire society that will have resistance to combat bad governments that is . why Monero represents a jewel in the present and future of our existence in life on blockchain.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Thorbit
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
'Thorbit' is a combination of the words 'thought' and 'orbit'.

It is a visual generator of creative prompts, operated by three color-coded rings. 

Each ring can be rotated in 15 degree increments. 

By combining different rotations, new ideas and conceptual approaches are created in the glowing text on the right. 

Additionally, any of the results that appear around the orbit can also be used as viable solutions.

With a minimum of 12,167 possible combinations, Thorbit is designed both as a display piece and as a tool that can be used during times of creative blocks, artistic difficulties, or to provide inspiration.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Forks
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This piece was inspired by the concept of blockchain forks and the decisions needed for blockchains to evolve. I liken this to forks on our own life path, how we use our past and present experiences to make decisions for our near and far future. How we exist each day encountering many different forks, making big and small choices, validating our decisions and hoping the forks on our path lead us in good and rewarding directions. How much of the past do we take with us to make our future?
Forks continues the 'computer space' series - works based on the internal mechanics of what makes the digital realm possible.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: A Disappeared Movement   一场消失的运动
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"A Disappeared Movement" is a performance art project in which the artist acts as a guide and leads the participants to disappear from Xingfu Street. It was launched in 2020, in which the artist spent 6 months investigating the surveillance in the Xingfu Street district in Beijing. He delved into the blind spots of each surveillance camera, creating a set of maps that enable participants to avoid surveillance, and releasing it to the public for free. Later, a fire of wide spread social controversy was ignited due to the reports from multiple world media, such as BBC, SCMP HongKong, France Télévisions, The Globe and Mail, The Times, Dutch Telegraph, Tokyo Shimbun, etc. Subsequently, the Chinese government intervened, investigating all participants of the art project and giving them admonition. Since then, reports and exhibitions of "A Disappeared Movement" have been banned in China.  
Now "A Disappeared Movement" will forever exist on the Blockchain as a piece of Programmable Art.

《一场消失的运动》是艺术家邓玉峰在 2020 年花 6 个月的时间调查北京的幸福大街街区的所有摄像头,并研究每个摄像头的死角,创作一套能躲避摄像头监视的路线图,免费给大众使用。艺术家以“导游”的方式带领参与者一起消失在幸福大街的行为艺术项目。后因 BBC、香港南华早报、法国电视台、加拿大环球邮报、 英国泰晤士报、荷兰电讯报、日本东京新闻等几十家的世界媒体的报道引发了广泛的社会争议。 随后，中国警方介入，对艺术项目的所有参与者进行调查并给予警告。 此后，“消失的运动”的报道和展览在中国被禁止。
现在《一场消失的运动》以可编程艺术的形式永远存在于区块链上。

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Asteroid Blue
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Asteroid Blue


Consists of two 1 of 1 unique panoramic views of a digitally hand carved metamorphic architectural space, that represent day and night cycles.


Gentle lines hide among intense meshes, flowing freely they create a fabric of space or maybe a landscape of a distant asteroid from an outer space? In this art work we invite your imagination to travel outside of human perception or maybe even outside of this world. We invite you on a journey that explores the idea of architectural space. Follow the day and night cycles to become a space explorer and make new discoveries.


Coming from years of architectural research in depth, each digital painting is a carefully crafted abstract architectural landscape, that explores spatial qualities of landscape, surface and texture.
Each art work comes from a process that involves hand sculpting in different mediums, starting from physical sculpting and into a 3D digital hand sculpting.
The art work comes from the project Interface, that took more than 7500 hours to develop the project and methodology plus more than 250 hrs to finish one digitally hand sculpted landscape.

1 of 1
2021
MABLAB

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Lord Gravity
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Lord Gravity is a Master of the Space Age, a contemporary superhero who floats in space. 

He is a ruler of gravity and is often seen being dropped by his spaceship into a planet. He can move objects as well as gravity itself when he uses his abilities. He has very little physical strength, so he is always looking for new ways to help out humans and other planets' inhabitants. 

He is immune to any form of gravitational force and is known for being able to absorb any shape or object that he encounters and then redirects all that energy into a force field that surrounds him while he floats around Space. 

His left arm helps his movements and he often needs to change his appearance, in 24 hour cycles, every hour, to blend in with the colours of the multiple planetary regions that he visits every day.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:

It works by implementing the RGB Color Model, in which the red, green, and blue primary colors of light are added together in various ways. Each layer has multiple states from 0-255, which can be changed to produce any color within the 16,777,216 available colors.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Nothing Out Here / Something Out There
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:

It might not seem like it, but there’s still so much left to discover.

This piece draws some inspiration from the science-fiction short stories of the 1970s, but it is predominantly an attempt to capture visually how the artist feels when listening to their most-played album of 2021: ‘Nothing Out Here’ by Nigel Good.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: What Time is it in My Imaginary Shanghai Right Now?
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This is a glimpse into the creative process. An attempt to show what is going on in the artist's mind. The infinite possibilities when he or she stands in front of the blank canvas in the studio. Every color pick or a brush stroke presents a
fork in the road. The artist keeps exploring, having no idea where the road might lead him/her. Composing, constructing, deconstructing, and rebuilding; brushing,
smearing, covering, and erasing; trying to get to a place that feels right.
While all 24 paintings start with the same basic idea, each ends up in a very different place. Each painting becomes a unique journey not so much about the time of the day but about the artist’s mood at that hour. There is no one painting
that is perfect; rather, each one is a unique journey.
The artist stays out of the frame most of the time. He appears only once, on one
panel, sometime late at night.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Opium
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Your religious beliefs,
Over time, it will not be enough for your body and you will increase your dosage each time. You will lose your ability to question. You will become a stranger to the system you live in... you will believe in stoning women.. or you will start to think that the injustice you experience in societies that see religious administration will be eliminated in the hearafter. You will buy a place from heaven. You will be guided without realizing the power in your hand. You will knit yourself a black shroud while you live. Marx had thought well. Opium was a factor that would lead to violence in cold blood. This is the similarity with religion.
This work; reflects the religious societies that blindfold themselves. Don't believe in anything so much that it completely kills your logic and put an end to some tragic events that have happened over millions of years. The power is in your mind.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: பண் (Pann)
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The seed of all melodies, "பண்" is the truest representation of Tamil music, culture, land and its people. A voyage that connects the past, beholds the present and accompanies into the future, Pann is the beginning of a journey into the world of performed, programmable art. This 30-minute piece of music written in Tamil, was commissioned and produced by Metapurse and is a first of its kind NFT from India. It had its premiere in New York’s Terminal 5 on the 4th of November 2021 at Dreamverse, the world’s largest NFT exhibition curated by Metapurse. Pann became the ambient music for this historic event that merged the physical and digital realms for the first time, showcasing the pinnacle of NFT art of more than 150 artists from around the world.

Woven from nine layers of music, each having several variants within it, the Pann master track captures a fresh collaborative performance of 40 musicians and visual artists.  It can be heard in 19440 different combinations, making it a dynamic piece of music with artwork done by Susha, Ghana N B and Vidhya Vijay that evolve along with every changing state of music. While most of the variants were recorded at 2barQ Studios, Chennai, Tamil Nadu by Sujith Sreedhar and Divine Joseph, the cherry on the cake is the live performance of some of the musical and art variants captured during the Dreamverse experience.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: / WHEN THINGS CHANGE INSIDE YOU, THINGS CHANGE AROUND YOU /
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
We live in a constant rush all the time, and the insatiability of success has been imposed on us unconsciously and consciously as an obligation.


This every day leads us to feel that we need more, that we want something more than what we have, that recognition is an obligation that we need in our lives. Success as an obligation.


What if I don't fit into that, if that's not what I want and need for myself?
Being brave, going against all that, is an act that I value too much. Being passionate about the topics that you like , and proclaiming it I see as a great daring, which not everyone dares to do.
Even if others may not agree, be yourself, that authenticity is what makes you special. If it's what balances you and makes you happy, it's what you have to fight for.

Go back to the basics, go after love, dreams, for a hug, for more smiles, take an unforgettable trip, and find yourself.

This piece features artwork from my children’s book, THE DREAM KEEPERS, but with some teeny-tiny changes.  Can you spot the differences?  There are 4 states, each with 10 unique differences to find. 

Plus, only for the collector of the primary sale, I will mail you a signed copy of the actual children’s book.  After the auction is settled, just DM my Twitter account to provide shipping information.  You can also request a hand-written message if this is a gift to the little Dreamer in your life. 

THE DREAM KEEPERS was published by POW Kids Books in August of 2021, and I am the author and illustrator.  It’s a story about perseverance and positivity. Dreams can come true when you team up with these two helpers - Hard Work and Happy Thoughts!

Compare each state with the original artwork in the book.  Some of the differences will be easy to spot by your 5 year-old.  Some will be trickier!  Totally stuck?  Need a clue?  Just DM me on Twitter.  Happy Reading!

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Dandelion
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
2021, digital manipulated photography, light drawing, abstract symbolism.
Light drawing is a technique in which a camera is used as a canvas and a light source is used as a brush. Some may find it abnormal to move the canvas over a fixed brush, but I like it. The result may be something unexpected. This is drawing blindly; it is difficult to depict something recognizable other than line and color. From time to time, I finish the images in a photo editor. Dandelion is a work from the Narcissus series. The series is united by the presence of an abstract image of a flower in each piece. The theme of the series is Self-concept.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Inwardness #452067
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
I have explored the relationship between the light in photography and line in painting since 2020. This series integrates the results of my research which are photograms, Mixed Media artworks, and AI-generated images. The dataset from this series includes 300 photograms I made in the darkroom and 300 digital paintings I drew.

The concept of Relativity dearly changes my way of seeing and creating. When I hold light source on the Black & White photographic enlarging paper in the darkroom, I come over a sort of illusion that I am drawing. Even though I know that I'm making photographs because each beam of light represents its time and space. Painting is the outlet for my feelings. When I am drawing on the AI-generated image on the computer, the emotion comes and goes, just as the light only lasts for a second and never comes back. For me, this series is neither photography nor painting. It's a kind of new form.


Artwork Title: Inwardness #452067
Date of Artwork: 2021
Dimension: 3840 pixel x 3840 pixel
Type of Work: Programmable Art (Photogram, Digital Painting, GANs Algorithm trained images)
Date of Dataset: 2021
Edition: Unique

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Unfolding Dream
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Collaborative interactive artwork by Coldie and John Van Hamersveld, this composition explores the shared life experiences of both artists as they come together in a highly customizable, living art format. This artwork was created in real-time for the Bonham's auction in November 2021. Elements of this project were captured days prior to minting the artwork including New York City landscapes captured by Coldie. We believe that important experiences can be from long ago as well as a day ago and they hold the same historical significance. The visual vernacular of John Van Hamersveld shares both a realistic and surrealistic vision of what is possible in the real world, as well as the dream world.

The artwork created is meant to bring the viewer and collector inside of our shared dream reality and allow for the story to be visually told through the collector who owns each layer. The variety of options give the opportunity for the layer owner to express their current feelings about the artwork and share in real-time how it affects the total artwork.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: THE DREAM KEEPERS: Cover + Signed Physical Book
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This piece is the cover art for my children’s book, THE DREAM KEEPERS.  A true one-of-a-kind, this is only time I will offer this cover art NFT with 24 changing states.

Plus, only for the collector of the primary sale, I will mail you a signed copy of the actual children’s book.  After the auction is settled, just DM my Twitter account to provide shipping information.  You can also request a hand-written message if this is a gift to the little Dreamer in your life.

THE DREAM KEEPERS was published by POW Kids Books in August of 2021, and I am the author and illustrator.  It’s a story about perseverance and positivity. Dreams can come true when you team up with these two helpers - Hard Work and Happy Thoughts!

This NFT updates each hour, in a 24-hour cycle. Small stars change location and color, and there is one state that is true to the actual book cover.  Can you find it?  Plus as a bonus at midnight, there’s a peek into my illustration process... my original sketch.  It’s not exactly the same as the final cover.  Can you find the parts that evolved throughout the creative process?  

As one of the very few children’s illustrators working in the NFT community, I feel like I’m exploring uncharted territory.  This cover art is the very beginning of introducing NFT art and blockchain technology to a new generation.  I hope you’ll join me.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: / CATCHING  FEELINGS & PERCEPTIONS /
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Identify your mood. To change your mood, you need to realize what you are thinking and feeling. This way you can decide if you need to change your mood to one that best suits your situation.

To identify a mood, stop to think about what you are feeling and why. Put those feelings into words, like, "wow, I'm very passionate right now! " or "I feel very lonely..." You can say this to yourself silently, out loud, or to someone else.

Accept what you feel. After you name your emotion, understand yourself by feeling the way you do. It's perfectly okay (and it's natural!) For you to feel vulnerable, hurted, deceived…or by the was, full of glamour, love and passion. All emotions are acceptable and understandable. But you don't have to hold on to feeling that way. Notice your mood and then choose to modify it.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: One Day, We'll Fly Away
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"So with her eyes wide open my mother dreamed and dreamed some more, describing what life could be for us. She wasn’t talking about a postmortem world, some kind of heaven or afterlife; and she was not speaking of reincarnation (which she believes in, by the way). She dreamed of land, a spacious house, fresh air, organic food, and endless meadows without boundaries, free of evil and violence, free of toxins and environmental hazards, free of poverty, racism, and sexism . . . just free. She never talked about how we might create such a world, nor had she connected her vision to any political ideology. But she convinced my siblings and me that change is possible and that we didn’t have to be stuck there forever."

DG Kelley- "Freedom Dreams"

Featuring Ky'ri  and Ka'mauri

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Misty Rain of Bitan
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Bitan is one of the famous tourist attractions in Asia. It is named after its tender light of the waves and the dark green water. 
At the early stage, it was a pier to bid farewell to the reluctant travelers, and the misty rain even enhanced the sadness to say goodbye to each other. 

Recently, I just said goodbye to a friend who live abroad. Although we promised we will see each other soon, we didn’t know when. 
I was so depressed that I had to transfer my emotion into the scenery and took the pen to draw this work. 
I couldn’t help but thinking of the poem of the great ancient literature master, Ouyang Xiu. “It’s natural that we have infatuations in lives, and they have nothing to do with the wind and the moon.”


2016
Shen Fung Lin

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Childhood Memories of WW
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: I have been creating images of icons from my childhood memory in a thematic series called 'what are they looking at." While exploring these images I realized that a kind of education happened from watching these images in pop culture and I began to paint them using the hybrid approaches of both analogue and digital processes. As I was painting, I reflected on those distant fuzzy memories of seeing these icons on TV, going to their concerts, and reading about them in teen magazines. What had they taught me? This series originally painted on found glass represents those TV screens and, in turn, the iPhone and computer screens we look at now. I invite the viewer to look through this personal homage to my childhood pop iconsand reflect on how culture has changed, how the messaging has regressed and consider what are we looking at now?

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Matrix metastory by 65.000+ avatars
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The day: 32.815 avatars playing Nemo -Keanu Reeves- show you the possibilities and transparency of a fluid reality. The Matrix (1999), by the Wachowskis.
The night: 32.832 avatars tell you during the night: there is not just a red pill and a blue pill, there are many other pills, and the most important ones: the ones you create.
Ghost avatars tell you silently while you sleep: be the owner of your unique reality.

The series “metastories”
I am a Western actor playing roles in Chinese movies; these are 65.000+ Chinese actors playing roles in Western movies. 
In the Pekin Opera (China, 18th century) the color of the mask denotes character: a red face is courage and bravery; a white face is a treacherous and evil man, or a green face reveals surly obstinacy and lack of self-control… These NFTs are made with those masks: we know the character, but we don´t know the actor behind the mask, they are avatars. 
For me is like a “microverse” of thousands of avatars playing “microstories” inside the big story (stories about the story, “metastories”). Personally, I like that this series connects East and West, unites Opera, Film and Digital art, and links the 18th to the 21st century.
(In the second to last column is my signature in “metamorse” :) -morse with avatars, 1 mask=dot, 2 masks=dash).

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Unity in Diversity
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
(24 hours, 24 different colour color variations).
Difference is a necessity, created so that there is a balance of life. If color is a visual language that represents all the differences that exist, then what we see with both eyes, will not be able to represent all the differences that have been created in the universe. It takes thought, understanding and appreciation. Abstract Expressionist painting for me is a way of understanding the visible and the invisible. Freedom to cultivate imagination, empathy, to the deepest feelings. Today's life, which is all mechanical, applications and instant, often makes us forget that we are human beings who have hearts and minds. This work is based on my large scale painting on canvas.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: dynamic rule 1
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
A classic cellular automata updates its state with a static rule based on the state of its neighbor. This piece was created with cellular automata with an extension of that idea. Here the state and the rule are updated based on the state of its neighbor, here the rule changes in every iteration, here the rule is dynamic.

That change moves cellular automata to another level of complexity.

This piece is the result of years of exploration and experiments over that idea.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Origin
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The journey of man has finally taken us to the heavens where one day we might possibly find the source that we are made out of or, better yet; see our own reflection, kindly and graciously, looking back at us. 

This is a series of photographs created in a time where space travel is becoming more accessible to the average person and where mankind is looking outward more than any time before. 

As an artist with a photographic vision, I believe strongly to portray the human spirit as a center point rather than a pawn within our universe. 

May this brief yet timeless collection bring you continued success on your journey through space, time, and immortality. 


Creatively Yours, 
Giano Currie 


(As the first artwork of hopefully many more on this platform I am offering a printed version to its future owner)

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Lord Gravity is a Master of the Space Age, a contemporary superhero who floats in space.

He is able to dissolve himself as the day evolves, from sunrise to sunset and then again every day and night.

This superpower helps Him to discover new worldwide issues, to help humans overcome their struggles, to meditate and to find peace in His work by making Himself invisible to human eyes.

His critics have mistakenly named this power 'Abstract Dissolution', emphasising the artistic nature of his existence. In fact, dissolving in colours also recharges Lord Gravity energy levels and assists Him in the fight against natural forces.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: New York Commuter Sunrise
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This is a series of images depicting the sun rising over New York City, and the ramp that leads into the Lincoln Tunnel, as photographed from Weehawken, NJ -taken on 1.1.2017

The timing of the series is based on the Eastern Standard Time zone (New York)- the sun rises slowly into the morning hours and then goes back down slowly into the hours of the night based on 24 images, each assigned to a specific hour of the day.

The curved road-ramp pictured in the bottom left of the image is essentially the busiest half-a-mile stretch in the whole East Coast, every single morning of the year, as it is the main route that commuters take into New York City for work if they are travelling by vehicle.  "The Lincoln Tunnel, named after President Abraham Lincoln, is one of the busy roadways, with upwards of 120,000 cars passing through every day. The Tunnel’s separate bus lane sees about 1,700 buses every morning." (2017)

These images of the ramp leading into the Lincoln Tunnel are especially unique because they were taken on the morning of New Years Day, 2017.  New Years Day each year is the only time of the year that this ramp is not entirely backed up with traffic by vehicles travelling into New York City.  One day every year, this roadway can be found in a quiet and peaceful state, and only for a few hours- if you're awake to catch it from the night before.

Another unique quality of this image is that this view will absolutely never be seen again- and that is because after 2017, the building that is seen being constructed in the foreground of the Empire State building was completed, and now blocks the view of the Empire State Building from Weehawken, NJ, and the Lincoln tunnel ramp.  Many other buildings have also been constructed which now take away from a lot of the beauty that I once attributed to this skyline as seen from Weehawken and the Lincoln Tunnel.

Generations of my family and myself have used this ramp and tunnel countless times to travel into the city, and this view will always hold a special place in my heart.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: A tribute to the art and design of the mid-twentieth century as well as the jazz music of the 1950's and early 1960's. 0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Imagination Swamp. Tribute to Attitude Apoteket
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Imagination is a swamp of ideas that often decomposes and rarely floats free. In this swamp things move more quickly beneath the surface. The things we do not see, the things we do not tell, lie beneath a variegated layer of green and damp. 

A constant effort to do more of one and less of the other as life slips between our fingers like water under a tap, but just as the water disappears, a current fills the swamp with new organic material matter. 

This piece is a tribute to two of the most creative people I have ever met, Attitude Apoteket, a digital design studio based in Aarhus. Look for them in the metaverse.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The juxtaposition of a historical mythological tale realizes the puppeteers of the 21st century.

Part of the on-going Master Study project @bigcomicart
Also coinciding with a possible of portrait of Satoshi Nakamoto:

"Under Kim Jong-un, North Korea has continued to develop nuclear weapons, testing bombs in February 2013, January and September 2016, and September 2017.[133] As of 2018, North Korea had tested nearly 90 missiles, three times more than in the time of his father and grandfather.[102] In 2012, on the 100th anniversary of Kim Il-sung's birth, he said, "the days are gone forever when our enemies could blackmail us with nuclear bombs"" -- Wikipedia, 'The Education of Kim Jung Un'

"Jupiter is usually thought to have originated as a sky god. His identifying implement is the thunderbolt and his primary sacred animal is the eagle,[13] which held precedence over other birds in the taking of auspices[14] and became one of the most common symbols of the Roman army (see Aquila). The two emblems were often combined to represent the god in the form of an eagle holding in its claws a thunderbolt, frequently seen on Greek and Roman coins.[15] As the sky-god, he was a divine witness to oaths, the sacred trust on which justice and good government depend." -- Wikipedia

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Inwardness #332165
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
I have explored the relationship between the light in photography and line in painting since 2020. This series integrates the results of my research which are photograms, Mixed Media artworks, and AI-generated images. The dataset from this series includes 300 photograms I made in the darkroom and 300 digital paintings I drew.

The concept of Relativity dearly changes my way of seeing and creating. When I hold light source on the Black & White photographic enlarging paper in the darkroom, I come over a sort of illusion that I am drawing. Even though I know that I'm making photographs because each beam of light represents its time and space. Painting is the outlet for my feelings. When I am drawing on the AI-generated image on the computer, the emotion comes and goes, just as the light only lasts for a second and never comes back. For me, this series is neither photography nor painting. It's a kind of new form.

Artwork Title: Inwardness #332165
Date of Artwork: 2021
Dimension: 3840 pixel x 3840 pixel
Type of Work: Programmable Art (Photogram, Digital Painting, GANs Algorithm trained images)
Date of Dataset: 2021
Edition: Unique

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"Once there were people here. More people than you'd ever believe. More people than Earth has seen since the day or.. Or even until now. They lived in this huge tower. Kind of like the massive multi purpose high rises they have in China these days. But bigger as there was not exactly an end in sight. I mean if you looked at it it was a structure. Defined with boundaries and all that. However when you tried to find the end of, the last floor for example, it was an effort in vain. In The Old Tower, the end as well as the beginning were all elusive, at best an ouroboros."

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Warrioress | Twisted Tree No. 2
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This is 'Warrioress'. She is the second of my Twisted Trees, and she also changes through the year's worth of seasons in 24 hours. She is a 1/1 creation. Watch for a few of the Wild Ozark critters to appear in this one: bobcat, deer, and bear. These are all critters that live here at Wild Ozark.

All of my NFT work begins with a real painting in handmade Ozark watercolor pigments. To make my paints, I gather, crush, and process rocks I find here in the creeks or on our land in northwest Arkansas USA. When I paint a Twisted Tree, I don't know how they will look until their personality reveals themselves to me. Each one is unique.

I made modifications to the painting for this NFT by adding hand-drawn or photography elements. The leaves are hand-drawn and digitally edited. The animals began as photo captures from our game camera. Other differences from the real-life original, like the flowers and weather elements, for example, are done digitally.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: AI x Klimt x Adele x Dreams
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
AI x Klimt x Adele x Dreams
by Hulki Okan Tabak
minted on Async Art

24 pieces 24 hours 

...

This work is based on Gustav Klimt's first portrait of Adele Bloch-Bauer (1907). The piece has been sold by Christie's in a private for USD 135 million in 2006. The piece is in public domain. 

I have walked through various stages of re-imagination on the original piece. I have first applied a general conversion which was subsequently mixed with various genes from randomly selected digital works. I selectively defined starting points and increments that I followed for the next 23 images in journeying with Adele through genders and worlds. The process was awesome, fun and immersive. The end result is strange, post-modern and anything but plain beautiful. It speaks to my mind partly as a visual provocation but even more so as a vessel to convey how close sit different states and sides of life.

...

Portrait of Adele Bloch-Bauer I (also called The Lady in Gold or The Woman in Gold) is a painting by Gustav Klimt, completed between 1903 and 1907. The portrait was commissioned by the sitter's husband, Ferdinand Bloch-Bauer, a Jewish banker and sugar producer. The painting was stolen by the Nazis in 1941 and displayed at the Österreichische Galerie Belvedere. The portrait is the final and most fully representative work of Klimt's golden phase. It was the first of two depictions of Adele by Klimt—the second was completed in 1912; these were two of several works by the artist that the family owned. (Wikipedia)

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Our Mind is a Multiverse
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The MIND is a power entity and it is more alive than we ever know, more alive than we can ever imagine. 
Every time we delve into the depths of our mind, we are essentially traversing through a MULTIVERSE. 
And the more we traverse, the more we discover ourselves in the process.

This piece has four states, each reflecting the state of our mind at that time of day. 

During the day we are mostly filled with LIGHT, but the dark zone is just lurking in the middle just out of reach of the light.
When we wake up at day break we are filled with a FIRE to make things happen during the day. 
And by Sunset we have reached a state of NIRVANA, or so we think only to recognise that the DARK is just starting to creep in the replace the Light, until daybreak.
... Until Daybreak.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The Four of Wands represents appreciation for family, gratitude for the best things and experiences life has to offer. The central figure in this image is a Twisted Tree clutching eggs within the embrace of her roots, fierce and loving as she guards them. Life-giving waters run a meandering path among the dark and murky landscape - a reminder that even in the darkest hours there is hope for survival. WAGMI. 

This work is based upon one of my paintings using Ozark pigments. My inspiration for the 'eggs' came from seeing trees alongside the creeks here in northwest Arkansas (USA). Many of them have rocks trapped within the roots and the trees have grown to enclose them.

I took over three thousand photos spanned nearly a decade for a specific project and selected over a thousand photos from there as the Dataset for AI training. The photographs have been gestated by AI that integrated all the subtle emotions of the original pieces, which are the most exciting parts of this series.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Stereoscopy Skull
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Indeed, death is not a terrible thing. What is more terrifying is the fear of death. The fear of death makes us besides suffering. It also makes us refuse to prepare for death. That refusal will eventually bring great suffering when that day comes. But if we admit that we ourselves will die sooner or later We realize that instead of running away from death for the rest of our lives. It is better if we turn our hearts to prepare for death. For this is the only way for us to find peace when the end comes.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: dLOVE.
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
​dCREATION. is the first artistic attempt to represent and idealize the origin of humanity following the new evolutionary theories. Fine Art history meets the Sci-fi worldwide trend in a unique atmosphere of emotions and colors, leaving a window for every kind of personal interpretation. A fantastic series of four different Art Pieces to describe the unknown feeling between the Creator and his born, all connected by a third element, the “God Particle” or the Higgs-Boson, which plays an essential role in this metaphysical relationship. The three parts of the whole, the sacred Trinity, all those essences find a place to exist in this abstract world, a reality full of mysteries and secrets, which will reveal a new vision of human evolution myth. A dualism of specific colors characterizes each piece to describe all feelings involved in this ancient and primordial love, where is essential to find your own truth to explain the whole.

Illustration n.2: dLOVE.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Inwardness #129001
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The concept of Relativity dearly changes my way of thinking, seeing, and creating, and keeps looking for balance and harmony in the final artwork. I have explored the relationship between the Light in photography and the Line in painting since 2020. Photography retains the interpretation of the Light, and the Line could be one of the forms to present the Light. I created photograms with the shape of the light in the darkroom, then trained them to generate brand-new integrated images. After that, I painted and destroyed the image with lines, colors, and recomposed the image.

The material in this series includes Photograms (Cameraless photographic processes), Digital Paintings, and AI-generated images (Gans Algorithm). The dataset of AI-generated images contains 300 photograms and 300 digital paintings.


Artwork Title: Inwardness #129001
Date of Artwork: 2021
Dimension: 2160 pixel x 2160 pixel
Type of Work: Programmable Art (Photogram, Digital Painting, GANs Algorithm trained image)
Date of Dataset: 2021
Edition: Unique

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Welcome to the Barnyard! It's a place where mayhem and madness rule the days. The citizens of the barnyard think WAGMI, but I'm not so sure about that. Goat is likely NGMI, for sure. And let's hope that balloon stays aloft.

The background for this work is one of my original paintings in Ozark pigments. It's a real scene from a real barnyard in Weesatche, TX in a little German settlement that is now a ghost town. I used pics from my husband's photo album to recreate the scene. For this NFT I embellished it. A lot. I hope you enjoy it. I had a ton of fun creating it.

and the chalk said like a fresco inside the earth

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Swimming Through the Weephole
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Exploring the ideas of bodily autonomy, nature and fantasy through mixed media. This NFT has been created from an original sculpture. The box was primed in my favourite earthy pink, I layered found objects and drawing using resin on the inside. The title refers to the figures swimming. A weep hole, weep or weep-brick is used in masonry to allow moisture to escape from walls, they function like the eyes of a walls, keeping the inside of the home safe from rot and mould. The weep hole is an essential, generally unnoticeable part of brick houses. I imagined the world inside that space of essential-invisible being. The button headed swimmers are a playful take on humanoid figures.

24 images, 24 states of mind on Async Art

Mobile Houses
by Hulki Okan Tabak

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Big Bounce
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
According to the Big Bounce scenario, the universe did not begin with the Big Bang. Rather, a universe existed that contracted into an unprecedentedly hot, dense state (which we think of as the Big Bang) and then expanded again. These drawings - Day and Night - reflect that scenario, the Big Bounce, in which everything contracts again.

These are unique hand-drawn artworks. The artworks Day and Night - #2 and #3 - were created on sturdy black drawing sheets measuring seventy by fifty centimeters. Due to the unique drawing technique, each art production was time intensive.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Street Photography, Japan - ストリートフォトグラフィー
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
A series of 6 black and white street photos I took during my time in Japan (full descriptions below). 
The idea was to use the 24 hours autonomous template with only 6 images which change every hour. This way wherever you are you'll be able to enjoy the full set of images. 
The 6 photos are part of the series: "WABI-SABI: Acceptance of transience... The Beauty of things that are Imperfect, Impermanent, Incomplete." 
There are lots of details in these images. It is ideal to show this artwork on a large 4K screen. Please take the time to look at them on full screen. Thank you.

DESCRIPTION OF PHOTOS:

1. "Wa": Harmony. The harmonious heart of the Japanese value system | Reflections... Into The Depth Of Life.
KYOTO - I was standing behind the man with the umbrella taking a picture of his reflection on the window while he was looking into the shop at the two women working. The idea was to create something like a double exposure but within a single shot. Many layers in this image. 

2. “Satori”: Enlightenment. 
TOKYO - To attain Satori a person must get rid of all their desires and enmities at the source... This monk in the middle of the busy streets of Tokyo was completely detached from the chaos of daily life.

3. "Reflect On Yourself, The Dance Of Man And God"
KAMAKURA - The idea was to show "Man" as the small entity he is in comparison to the greater powers at play such as nature/universe/energy. The little man seems to be dancing in front of his God, which in reality is just a reflection of what he does not fully understand.
I took this photograph with certain elements in mind:
- the small man is in direct contrast with the large reflection of the Buddha (to balance it out).
- the part of the Buddha at the top is the one missing in the reflection.
- The "leading" lines of the pavements have been used to direct the viewer's attention to the "real" subject... the little man. 

4. “Mono no Aware”: Pathos. Contemplating the Fleeting Beauty and elegance in action. 
YOKOHAMA - My objective was to freeze the moment yet retain some movement on the main subject (the hair of the woman, the dress, the shoe) to make the photo more dynamic and interesting. Also, the woman walking out of frame was part of the intention, so that it appears she is leaving (this is not a crop but the full image). Please note that there is no model in this image - it is just someone walking by.
All of these elements were combined to convey the idea of Fleeting Beauty and Elegance... no beauty will last forever, and the Sakura/Hanami itself is a symbol of the transience of beauty in Japanese culture.

5. "Setsu": Transition. An important turning point in life.
TOKYO - When I saw this couple leaving each other, I composed the shot using the phone boot to balance the white rectangle where the two people are standing.

6. “Uchi to Soto:” Inside and outside social relationships. Who to share your feeling with.
KYOTO - A street photography composition.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Kate Moss
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
For the newest addition to my ICON series, I present to you Kate Moss. Kate has been at the forefront of fashion and art since the early 1990s. I wanted to pay homage to her timeless beauty in the form of a beautiful clock. 

Each of the 12 polaroids that comprise this mosaic is given a time slot of one hour. At midnight Kate is shown in deep blue, but as each hour passes, another polaroid will shift color, starting at the top left and going through the hours of the day from left to right. So when it is 4am, the first four polaroids will be lit up in color. At noon, when all of the polaroids have changed colors, the piece will begin to reverse and shift gradually back to deep blue, with the amount of blue polaroids now dictating the hour. I have signed the piece with my initials AM on the bottom right corner for the AM hours, and left it blank for PM. Like a clock, you will be able to see what hour of the day it is based on how many of the polaroids have shifted color. 

The first owner of this NFT will also be gifted the 1/1 physical polaroid set used to create this digital clock. The piece will come framed in a sleek white frame measuring 20'' x 15'' and have a unique color combination not seen here on Async. It will be accompanied by a signed certificate of authenticity.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Mental Images
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Alison Jackson presents 24hrs in the life of Queen Elizabeth II.

Jackson is a BAFTA and multi award winning artist who explores the cult of celebrity, using cleverly styled lookalikes depicting scenarios we have all imagined but never seen before

Jackson discusses ‘The Queen’ in more depth. She creates the works in the Chelsea streets & a roster of elaborate country estates. She, her crack team, and lookalikes are highly skilled at running from Police when they turn up unannounced for a photoshoot with ‘The Queen'.

00:00 Breakfast in Bed with Corgis
The Queen wakes up every morning with her corgis, and breakfast.

01:00 Putting on Stockings
The Queen never dresses herself.

02:00 Feeding the Corgis
Always fed on a silver salver, never by a footman

03:00 The Footman plays with Corgis
The Queen was a little tired this morning, so a footman had to take over

04:00 The Queen on the Loo 
You can’t imagine The Queen on the loo, but here she is! The location really disagreed to “The Queen”, so she snuck in...

05:00 Diana gives the Finger
I was so nervous when I made this! Studying at the Royal College of Art, shortly after Diana’s death, I wasn’t allowed to make any work about Princess Diana! The ‘Royal’ college didn’t want to become the ‘College of Art’. It’s Diana saying ‘F*** You’ to the media for chasing her.

06:00 Walking with Camilla
I always wonder what they discuss

07:00 The Queen watches her Horses Mate
This was shot at a friend’s stud. My photo assistant and I were so shocked at the first ‘go’, no one took any pictures! We had to wait 30 mins for the stud horse to reload...

08:00 The Queen and Camilla Drink 
I think Camilla needs a stiff drink

09:00 Looking at Cards
The Queen is the most popular celebrity in the world.

10:00 Catching the Bus
One likes to do normal things

11:00 At William Hill
The Queen can't resist racing! Here she is getting in a quick bet in

12:00 The Queen, Camilla and Kate at the Hair Salon 
Of course, The Queen has to keep her hair absolutely set

13:00 The Queen Shops at Tesco 
This was shot ‘guerrilla style’ I just turned up with ‘The Queen’ and my whole crew. Shot on Curzon Street, London

14:00 The Queen’s Selfie with Kim Kardashian 
I had to create a brand new wig for this, which cost around £10’000 to create

15:00 The Queen with Sir Elton John
The real Sir Elton John, shot in his home in Las Vegas. He sang Dancing Queen and they danced together in his ballroom

16:00 Blowing out her Candles
This cake had to be 1/2m wide in order to fit all 95 candles on it

17:00 Sunbathing in a Deckchair 
Relaxing at one of the most beautiful castles in England, Belvoir Castle

18:00 Royal selfie
This was a nightmare shoot. None of my lookalikes actually look like the real person, it’s all about getting them in the right position. But as soon as one person was set up, the next had moved

19:00 The Family receive Gifts 
PDA from Harry and Meghan, and William and Kate representing the institution, as usual. Shot at The Director’s Institute 

20:00 Celebrating with Champagne
We opened 5 bottles of Champagne: it felt exactly like Christmas, despite shooting in summer

21:00 The Royal Family watches Oprah
I envisaged a shocked scene whilst  ‘The Firm’ watched Oprah’s interview. My Oprah lookalike is a dead ringer.

22:00 Queen with Marigolds
This is my response to the public-fantasies around The Queen

23:00 The Queen Sleeping in Regalia 
The Queen is one of the busiest women in the world. She completes nearly 400 engagements a year, and she’s got to carry that Crown
