0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Sonder
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
“Sonder. You are the main character—the protagonist—the star at the center of your own unfolding story. You're surrounded by your supporting cast: friends and family hanging in your immediate orbit.

Scattered a little further out, a network of acquaintances who drift in and out of contact over the years.

But there in the background, faint and out of focus, are the extras. The random passersby. Each living a life as vivid and complex as your own.

They carry on invisibly around you, bearing the accumulated weight of their own ambitions, friends, routines, mistakes, worries, triumphs and inherited craziness.

When your life moves on to the next scene, theirs flickers in place, wrapped in a cloud of backstory and inside jokes and characters strung together with countless other stories you'll never be able to see. That you'll never know exists.

In which you might appear only once. As an extra sipping coffee in the background. As a blur of traffic passing on the highway. As a lighted window at dusk.”

― The Dictionary of Obscure Sorrows - John Koenig

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The shadow clock
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Time is a entity that is purely human made but certainly controls all aspect of us. Right from birth or meetings to literally everything.  The rotation of the planets although is symbolic of time - we say one day when earth completes one rotation and we say one year when earth completes one revolution. 

The position of a mere planet in the galaxy is representative of time - the all powerful entity. This is in fact true in our social lives too - we feel like time is too slow when we’re in certain circumstances while it’s too fast in others - our emotional position is the measure of time in this case. 

The shadow clock is a symbolic representation of the premise of how mere positions in space of various elements of life represents time.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: This art reflects one of the pandemic consequences, which is a poor mental health. Sometimes life turns into a prison and we don't know how to wait for the blow of fate. While in the day we can hide our feelings, in the night the horror takes control of ourselves. The horror can be painful. But one thing allow us to survive the night. The certain that after the night it cames the day keeps the flame inside our hearts alive. With the day it cames the small hapiness of seeing the sunrise. With the sunrise in our minds we progress and become stronger.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Sirens Call
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Created in collusion with graphic designer TypeDistortDecay, as part of Copy Planet's expanding universe. 

Informed by the physical, mental, and behavioral changes that follow a 24-hour cycle. 

“Circadian Rhythms” is a pilot series comprised of 3 works for Copy Planet’s Centre for Climatology. 

The work intends to present a meditation on the sublime as a way to contemplate these natural phenomena as agents of change through emergent technology. 

As a respond to the shifts experienced within the current zeitgeist and its effects on the human and non-human participants existing in space time. 

Each work will be uploaded twice ( daytime / nighttime ) responding to the natural processes of light and dark.  

Words by James Ly

Created in collusion with graphic designer TypeDistortDecay, as part of Copy Planet's expanding universe. 

Informed by the physical, mental, and behavioral changes that follow a 24-hour cycle. 

“Circadian Rhythms” is a pilot series comprised of 3 works for Copy Planet’s Centre for Climatology.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This unique crypto-native piece features 24 mandalas changing every hour, imitating the rhythm of an entire day. It is a collaboration between 24 diverse artists from 12 different nations ranging from the playful age of 6 to the graceful age of 65.

It features 24 stories ranging from heartbreak to loss of innocence, the discovery of faith, and everything in between. It imitates life, creating a perfect yin-yang wrapped inside an eternal clock.

The Complete Story of the Piece: https://www.daogen.io/the-world-in-sync

This is a DAOGEN Collaboration. We are a ​creator collective aimed at facilitating the reach and impact of diverse voices. We exist to empower and in turn, facilitate never before seen crypto-native creations.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Paradox Pathways
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
In the 1980s, string theory was proposed to be the sought-for unified theory that unifies all forces and matter. The strings are unable to be detected with current scientific methods. It's theorized that there are mini dimensions that are undetectable to us, and the strings are just as small so that they can vibrate through these dimensions connecting all forces and matter. 

In this artwork, an individual discovers how to see and interact with these strings. He is able to navigate the strings as if they are a path on the ground. While traversing the paths through dimensions, he saw and experienced such otherwordly sensations and emotions. Experiences that are so alien to one's sense of reality that they can not be explained justly. 

Tears run down his face as he is overcome by such never-before-seen beauty and by the realization that he is lost with no way back to his home dimension. What first felt like a dream quickly became a nightmare. He is constantly traversing the dimensional paths, running into the other versions of himself. However, his other selves aren't the same as him - they feel as though they are imposters, dangerous ones at that. His other selves feel the same way toward him.

Is he doomed to wander the paths in fear for eternity? Will he eventually find a way out? The answer is unknown.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Ratio
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
“Every unique thing in nature is related to the whole, and partakes of the perfection of the whole. Each particle is a microcosm, and faithfully renders the likeness of the world.

In geometric harmony of the cosmos there are ways that resemble, there are universal patterns, from blood vessels, to winter trees or to a river delta, from nautilus shell to spiral galaxy, from neurons in the brain to the cosmic web.

A whole universe of connections is in your mind – a universe within a universe – and one capable of reaching out to the other that gave rise to it. Billions of neurons touching billions of stars – surely spiritual.”

Alejandro Mos Riera

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Sonder Vol.2
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
“Sonder. You are the main character—the protagonist—the star at the center of your own unfolding story. You're surrounded by your supporting cast: friends and family hanging in your immediate orbit.

Scattered a little further out, a network of acquaintances who drift in and out of contact over the years.

But there in the background, faint and out of focus, are the extras. The random passersby. Each living a life as vivid and complex as your own.

They carry on invisibly around you, bearing the accumulated weight of their own ambitions, friends, routines, mistakes, worries, triumphs and inherited craziness.

When your life moves on to the next scene, theirs flickers in place, wrapped in a cloud of backstory and inside jokes and characters strung together with countless other stories you'll never be able to see. That you'll never know exists.

In which you might appear only once. As an extra sipping coffee in the background. As a blur of traffic passing on the highway. As a lighted window at dusk.”

― The Dictionary of Obscure Sorrows - John Koenig

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Regeneration #202997

Type of Work: GANs Algorithm trained photograph
Date of Dataset: 2010-2017
Edition: Unique

The photographs in the series of Regeneration produced by using Generative Adversarial Networks. I took over three thousand photos spanned nearly a decade for a specific project and selected over a thousand photos from there as the Dataset for AI training. The photographs have been gestated by AI that integrated all the subtle emotions of the original pieces, which are the most exciting parts of this series.

Like I said, simple logic.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Viksate
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Viksate means ponder or observe. Viksa means the unconsciousness. 

This creation has a total of 42 variations. each variations meaning changes based on the symbols in it. It is up to you to interpret what each variation means. 

Fish symbolises our unconscious mind that holds secrets and intelligence. It shows a need to look within the deep waters of our unconsciousness to be awaken.
The crescent moon symbolises entering into new chapters in ones life while the third eye symbolises an awakened soul. 

Lotus symbolism is sacred in many religions and culture including in Hinduism. In Asia you will find the lotus prominent in various cultures.

In Hinduism, the Lotus symbolises knowledge, abundance, wealth, sexuality and spirituality. The partially bloomed lotus represents the need for us continuously learn and question our ideas and thoughts. The lotus emerges from murky waters to bloom into existence. 

Carl Jung likened the flight of birds to the spiritual development of the human soul. Like birds the soul flies upward in its search for enlightment, freeing itself from its attachment to earthly desire. 

But the process of self realization takes time and our attachments to materialistic desires don’t vanish immediately but with each flight, it brings back to us new wisdom for the soul to develop and learn. 

Like the lotus, we suffer, experience and learn to grow from the mud and bloom into enlightened souls.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: SPHINX WITH WINGS
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
THE WORK INCLUDES LAYERS WITH A TOTAL OF 4 DIFFERENT WING EDITIONS IN IT WHICH CAN BE COMPARED TO MULTIPLE RESULTS. THE BODY PART WAS CREATED BY A GENERATIVE 3D DESIGN WITH THE ARTIST'S DEBUGGING. THE ARTIST, CHEN ZENG, TRIES TO BRING NEW GENERATIVE TECHS INTO CLASSIC FIGURES, CREATES BRAND NEW VIRTUAL EXPLORATION.
斯芬克斯最初源于古埃及的神话，是长有翅膀的怪物，通常为雄性，当时的传说中有三种斯芬克斯——人面狮身的Androsphinx、羊头狮身的Criosphinx、鹰头狮身的Hieracosphinx。亚述人和波斯人则把斯芬克斯描述为一只长有翅膀的公牛，长着人面、络腮胡子，戴有皇冠。多种形态的变化是艺术家选取司芬克斯作为图层拆解的出发点。
在希腊神话中，赫拉派斯芬克斯坐在忒拜城附近的悬崖上，拦住过往的路人，用缪斯所传授的谜语问他们，猜不中者就会被它吃掉，这个谜语是：“什么动物早晨用四条腿走路，中午用两条腿走路，晚上用三条腿走路？”俄狄浦斯猜中了正确答案，谜底是“人”。斯芬克斯的人面象征着智慧和知识。一说斯芬克斯之谜在更深层次的表现为“恐惧和诱惑”，即“现实生活”。在艺术家看来，司芬克斯同样在帮助人理解人本身。艺术家的系列雕塑作品都使用人工智能参与造型生成，本次nft作品中分开的身体元件来自于不同参数下程序给出的结果，艺术家认为，研究人工智能生成逻辑的过程同样是一个尝试理解人本身，理解创造力的过程。


The sphinx originated from ancient Egyptian mythology. It was a winged monster, usually male. There were three types of sphinx in the legend at that time - the Androsphinx with the human face and lion body, the Criosphinx with the head of the sheep, Hieracosphinx with eagle head. Assyrians and Persians describe the Sphinx as a winged bull with a human face, beard and crown. The variety of forms is the starting point for the artist to choose Sphinx as the layer dismantling.

In Greek mythology, the Sphinx sat on a cliff near the city of Thebes, stopped passers-by, and asked them with a riddle taught by the Muses, and those who could not guess right would be eaten. This riddle is: "What animal walks on four legs in the morning, two legs at noon, and three legs at night?" Oedipus guessed right. The correct answer is "human". The human face of the sphinx symbolizes wisdom and knowledge. It is said that the mystery of the Sphinx is expressed in a deeper level as "fear and temptation", that is, "real life". From the artist's point of view, the Sphinx is also helping people understand people themselves. The artist's series of sculpture works all use artificial intelligence to participate in modeling generation. The separate body elements in this nft work come from the results given by the program under different parameters. The artist believes that the process of studying artificial intelligence generation logic is also an attempt to understand people themselves. , to understand the process of creativity.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Man is a great puzzle, the top of which lies in the human subconscious - dreams.

"Dreams are the representation of instinctive desires." Sigment Freud said once.

"Dreams are the collective subconscious, the bloodline memories of our ancestors." Carl Gustav Jung expressed similarly. 

gN(dReaM^16)Gm - a complex, interesting and thoughtful work created by WeirDao's 16 artists based on their own experiences and feelings. The confliction of multiple elements constitutes a large number of Day&Night transformations, representing the dreams' from shallow to deep, from surface to inside, from still to movement.
Each element is the intention of an artist's deep perception, so that dreams are no longer dreams or not only dreams. This is a journey from symbol to reality, an awakening of the collective subconscious.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: A Money Tree from the Cedar Tavern
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
A 'Money Tree', or Pachira Aquatica is said to bring good financial fortune and positive 'chi', or energy, into a home.
I'm interested in plants and organic structures, here from an artistic perspective and as a means of (abstract) expression in various media including photographic art, also to confront both a seasonal (winter) and social (covid/omicron) mood.
We still have so much to learn from plants: architecturally, spiritually, scientifically... 
A main objective is simply to take the viewer closer or 'inside' the houseplant over 24 hours and to explore and appreciate its details via unusual perspectives, perhaps finding inspiration in the organic design. The 24 individually-enhanced, selected images are not tied to the hours from any single day but have been chosen to follow a loose progression; my own adventure or preoccupation. You could say this Money Tree is a reflection of its unique growth and my small mission to find out (or 'see') the details of this growth. Why do we strive to explore and enhance Nature? Perhaps we want to make it more attractive than it is, to increase its appeal, and energy, and to impress the passive viewer (within) somehow through our diverse bids for control and freedom? The result: this new form of 'super' Money Tree as a dynamic NFT. The  process of art can be as obsessive as studying money markets, or finding global cures for viruses, and it's a question which relates to an ongoing series titled  'Organic Metaverse'. It aims to explore our need for being lost in the natural world, already present, right before our eyes, and where 'a fool sees not the same tree that a wise man sees.' (Blake). Most of art is a safe form of exploring, so let's set out again, and possibly reveal more of the less familiar and hidden things, or just find sanctuary there.

ade mc
2022

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: CodeSpace #1
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: These geometric structures are created by conception at the intersection of the purely mathematical structure of figures and the cultural perspectives. Also, the lines in the structure are influenced by the creator's intention, as well as unconscious intervention elements to generate and deliver contemporary insights. In addition, individual geometric shape combined with each other can expand the possibilities of new spatial interpretation. ‘Found line', ‘Selected line', ‘Discovered line', ‘Intersected line', ‘Line with unstable proportions', ‘Curved line', ‘Sharp line', ‘Complex line' etc… These various kinds of 'lines' intersected each other, may enable us to get new aesthetic interpretations and appreciation. Those geometric forms could be harmonic traces  between the unpredictable lines of intuition and the lines with a rule. This CODESPACE project is for experimental question : the operability between the imperfection of the physical world and the perfection of the mathematical world, or on the contrary.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Labor of Love | Mixed Media Collage
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This project began as a tactile, mixed media collage series using the simple, geometric, heart shape, a symbol of love and joy and used quite heavily as an emoji these days. These works were created to manifest and channel love into this physical world directly from the source of all that is through the creative process, using found paper and reinterpreted digitally through the use of clipping masks and vector graphics and yet again through blockchain technology and generative art processes. Some of the found paper for these works include; shopping bags, 1970's toy catalogs, food packaging, kids' activity books, newspaper and magazine pages, and more.

Mr.Brian Design has been using found paper and tactile materials as a rendering technique in his mixed media portraiture for several years and has exhibited those works throughout Japan. This series is a paired down result of those efforts in pure form.

Mr.Brian Design's Mixed Media Portraiture may be viewed here: https://mrbd-at-good-neighbors-gallery.tumblr.com/

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: 3l3m3nt4l
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This series of elemental mandala collages were created during a time filled with emotional turmoil. 

Inspired by a Buddhist meditation practice called Metta Bhavana (Loving Kindness); I embarked on the creation of these four collages, with the objective of transmuting through creative practice, this unskillful yet natural emotional state of mind, into love, kindness and forgiveness - for the self and the other.

In researching Buddhist iconography and associated symbolic meaning, homage was payed to the source of this Metta practice, by incorporating the five Buddhas with their associated correlational properties:

Akshobhya = Blue = Water = Dawn
Ratnasambhava = Yellow = Earth = Noon
Amitabha = Red = Fire = Sunset
Amoghasiddhi = Green = Air = Midnight.

The 5th Buddha is incorporated around the circumference of the four collages:
Vairochana = White = Space = Timeless

These images were original digitally created a 4000x4000px, then reduced to 2160x2160px to upload to ASYNC.

Correlation source: 'The Mandala of the Five Buddhas' - by Vessantara (c)1999 [Windhorse Publications]

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Per Unitatem Vis
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
“What we call the beginning is often the end. And to make an end is to make a beginning. The end is where we start from.”
-T.S. Eliot

"Lo que llamamos el principio es a menudo el final. Y hacer un final es hacer un comienzo. El final es donde comenzamos." 
-T.S. Eliot

This is my first piece created to change every hour and it is a part of a transmedia exploration that consist of a series of sculptures, paintings, drawings and also a Virtual/immersive exhibit that I made as an app for Apple, Android and Windows called "Amor Fati Exhibit". I used T.S Eliot to explain the theme of the piece but every hour has a different meaning.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: 24h Dimanche / Pls Send Nudes
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
BRIEF: “Hot, Hot, Hot!” is a collection of static and animated digital art reflecting on love, longing, and existential loneliness. A self-exploration of the feminine form; an introspective odyssey upon the digital seas only touching briefly the sensual shores of the real world. Named after each of the 7 days of the week in French &  English words/phrases; this piece represents 1 day consisting of: 1 primary static image + 5 alternate glitch states (used to create a separate animation). 

BACKGROUND: 

For millennia the feminine form has been appropriated, commodified, objectified, curated, policed, and brutalized by men and for the male gaze. 

Today, unconditional self-acceptance of feminine bodies remains an act of radical self-love and still carries risk of violence in a deeply misogynist culture. The luxury of safe self-expression is elusive; only further complicated by age, color, creed, sex, gender, ability, sexuality, and class. Whether it be in real or digital spaces, feminine bodies are treated with a spectrum of toxic hostile reactions from self-appointed patriarchal enforcers who take it upon themselves to steal joy, love, life, and happiness from any female (sex or gendered) persons that exercise their self-sovereignty in public or private; real or digital spaces. Despite the culture of terror, the feminine aspect of humanity is asserting herself and sisters are embodying in their power.

INQUIRY: 

When the last grain of dust settles on the digital frontier what will the real world look and feel like? Will NFB’s (non-fungible-beings) and their fleshy forms be treasured or despised? Will the real world lay in rubble? Does a world still reeling from the pandemic return to desperately pressing flesh against flesh; or will glass, silicone, and electricity be the sole comforts accessible to those inside of a deepening dystopian nightmare? 

What does love, intimacy, and vulnerability look and feel like in the future? How does it feel in the present? Will the essential need of skin to skin contact between human beings drive our species to create teleportation devices out of sheer desperation? As HD gives way to 4K, 6K, 8K, Augmented Reality, and Virtual Reality, how far can we, and will we, push ourselves across the world; across the universe — at the speed of light — in search of love?

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
BRIEF: “Hot, Hot, Hot!” is a collection of static and animated digital art reflecting on love, longing, and existential loneliness. A self-exploration of the feminine form; an introspective odyssey upon the digital seas only touching briefly the sensual shores of the real world. Named after each of the 7 days of the week in French &  English words/phrases; this piece represents 1 day consisting of: 1 primary static image + 5 alternate glitch states (used to create a separate animation). 

BACKGROUND: 

For millennia the feminine form has been appropriated, commodified, objectified, curated, policed, and brutalized by men and for the male gaze. 

Today, unconditional self-acceptance of feminine bodies remains an act of radical self-love and still carries risk of violence in a deeply misogynist culture. The luxury of safe self-expression is elusive; only further complicated by age, color, creed, sex, gender, ability, sexuality, and class. Whether it be in real or digital spaces, feminine bodies are treated with a spectrum of toxic hostile reactions from self-appointed patriarchal enforcers who take it upon themselves to steal joy, love, life, and happiness from any female (sex or gendered) persons that exercise their self-sovereignty in public or private; real or digital spaces. Despite the culture of terror, the feminine aspect of humanity is asserting herself and sisters are embodying in their power.

INQUIRY: 

When the last grain of dust settles on the digital frontier what will the real world look and feel like? Will NFB’s (non-fungible-beings) and their fleshy forms be treasured or despised? Will the real world lay in rubble? Does a world still reeling from the pandemic return to desperately pressing flesh against flesh; or will glass, silicone, and electricity be the sole comforts accessible to those inside of a deepening dystopian nightmare? 

What does love, intimacy, and vulnerability look and feel like in the future? How does it feel in the present? Will the essential need of skin to skin contact between human beings drive our species to create teleportation devices out of sheer desperation? As HD gives way to 4K, 6K, 8K, Augmented Reality, and Virtual Reality, how far can we, and will we, push ourselves across the world; across the universe — at the speed of light — in search of love?

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Aesthetic Antagonists
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Lord Gravity tends to spend most mornings,
staring at the windows of his own place at Lake Black Albatross. 
From there He is often able to see strange figures from the distance, 
that populate the lake and its surroundings.
These figures are part of the nihilistic group called "Aesthetic Antagonists", 
a propaganda machine that generates
deception, hype and disinformation.
The hero, Master of the Space Age,
is constantly monitoring this group, 
as they parade across his window over the lake, 
in search for a rebellious reaction from Lord Gravity 
- repeatedly unsuccessfully.

It is designed to activate your subconsciousness using self-directed neuroplasticity.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: What time is it? S H : I  T
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Anxiety, parents, hurry, career, pressure, friends, speed, work-work-work, dream of days 48 hours long, diet, stress, time, adrenaline...
An ironic version of the human being today and his fantastic relationSHIP (or "relationSHIT") with time.

As it usually happens in life with our state of mind, also here every hour is closely linked to the other ones through the use of color: every layer takes one color sample from the previous layer and then adds a new color, creating a never-ending cycle and a wide range of hues.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
“Cyberspace. A consensual hallucination experienced daily by billions of legitimate operators, in every nation, by children being taught mathematical concepts... A graphic representation of data abstracted from banks of every computer in the human system. Unthinkable complexity. Lines of light ranged in the nonspace of the mind, clusters and constellations of data. Like city lights, receding...”
― William Gibson, Neuromancer

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Belleza A New Age "Genesis"  (4 Layer)
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"Belleza A New Age"

Genesis Piece for WILLIAM BARRINGTON-BINNS with collaboration from ERIK MATSON

This will be followed up by a small yet intimate collection from William & Erik.

Photography + Abstract Art : 4 Layers set to a 24 hour cycle.

Featuring model Natasha J Bella.


William is an International award winning DOP - In both Still & Motion Imagery Creation. Key work in Architectural/Commercial/Haute Couture/Lifestyle/Hospitality and Conceptual  Art, now based in Bangkok, Thailand, he has exhibited globally at galleries and exhibitions including OXO London, Xposure UAE, Macau, Hong Kong Museum Of Contemporary Art Bangkok (MOCA), HOP Gallery Bangkok and Dubai, William has won many accolade and awards including Dezeen awards , MPA, PPAC The Prestigious Photography Award from His Royal Highness Sultan bin Muhammad Al-Qasimi. He is an Ambassador for ARRI Lighting and is Currently working on several Commercial projects for, Apple, world famous Hotel Architects Bensley, a UNESCO Arts Scholarship Foundation Project . William is proactive in promoting both gender and ethnic equality, sustainable and fair trade for all.

Erik has  a passion for the dark yet vibrant creative pallet, Erik Matson is an abstract artist, musician and animation designer. Credits include Netflix, Steam/Valve, FUEL TV, Wave and Blaze, Levi's and many others

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: SPINAL
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
SPINAL is a piece I originally created during the summer of 2021. It was born not unlike any of my other creations. After a long day at work and getting the kids tucked in for the night, I sat down at my desk, put on the headphones, and got to work. If I recall correctly, there was a mix of Soundgarden, Alice in Chains, and Pearl Jam streaming from the playlist that night. And, as usually happens, a couple of hours later, the piece was complete. I'm honestly not sure what happens during that time, I just let the music lead the way and eventually push the shapes and colors into a form that speaks to me. There's something about the symmetry and the mix of hard and soft lines in this one that give it a great mood I think.

For this updated version of SPINAL, I chose to bring the artwork to life on Async and reveal the power of adding and removing the various layers to create 24 unique versions of the artwork that update every hour of the day. Each has its own minimalist vibe while simultaneously tying itself back to the original creation.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: The Keeper of Days features a different specter for each phase of the day based on Eastern Standard Time. There are four Keepers altogether, Day, Sunset, Night and Sunrise. Each at 2160 x 3840 px.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Radiant Child
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: The Radiant Child is a portrait celebrating the life of the legendary Jean-Michel Basquiat. The artwork goes through multiple stages of transformation (through collaboration) including some engagement with augmented reality elements. In this portrait I have collaborated  with Gerald Genie who has been quite instrumental in the transformation of the artwork and has come to show how powerful teamwork can be.  Basquiat is indeed a source of inspiration and great influence in our work prior to our collaboration and reflects in our artworks.  Enjoy the piece

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: FOMO, Greed and the parasites
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This piece takes a look at the Ikari side of human behaviour. Ikari means anger, wrath, exasperation. I use expressionism to visualise Ikari. 

Here I visualize societies social and moral issues that cause harm and grief to human lives. 

FOMO and greed is often interchangeable. In these pieces you will see minimal changes and similarities in FOMO and Greed. 

Parasites on the other hand leech onto people and drain them. Humans are the greatest parasites.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Artwork Title: Regeneration #131310
Date of Artwork: 2020-2021
Dimension: 3840 pixel x 3840 pixel
Type of Work: GANs Algorithm trained photograph
Date of Dataset: 2010-2017
Edition: Unique

The photographs in the series of Regeneration produced by using Generative Adversarial Networks. I took over three thousand photos spanned nearly a decade for a specific project and selected over a thousand photos from there as the Dataset for AI training. The photographs have been gestated by AI that integrated all the subtle emotions of the original pieces, which are the most exciting parts of this series.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Water Roses Memories
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This artwork consists of 4 separate digital drawings in a Day/Night cycle as enabled by Async Art's technology.

...

Hearing the vocals of Fish when I was 16 was an unforgettable moment. I guess it was Warm Wet Circles the first time and soon after I discovered the early works of Marillion including a set of incredible B sides.

Now many a time later, I fed some of the lines from Script for Jester's Tear to the VQAN+CLIP software. I experimented with the results with additions, my photographs and some iterations to arrive at these images. The final edit in Photoshop was only for sizing and minor contrast curve adjustment. The artwork is pretty much AI x HoT as it came out.

...

Water Roses Memories by Hulki Okan Tabak
minted on Async Art, 2022

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Inwardness #700791
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The concept of Relativity dearly changes my way of thinking, seeing, and creating, and keeps looking for balance and harmony in the final artwork. I have explored the relationship between the light in photography and the line in painting since 2020. Photography retains the interpretation of the light, and the line could be one of the forms to present the light. I created photograms with the shape of the light in the darkroom, then trained them to generate brand-new integrated images. After that, I painted and destroyed the image with lines, colors, and recomposed the image. The materials in this series includes Photograms (Cameraless photographic processes), Digital Paintings, and AI-generated images (Gans Algorithm). The dataset of AI-generated images contains 300 photograms and 300 digital paintings.


Artwork Title: Inwardness #700791
Date of Artwork: 2022
Dimension: 2160 pixel x 2160 pixel
Type of Work: Programmable Art (Photogram, Digital Painting, GANs Algorithm trained image)
Date of Dataset: 2021
Edition: Unique

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: 3D rendered image composed of numerous runs of generative coding and basic fractal reciprocals functions.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Real Imaginary Async #1
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
In The Real Imaginary Verse, contemplating flowers made of fractals of time and space. 
You can feel the quantum energy popping here and there during the early seasons. A bit similar to our pollen during spring in our universe I guess. 
Depth of Infinity makes these beautifully changing over nuances of lights during a full cycle. Absolutely stunning in person... 
Time is relative and flexible, and the dividing line between past, present, and future is an illusion. Reality is ultimately timeless. These quantum flowers are the reflection of that magical delight of pure energy with no time nor space boundaries. 

"There is no branch of mathematics, however abstract, which may not some day be applied to phenomena of the real world." ― Nikolai Lobachevsky

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Cubechain
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Any work we do at any time of the day does not stay there. A cycle begins that will affect everything forever. Every good or bad thing we do goes into a loop that affects everything else.

Our thoughts and actions are sometimes very clear, sometimes a little vague, sometimes harsh, sometimes soft. We build our life on this cycle.

24 cubes, this is a cycle that expresses sharpness, clarity, dark and light. All of them are in a cycle both in relation to each other and within themselves.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: MASK OF PHILOSOPHY IS CREATED BY WINCHAWA ///

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Real Imaginary Async #2
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
How deep would you go following the infinite patterns of The Real Imaginary Verse. Indefinite Sunsets and Sunrises, yet defeating Time and Space.
This reminds me of the spiral dynamics theory. Organisms in the universe go through a predictable set of stages of development. These stages each exhibit a set of values that the organism tries to obtain. 
Such an amazing feeling to experience this powerful moment full cycle, calm and serine, full of energy, yet stormy and intense of vibrancy. 

"If I have seen further than others, it is by standing upon the shoulders of giants."  – Isaac Newton

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Fraud case
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Criminal Judgment of the People's Court of Hanjiang District, Putian City, Fujian Province
 (2017) Min 0303 Xingchu No. 571

        Cai Qinglan defrauded the victim Chen Meiyuan, which caused Chen Meiyuan's daily mental suffering for many years. She and her husband have been petitioning the court without a clear result. In the criminal judgment issued by the Hanjiang District Court on April 27, 2018, recovering the illegally obtained finances of the defendant Cai Qinglan and returning it to the victim. In August of the same year, the court seized the house that Cai Qinglan illegally purchased. So far, the court has not appraised and auctioned off the property in question. The victim has petitioned many times, but no clear result.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Before Sunrise
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: For the most part, we are abstract, determined by motives that arise from thoughts, not by immediate impressions.  Much of the reason for our pain and happiness is not the actual "now" but abstract thinking. When we have intense mental pain, we even create some physical pain, just to divert our attention from mental pain to physical pain. Mental pain is far greater than physical pain, it hurts the body more easily and more seriously than physical pain. "It's not the things themselves that trouble people, it's people's beliefs or perceptions about them."

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Our Bright Future
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
I hope that our future is going to be bright. 
Simple logic says that it won't. Ecology, politics, medicine, social questions - so many problems to solve! 
But I still hope...

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Dive
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
How often do we pay attention to things located in the center?
The one that takes up the most space. Large dimensions. Louder voice.
We are jumping on the top, while missing the details and what is really important.

After all, often only a small part (person, event, creation) can give a name to the whole phenomenon, era or canvas. 

Who has the main role in this picture?

This work is done in an original combination of fine art, digital art, collage.
Consists of 4 parts.


ABOUT THE ARTIST:

For a long time I was associated with art, artists, galleries, exhibitions. And all this time he was behind the scenes. Worked with Art Gallery (by R. Abramovich) / Sotheby’s Institute of Art. And at some point, overwhelmed with inspiration, decided to become an artist.

In my work I combine different styles, approaches and techniques.
Statics and movement. Color and monochrome. Fine Art and Generative Art. In combination, all this gives the effect of hypnosis, fundamentality and unique esthetics.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Think Pink - #1 - Loneliness to Depression
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This piece is part of a mental health awareness campaign called Think Pink, designed to help people spot, relate and understand the emotions they are feeling. Each piece of artwork is a representation of what the mind could project if one was experiencing that said emotion.

When it is daytime, this piece represents Loneliness. When the sun sets and the moon rises, its state will change to Depression.

LONELINESS - The feeling of being isolated or cut off.
Mental response: Avoiding crowds, large events, or social situations. A desire to be included, wanted.
Anger, bitterness. A feeling of unworthiness. Daydreaming about inclusion.
May escalate to: SADNESS, HURT, DEPRESSION, RESIGNATION.

DEPRESSION: A state of withdrawal; extreme sadness and reduced vitality.
Mental response: Focusing inward. Desiring to live in the past or be alone. Poor observation skills. Obsessive thoughts. A negative outlook. Losing track of time. An inability to concentrate.
May relate to: NOSTALGIA, REGRET, SADNESS, LONELINESS.

We struggle to talk about our emotions and our mental health. Through art and NFTs people and communities can come together to recognise and speak openly about their mental state.

Emotions are nothing to be ashamed of. We all have them.

Welcome to the movement that is... Think Pink.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Fountainhead
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: There is a fundamental loneliness, which is different from everyday loneliness, nor is it being without friends or being alone. Some people are forced to betray themselves, but think they are loved. Some people are lost all their lives, and finally drive themselves crazy with fire. There are also people who control the life and death of others, but they cannot accept the death of flesh and blood. Connected to each other, unable to escape the trajectory of life. We are pregnant with destruction and rebirth, fighting against disasters in our lives. It seems to cut the raw green fruit with a sharp knife, leaving pale juice and black sacs.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Think Pink - #2 - Guilt to Remorse
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This piece is part of a mental health awareness campaign called Think Pink, designed to help people spot, relate and understand the emotions they are feeling. Each piece of artwork is a representation of what the mind could project if one was experiencing that said emotion.

When it is daytime, this piece represents Guilt. When the sun sets and the moon rises, its state will change to Remorse.

GUILT: A feeling of culpability over an offence (either real or imagined).
Mental response: Replaying what happened. Anxiety. Thoughts filled with self-loathing. Desiring to confess or share the pain or burden with another. Brooding, retreating inward, withdrawing from others.
May escalate to: CONFLICTED, REGRET, SHAME, REMORSE

REMORSE: Distress resulting from guilt over wrongdoing; a desire to undo
Mental response: Mentally berating oneself over an action or poor decision. Wanting to face consequences. Empathy for other parties and what they are going through. Obsessing over finding a way to repay the debt.
May escalate to: SHAME, REGRET, DETERMINATION.

We struggle to talk about our emotions and our mental health. Through art and NFTs people and communities can come together to recognise and speak openly about their mental state.

Emotions are nothing to be ashamed of. We all have them.

Welcome to the movement that is... Think Pink.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: SPLIT: portrait within a portrait
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This unique artwork made in the "Portrait within a portrait" technique and consists of 24 self-sufficient peaces.

If you look closely, there is someone else in the portrait (besides the main character) who is looking at us. 
Every hour, the “inner portrait” changes.

IDEA. 
There are different personalities hidden within each of us. They huddle in the rooms of our unconscious, watch and wait to break out of confinement and take over us.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Under Construction
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
What the “Modern” human describes as the “primitive” human, has long used or re-used places that are suitable for living without leaving for thousands of years, which has resulted in multi-layered hill like structures which we call “mounds”. Mounds are the usage of living spaces that are constructed from the ashes of what has been destroyed by wars or natural causes, a rebirth.

It is possible to examine the distant past through archeological methods. But how can we examine the current moment we live in and the process of these “modern mounds”?

Throughout history and today, we see these layered structures rapidly moving towards both the sky and the undergrounds while transforming, breaking, accumulating, and mixing. In this context, the project works to strip away from the real plane, and move towards the plane of an image while creating a new space that offers contemplation through the examination of overtime. Also the project challenges the concept of “a moment” while examining a long stretch of time and works to keep an up to date record of these modern mounds.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Artwork Title: Regeneration #301229
Date of Artwork: 2020-2021
Dimension: 3840 pixel x 3840 pixel
Type of Work: GANs Algorithm trained photograph
Date of Dataset: 2010-2017
Edition: Unique

The photographs in the series of Regeneration produced by using Generative Adversarial Networks. I took over three thousand photos spanned nearly a decade for a specific project and selected over a thousand photos from there as the Dataset for AI training. The photographs have been gestated by AI that integrated all the subtle emotions of the original pieces, which are the most exciting parts of this series.

“Beauty is about more rounded, substantial becoming. So I think beauty in that sense is about an emerging fullness, a greater sense of grace & elegance, a deeper sense of depth & also a kind of homecoming for the enriched memory of your unfolding life.” -John O’Donohue

Initial collector will receive a link to the AR experience for personal use. This memento mori was originally created for the Billelis remix competition.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Florality
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Florality is an artwork depicting how the vibrance of our cultivation looks when the sun/moonrays falls on it at different times both during the day and night. Far away from the hustle-bustle of our city life which is full of machines, here we see the beauty of the nature in various shades. With advancement in technology, we look at out mobile phones or our watches to know the time, but a farmer who has sown seeds and seen the soil enriched with cultivation, knows the time of the day just by looking at the sun/moon rays falling on it. He does not need any watch or a mobile phone to know if its noon or evening. The same flower can look differently and in a different colour throughout the day, just like humans who can be vibrant  irrespective of time - be it a warmer day, a sunny noon, a breezy evening or a chilled night.

Florality is a unique 1/1 artwork based on 24-Hour time cycle comprising 24 images that change one image per hour (Pacific Time). The art created using javaprocessing & simulated based on day & night time cycles using neural machine learning algorithms.

Technical specifications ->
Dimensions - 3000 x 3000
Total Images - 24
Average size per image - 11.08 MB
Total file size of 24 images - 266 MB
Edition - Unique (1/1)

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Love, anxiety, exploration. A nostalgic look at today's world through the filter of the virtuality we grew up with to reflect on the digital realities to which we are now migrating. Click it on.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Mind maze
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: The main thing is accuracy and work! All ideas are within the labyrinth that is our mind. From time to time, one of the ideas manages to follow you, leading you to the exit.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: I didn't see, I didn't hear, I don't know.
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Did they not talk or did we not make them talk? 
Did they plug their ears or did we deafen them? 
Did they close their eyes or did we blind them?

Whose natural habitats have been destroyed by humans,
whose hunted savagely for their skin, teeth, and fur,
who completed his whole life in a cage by being fed with drugs for his rapid growth,
tortured daily to fight each other,
It is dedicated to all animals who have been wronged and whose voices cannot be heard on the streets, in production farms such as prisons, laboratories, neglected shelters, circuses, zoos and many more.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: PHONONS
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Phonons is an Async Music piece composed of 7 individual stems, each one of them capable of 5 interchangeable variants.
A Phonon can be described as a unit of vibrational energy that arises from oscillating atoms within a crystal.
The vision behind this piece is to to represent the cycle of life, evolution, discovery, mutation and conflict through sound.
Each stem in each of its variants plays an equally important role in achieving this transformation by blending, fusing and at times clashing with its counter-particles.
This track is designed to loop endlessly: its end reconnects with the beginning in a perpetual cycle.

PULSE is the beginning of the voyage
BREATH is the first contact with reality 
MASS is where particles expands, experience and grow
TRANSMUTE represents the ability to change, morph and reinvent
ANTI-MATTER is absence of tone, a negative space where noise and disruption take center stage

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: OUR FATHER IN THE METAVERSE #1
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
https://mathiasrusch-metaverse.com/

The "Our Father" - The cycle of paintings by artist Mathias Rusch (*1927-2003)   

If we speak of the most important prayer of Christian faith, then of the "Our Father".  
 
This prayer gift of Jesus to his disciples, later handed down to us Christians, has become the actual Christian self-understanding, the "prayer of the Lord". Packed into a few sentences, it has come to be regarded as the actual confession of faith and is prayed millions of times a day, both individually and in communities. The fact that this "conversation with God" has hardly ever been depicted (in contrast to the Passion) is probably due to the immense message it conveys. The fact that the painter Mathias Rusch dared to translate the "Our Father" can be explained by the fact that his daily work was based on faith, hope and trust in God. Mathias Rusch was aware that he could only exist in the understanding of his art "as a gift of God". Most of his late works (Our Father, Live and Let Live, Sermon on the Mount, Lauretan Litany, Litany of the Sacred Heart) were written, as he confessed, under the "kind help" of the Highest, always accompanied by personal prayers, meditations or invocations. The fact that Mathias Rusch did not reveal a dying word for the interpretation of his works of art is to be justified by the fact that he understood himself to a large extent as a mediator of a higher power. Thus we are sometimes quite helplessly confronted with an immense abundance of Christian symbols, metaphysical allusions, concretizations and abstractions, in unique hues and compositions. Completely in the sense of Mathias Rusch we dive before the 13 works of art into the enormous topic of earthly existence and Christian eschatology, marvel before the color power, before the hints, confessions and convictions of the very deeply felt "Our Father's". Finally, we become humbled and ultimately grateful to be initiated into the world-prayer of a "knowing" believer, again and again, with each glance at each of these magnificent works of art. Whoever takes a longer "eye" look at this self-contained, unique complete work, consisting of 13 unique pieces in oil on canvas, 170x170cm, will not be able to resist a lasting effect and deep consternation.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Alcohol Inks on Black acrylic sheet.
Here you can see the Evolution of my painting. Each layer is made with fluid inks and pure 99% isopropyl that I poured on the acrylic sheet  and dried with a hair dryer. Each layer brings more dimension to the painting. The last layer is the final painting when the composition is achieved and completed.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: 38 States of a Young Woman - Set 3
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
38 States of a Young Woman - Set 3

38 States of a Young Woman is a generative study on an image itself created by mixing photography and other generative portraits.

There are 38 derivative images of which 28 are used to create 4 sets of images. The sets themselves are created in the order of image creation except for the 3 occasions (out of 28) when an image was replaced by one from the end of the list.

There are 7 sets of 4 images Day/Night cycles to be published on Async Art.

Athena Novo, 2022

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: AI x Street of Lost Dreams
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
AI x Street of Lost Dreams
by Hulki Okan Tabak
4 piece Artificial Intelligence based programmable artwork on Async Art
1/1 minted on 2022

...

This artwork is an AI led derivative version of the eponymously titled work on Async Art at https://async.art/art/master/0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0c8-3396.

I have run experimental variations on the base image which is one of the photographs used in this address. I have created a similar 4 piece pure GAN driven image set that can be viewed alongside the original mint on Async Art.

Part of a series of Marylebone, London based artworks. All of these works consist of photographs taken by me in January 2020. It is the time of Lunar New Year, Wuhan lockdowns, and the very first signs of the virus in Europe.

Marylebone was originally an Ancient Parish formed to serve the manors (landholdings) of Lileston (in the west - which gives its name to modern Lisson Grove) and Tyburn in the east. The parish is likely to have been in place since at least the twelfth century and will have used the boundaries of the pre-existing manors. The boundaries of the parish were consistent from the late twelfth century to the creation of the Metropolitan Borough which succeeded it. (Wikipedia)

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Beautiful
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This work is a celebration of the human skull. In our culture, the skull is seen as a symbol of death and horror. But it is more than that. It is also the vessel in which our life and personality resides. So I see it as both beautiful and precious.

Series of hand-drawn skulls and ornamented background, painted by ai computer algorithms.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Faces of Opinion
Regeneration #353046
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Artwork Title: Regeneration #353046
Date of Artwork: 2020-2021
Dimension: 3840 pixel x 3840 pixel
Type of Work: GANs Algorithm trained photograph
Date of Dataset: 2010-2017
Edition: Unique

The photographs in the series of Regeneration produced by using Generative Adversarial Networks. I took over three thousand photos spanned nearly a decade for a specific project and selected over a thousand photos from there as the Dataset for AI training. The photographs have been gestated by AI that integrated all the subtle emotions of the original pieces, which are the most exciting parts of this series.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Sometimes you feel like there is an invisible force.
The hidden figure that directs the chess game.
With the hands of puppet chess players decides the outcome of the battle.
Revolutions.
Pandemic. 
Economic crisis. 
Wars. 

It seems like someone's having fun playing games where you're just a pawn.

They hide behind colorful newspaper headlines.
Behind significant events and incidents.
They're watching you from stock charts and freshly printed banknotes.
What's this? 
Paranoia? 
Conspiracy theory? 
Or…?

Digital painting 
3000 x 3000 px

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Za Myr: I Have a Mouth and I Can Scream
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
“In keeping silent about evil, in burying it so deep within us that no sign of it appears on the surface, we are implanting it, and it will rise up a thousand fold in the future. When we neither punish nor reproach evildoers, we are not simply protecting their trivial old age, we are thereby ripping the foundations of justice from beneath new generations.”

― Aleksandr I. Solzhenitsyn, The Gulag Archipelago 1918–1956

Za Myr (Ukranian) = For Peace

For Peace is a series of artworks in support of peace, based on AI assisted artworks built upon Solzhenitsyn's words, conceptualized by HoT and MM and AN.

1/1 Edition on Async Art, 2022

Za Myr: I Have a Mouth and I Can Scream builds on the footsteps of a GIF I've minted in this series on KnownOrigin titled Za Myr: Sleza .. For Peace: A Teardrop .. In Three Languages at https://knownorigin.io/gallery/7935000-za-myr-sleza-for-peace-a-teardrop-in-three -- These works have similar AI origin points, different base image files and different editing methods. What they share is concern for what's going on in Ukraine today (Feb 26, 2022).

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: OUR FATHER IN THE METAVERSE #5
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
https://mathiasrusch-metaverse.com/

The "Our Father" - The cycle of paintings by artist Mathias Rusch (*1927-2003).

If there is a most important prayer of Christian faith, then it must be the "Our Father".

This prayer gift of Jesus to his disciples, later handed down to us Christians, has become the actual Christian self-understanding, the "prayer of the Lord". Packed into a few sentences, it has come to be regarded as the actual confession of faith and is prayed millions of times a day, both individually and in communities. The fact that this "conversation with God" has hardly ever been depicted (in contrast to the Passion) is probably due to the immense message it conveys. The fact that the painter Mathias Rusch dared to translate the "Our Father" can be explained by the fact that his daily work was based on faith, hope, and trust in God. Mathias Rusch was aware that he could only exist in the understanding of his art "as a gift of God". Most of his late works (Our Father, Live and Let Live, Sermon on the Mount, Lauretan Litany, Litany of the Sacred Heart) were written, as he confessed, under the "kind help" of the Highest, always accompanied by personal prayers, meditations or invocations. The fact that Mathias Rusch did not reveal a word for the interpretation of his works of art is to be justified by the fact that he understood himself to a large extent as a mediator of a higher power. Thus we are sometimes quite helplessly confronted with an immense abundance of Christian symbols, metaphysical allusions, concretizations, and abstractions, in unique hues and compositions. Completely in the sense of Mathias Rusch we dive before the 13 works of art into the enormous topic of earthly existence and Christian eschatology, marvel before the color power, before the hints, confessions, and convictions of the very deeply felt "Our Father's". Finally, we become humbled and ultimately grateful to be initiated into the world-prayer of a "knowing" believer, again and again, with each glance at each of these magnificent works of art. Whoever takes a longer "eye" look at this self-contained, unique complete work, consisting of 13 unique pieces in oil on canvas, 170x170cm, will not be able to resist a lasting effect and deep consternation.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
38 States of a Young Woman - Set 6

38 States of a Young Woman is a generative study on an image itself created by mixing photography and other generative portraits.

There are 38 derivative images of which 28 are used to create 4 sets of images. The sets themselves are created in the order of image creation except for the 3 occasions (out of 28) when an image was replaced by one from the end of the list.

There are 7 sets of 4 images Day/Night cycles to be published on Async Art.

Athena Novo, 2022

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Pharmacy
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This is a historical pharmacy room anywhere in the world.
Maybe somewhere in India BC.
Maybe somewhere in Egypt or Ancient Greece.
It may also be a pharmacist's room in China or Japan.
Maybe somewhere in Turkey.
Maybe the Middle East or Europe...
I created this room simply by thinking, "What would a laboratory be like at that time?"
I separately created the stones, wood, tables, lights and surrounding glass bottles.
When the room was illuminated with a volumetric light, a beautiful view emerged.
I wish I could work there.
I don't know what's in those barrels either.
:)
----
3D modeled and visualized.
Render: 3000x2000 px.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Artwork Title: Regeneration #201247
Date of Artwork: 2020-2021
Dimension: 3840 pixel x 3840 pixel
Type of Work: GANs Algorithm trained photograph
Date of Dataset: 2010-2017
Edition: Unique

The photographs in the series of Regeneration produced by using Generative Adversarial Networks. I took over three thousand photos spanned nearly a decade for a specific project and selected over a thousand photos from there as the Dataset for AI training. The photographs have been gestated by AI that integrated all the subtle emotions of the original pieces, which are the most exciting parts of this series.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: EUkraine flag
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Europe is much more than its geographical borders. Actually is more than a certain number of members states, it is a mindset with a strong set of values, like peace, freedom, solidarity, tolerance and democracy.

Noam Chomsky, asks the essential question whether democracy and inherent freedom are values to be preserved or threats to be avoided ?

He replies, "in this possibly terminal phase of human existence, democracy and freedom are more than values to be treasured, they may well be essential to survival."

If Europe represents that, we must all be europeans and contribute in that way to preserve humanity. This is WHA's contribution.

EUkraine flag by WHA. 
Colors: Yellow (FFFF00) and Blue (0000FF).

WHA is a multidisciplinary and hybrid author exploring the intersection of art, literature and technology, based in Europe.

WHA - preserve our humanity

https://www.wha.digital

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Wet bitterness, very white
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Those struggling in the "sea" face the most painful storms. Stone carves time, and in the process of creating things, we also see imperfection, failure, confusion, distortion. There is a tenacious and persistent sense of tragedy. It is tightly connected to the earth and has an immovable weight. It is closely related to the life philosophy and life of the people who live there.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Pain crushes air and water
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: People of different ages have different dogmas and creeds. Traces of truth can be found in many ways even in the most complex and absurd creeds. The traces are accompanied by bizarre things, mixed in a strange way, but always recognizable. All truth is like a plant, sprouting in rocks, burrowing in cracks and detours, crouching, pale, aggrieved, perhaps this pain can crush air and water, but still grow toward the sun.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: RELISH
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: BEAUTIFUL IMPERFECTIONS collection. A call on cherishing the present. Eyes are symbolic in my art. They represent state of mind or action. At the basics, closed eyes is introspective and open is observatory and interractive.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Faith. Hope. Love. Peace
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Studies show that Visualizing Peace is a powerful resource in Peace-building and Conflict Resolution.  

While violence receives lots of attention, it’s the visualization of peace that can actually stop the violence.

It is proved that colorful images of Peace and Harmony contribute to nonviolence.

“Art is a tool that can communicate and transform the way people think and act. Arts can change the dynamics in intractable interpersonal, intercommunal, national, and global conﬂicts.” (Michael Shank and Lisa Schirich, “Strategic Arts-based Peace-building”).

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Lady Luck from Manifesto of Chance - III
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Lady Luck from Manifesto of Chance - III

Manifesto of Chance is a Blueprints project I've created involving trillions of combinations. Its ultimate "massage" is to let go and seize the day. 

Lady Luck series is derived from one of the base images used in the project and it is extensively edited. They are stand alone pieces which point out to seeing (not solving) the larger puzzle of the project. None of the Lady Luck themed artworks appear in the project as the project is rather strange and different and wild and crazy.

conceptualized, created and minted by Athena Novo on Async Art 2022

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: La jalouse
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
As a press photographer, I attended many red carpet events. Though I witnessed glamorous moments, faces and looks, I realized that I was drawn to create this world from a different perspective; one which undressed the soul, and rendered a more authentic moment. After some time, it became the same scenes, the same clichés, the same smiles, the same looks and the same photographers. As a celebrity, having to see more than 30 flashes per second every time a photographer spots them, probably makes them want to protect themselves. Seeing celebrities live in this world of excessive media coverage, I started to develop a mixed feeling of admiration and respect, but also pity, and finally detachment. 

The Personalities are decomposed and re-assembled in an abstract composition, guided by my instinct and fed by what the model inspired in me.

The original digital size of "La jalouse" portrait is 120 by 180 cm. 

This is a portrait of the actress Ashley Judd.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Déesse en dérive
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
As a press photographer, I attended many red carpet events. Though I witnessed glamorous moments, faces and looks, I realized that I was drawn to create this world from a different perspective; one which undressed the soul, and rendered a more authentic moment. After some time, it became the same scenes, the same clichés, the same smiles, the same looks and the same photographers. As a celebrity, having to see more than 30 flashes per second every time a photographer spots them, probably makes them want to protect themselves. Seeing celebrities live in this world of excessive media coverage, I started to develop a mixed feeling of admiration and respect, but also pity, and finally detachment. 

The Personalities are decomposed and re-assembled in an abstract composition, guided by my instinct and fed by what the model inspired in me.

The original digital size of "Déesse en dérive" portrait is 120 by 180 cm. 

This is a portrait of the cosmetic doctor Tabasum Mir.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Have you ever talked to a tree?

I talked to a tree for a year. I've seen every aspect of that tree. Its first leaves, its broken branches, its anxiety for the future and the attack of people on it.

That tree endured everything in silence.

He was still alive when I left.

Artwork Title: Regeneration #852129
Date of Artwork: 2020-2021
Dimension: 3840 pixel x 3840 pixel
Type of Work: GANs Algorithm trained photograph
Date of Dataset: 2010-2017
Edition: Unique

The photographs in the series of Regeneration produced by using Generative Adversarial Networks. I took over three thousand photos spanned nearly a decade for a specific project and selected over a thousand photos from there as the Dataset for AI training. The photographs have been gestated by AI that integrated all the subtle emotions of the original pieces, which are the most exciting parts of this series.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Inwardness #231260
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
I have explored the relationship between the light in photography and line in painting since 2020. This series integrates the results of my research which are photograms, Mixed Media artworks, and AI-generated images. The dataset from this series includes 300 photograms I made in the darkroom and 300 digital paintings I drew.

The concept of Relativity dearly changes my way of seeing and creating. When I hold light source on the Black & White photographic enlarging paper in the darkroom, I come over a sort of illusion that I am drawing. Even though I know that I'm making photographs because each beam of light represents its time and space. Painting is the outlet for my feelings. When I am drawing on the AI-generated image on the computer, the emotion comes and goes, just as the light only lasts for a second and never comes back. For me, this series is neither photography nor painting. It's a kind of new form.


Artwork Title: Inwardness #231260
Date of Artwork: 2022
Dimension: 3840 pixel x 3840 pixel
Type of Work: Programmable Art (Photogram, Digital Painting, GANs Algorithm trained images)
Date of Dataset: 2021
Edition: Unique

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Some Boxes
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
In a random part of the universe where the stars shine bright, there is a place in which people come together and wait for a signal, to open and close some boxes. The meaning behind this phenomenon is still unknown.

SUMMARY
Some Boxes is a social experiment about art ownership. The goal requires collectors to open and close their boxes when signaled to do so. Any collector that fails to comply with the rules will result in their box being permanently sealed with tape, removing that collectors ability to open or close their box forever.

BOX(CONTROL)
This layer is the box at the top of the artwork. It’s used to signal Box(1) through to Box(20), when it's time to open or close their respective boxes. There are only 2 rules:
- If Box(Control) is open, collectors must open their box. 
- If Box(Control) is closed, collectors must close their box. 
All collectors will have 48 hours from the transaction timestamps of any Box(Control) changes, to comply with these rules. The frequency of when Box(Control) opens or closes is currently unknown. Box(Control) cannot be purchased. 

BOXES
There are twenty boxes from Box(1) through to Box(20). Boxes can be opened or closed by their layer owners. The decision to open or close a box is decided by the owners, but signaled by Box(Control).

TAPE
There are twenty tapes from Tape(1) through to Tape(20). Tape is used to permanently seal boxes when they fail to comply with any rules.
There are four colors of tape: brown, white, black and gold. The color of tape used to seal a box will depend on how many other boxes were sealed before it.
Once tape has been used to seal a box, that tape layer will be burnt, causing those boxes to be sealed forever. Tape layers cannot be purchased. 

For a more comprehensive guide and better understand of Some Boxes, please visit: https://www.bottlesartwork.com/someboxes

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Digital Distance
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Of all of the obstacles we must overcome to build a flourishing community, it is the distance between us that demands the most energy but that also inspires and excites. Many of us have discovered new friends on the far side of the world, distance many will never traverse, physically, but that is digitally just seconds away. We build these relationships in a digital world. Not unlike the physical world, we also need to learn to cope with this digital distance. 

This work is based on the series "Distance", Monotype prints in ink on paper. As an active member of the NFT community, I've discovered the many parallels between the physical and digital distances that impact our relationships; for better and worse. Not only are territorial distances that impact time zones but also cultural, generational and gender distances that must be carefully and thoughtfully navigated. Each of these have kept us separate from each other at times, everyone retreating to a safe distance, due to lack of mutual understanding. Here in the NFT space we've learned from each other's individual experiences, appreciating and inspiring everyone and inevitably reducing the distance between us. 

That's how we are building a strong community and a better future.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Welcome to my Crypto world, 

a world that is decentralized and beautiful. Storks carry your bags of crypto to a floating island where the space shuttle "Decentralize" is waiting to take you bags to the moon. Where mining means walking into an arched valley and connecting to your favorite cryptos and plugging in to it's data cable. Spending time with your family watching this all happen, even while flying your ETH kite. Imagining ideas for this series, I could see this image flash in front of my eyes and thought my daughter and I would definitely love doing this.

This is the 4th piece in my Crypto world and this piece was all drawn from scratch on my Graphics tablet. It was a family affair creating too with my wife and little girl helping with the colouring. To see the previous 3 pieces, please check my Twitter account @benza333 to work your way to them through my other galleries, or even drop me a DM about it, I'm happy to chat :) .

This is my Async Genesis

PS - Thank you to Async and The Guild for this opportunity to be a part of such an awesome platform.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: “Untitled #3”, from “Slits in Depth” series (2020/ 2022)
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
“Untitled #3” is part of the series of 3D stereographic photo collages “Slits in Depth”, by Pedro Victor Brandão, that since 2020 is being minted on async.art as dynamic compositions that alternate interior and exterior spaces in impossible perspectives, leveraged by the programmable features of the platform.

Created in the third pandemic year, this work was commissioned by Pivô for the exhibition "Guided tour", curated by the curatorial platform aarea (founded by Livia Benedetti and Marcela Vieira). "Guided tour'' is the edition #4 of Pivô Satélite program. In addition to Pedro Victor Brandão, artists Gabriel Junqueira, Júlia Rocha and Gabriel Massan also participate in the project. The artists were invited to create correspondences between Pivô's digital space and its exhibition space in the Copan Building, located in São Paulo.

The composition “Untitled #3” is made up of a frontal element together with two other images: an Adiantum twig photographed in front of a mirror; and two backgrounds: a cloudy sky and an interior environment of one of Pivô's galleries. During the 24 hours of the day, one background is gradually replaced by another. When viewed with red and cyan anaglyph glasses (red lens on the left eye), elements pop off the screen.

During the exhibition period of the work on Pivô's website (March 23rd to April 24th, 2022), visitors can sign a document with their non-custodial wallet to enter the giveaway of the work.

Pivô Satélite can be accessed at https://www.pivo.org.br/en/satellite/

“Sem Título #3” faz parte da série de fotocolagens estereográficas 3D “Cortes em Profundidade", de Pedro Victor Brandão, que desde 2020 tem sido emitida no async.art como composições dinâmicas que alternam espaços interiores e exteriores em perspectivas impossíveis a partir das funcionalidades programáveis da plataforma. 

Criado já no terceiro ano pandêmico, este trabalho foi comissionado pelo Pivô para a exposição "Visita guiada", curada pela plataforma curatorial aarea (fundada por Livia Benedetti e Marcela Vieira). "Visita guiada" é a edição #4 do programa Pivô Satélite. Além de Pedro Victor Brandão, participam também do projeto xs artistas Gabriel Junqueira, Júlia Rocha e Gabriel Massan. Xs artistas foram convidadxs a criar correspondências entre o espaço digital do Pivô e seu espaço expositivo no Edifício Copan, localizado em São Paulo. 

A composição de “Sem Título #3” é feita de um elemento frontal junto a duas outras imagens: um galho de avenca fotografado em frente a um espelho; e dois fundos: um céu nebuloso e um ambiente interno de uma das galerias do Pivô. Durante as 24 horas do dia, um fundo é gradualmente substituído por outro. Quando vistos com um óculos anáglifo vermelho e ciano (lente vermelha no olho esquerdo), os elementos saltam da tela. 

Durante o período de exibição do trabalho no website do Pivô (23 de março a 24 de abril de 2022), visitantes podem assinar um documento com sua carteira não-custodial para concorrer ao sorteio do trabalho.

Pivô Satélite pode ser acessado em https://www.pivo.org.br/satelite/

Pedro Victor Brandão
MAR 2022

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Riflessa
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Riflessa is the genesis programmable Art NFT by Italian artist Francesca Fini. In this work she recreates and re-prototypes in 3D the Art lamps conceived in the 70s by her father designer, and produced in limited edition by the visionary Italian company New Lamp. A few very rare examples of these Art lamps / light sculptures, now out of production and almost all lost, have recently become collector's items in the modernism market, and sold for tens of thousands of dollars by Christie's and other major auction houses.
This project, animated by the artist’s desire to celebrate the genius of her father, digitally brings back to life a lost piece of Italian design from one of the most innovative and brilliant periods in recent history.

Riflessa
by Gianfranco Fini
New Lamp, 1970

A luminous panel in stainless steel with white lacquered metal. The steel cubes are magnetic and can be interactively re-arranged to create infinite light patterns. This was originally a very large wall lamp, measuring 81 x 81 x 10 cm. The piece is featured in Luce lampade 1968-1973: il nuovo design italiano, Fulvio Ferrari e Napoleone Ferrari, Allemandi Editore.

The collector of this NFT will receive as a reward a hand-drawn sketch of the lamp signed by Gianfranco Fini.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Though I witnessed glamorous moments, faces and looks as a press photographer, I realized that I was drawn to create this world from a different perspective; one which undressed the soul, and rendered a more authentic moment. After some time, it became the same scenes, the same clichés, the same smiles, the same looks and the same photographers. As a celebrity, having to see more than 30 flashes per second every time a photographer spots them, probably makes them want to protect themselves. Seeing celebrities live in this world of excessive media coverage, I started to develop a mixed feeling of admiration and respect, but also pity, and finally detachment.

The Personalities are decomposed and re-assembled in an abstract composition, guided by my instinct and fed by what the model inspired in me.

The original digital size of "La fureteuse" portrait is 180 by 120 cm. 

This is a portrait of the entrepreneur, Angela Simmons. 
If you set it on "sunrise", it will display the original photography.
