"Intentions are mental states in which the agent commits themselves to a course of action. Having the plan to visit the zoo tomorrow is an example of an intention. The action plan is the content of the intention while the commitment is the attitude towards this content. Other mental states can have action plans as their content, as when one admires a plan, but differ from intentions since they do not involve a practical commitment to realizing this plan. Successful intentions bring about the intended course of action while unsuccessful intentions fail to do so. Intentions, like many other mental states, have intentionality: they represent possible states of affairs." ---Wikipedia

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Proof of Concept
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Proof of Concept contains a small square that can move to 19,522 locations using only two layers.

Dynamic non-fungible tokens of our time are still very much in their infancy. We are plagued with high transaction fees, smothered in centralization and limited in our technology. Our blockchain is off-chain. Those who can code thrive, while those who cannot are banished, alongside the ideas they will never be able to create. There are glimmers of hope though. A few individuals and entities have began sharing tools amongst the less knowledgeable, providing years of experience within what feels like days. This is life changing for a lot of us.

Proof of Concept has dimensions of 1920x1080 pixels. The grid space is 1880x1040 pixels, with each individual grid representing 10x10 pixels in width and height. This leaves 188x104 grids that the square can move to, which equates to 19,522 individual locations. 

The three layers available in this artwork are: X-Axis, Y-Axis and Color. The X-Axis controls the x position of the square, while the Y-Axis controls the y position of the square. The Color controls the color of the square. There are two colors to choose from: gold and black. Gold is slightly special as it behaves like a gradient, changing brightness depending on the x position of the square.

It's worth noting that with an additional 2708 states (1732+976) added to the X-Axis and Y-Axis layers of this artwork, all 2,073,600 locations could have been available for the square to move to (assuming each individual grid had a dimension of one pixel). This was purposely not included. A few of these locations would move the square off the artwork, minor x and y changes would be unnoticeable and individual grid spaces would be impossible to distinguish from one another. It's also worth noting that with an additional two layers, and 768 states, all 16,777,216 colors of the RGB Color Model could have been available to choose from for the square. This was purposely not included as well.

Proof of Concept was created to answer one simple question: "Given the knowledge and tools available to me at this current time, can I move a square around an artwork without limitation on how many locations it can move to?". 

The concept has been proven. It is possible.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Newly Abridged Happiness Manual Vol 1
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Conceived as a series with three volumes, the Newly Abridged Happiness Manuals are conceptual poems that explore the tension between time and mind, between what we tell ourselves and what our minds tell us. 

This first volume digs at our relationship to the present tense. The second and third volumes will probe our notions of past and future, worn down as they become with the passage of time, hour by waking or sleeping hour. 

Life happens inside our minds. To examine thought is to examine atomized bites of life. These series of poems seek to do so with humor, compassion, and straightforward honesty. 

Alternate titles for this series included: Present Tense, Past Tense, Future Tense. Or, Sketches of Singing and Failing.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: What time is it in Antarctica ?
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: Antarctica has six months of daylight and six months of darkness. The two pictures that makes this piece were taken 6 months apart in the same location in the Weddell sea. One in summer, when ice as it melts relentlessly reflects the light of a sun, and one in winter, when ice  as it builds up consistently reflects the light of the moon. This NFT thus freezes a year long cycle within a 24-hour rhythm. Every lines of longitude run through the south pole, meaning Antarctica is theoretically located in all time zones at once: How long will this cycle be allowed to carry on? What time is it in Antarctica.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: 15 minutes
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
antwoman makes a tribute to one of the most esteemed and important artists of the 20th century - Andy Warhol.
His art was playful and fun. He was not afraid to experiment and did not address what the critics said. Why do only one painting if you can do several, each in different colors?! this piece celebrates this approach because I think in art it is important to try and play. That's how you get to the really interesting things. 
He was fascinated by advertising and celebrities & by the idea of people as brands or consumer products. What's happening now really reflects his vision. We are all consumer products in some way and we all have our 15 minutes of fame.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Moth to a Flame
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This unique piece is very important to me. 

The reason for this is that it tells how two lovers, who can never be separated from each other, take care of and protect each other despite their fate. Just like twins, they are shields of each other. 

Life tries to devalue us for the sake of testing us. However, fortunately, there is always someone who sees our true worth. At this point, what we have to do is to protect that love and to cherish it, just like the crown placed on our head, which we are obliged to carry. After all, what makes us who we are is the meaning of our lives. The meaning of life is this power that feeds us.

With my endless respect and love for all the effort he put into making me who I am...

Mitra

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Mariupol
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
1937. As Spain War was at its apogee, Franco with his Nazi allies bombed civilians for the first time in the city of Guernica.

85 years later. As we could not imagine the comeback of a war at our borders; we see soldiers engaging in a war by bombing Mariupol, Kyiv and other cities, and millions of civilians are on the run, scattered over Europe away from their home they might never see again. 

Because of the Emergency of the Situation, 38 artists decided to create a massive collaboration within 3 weeks. 

'Mariupol' will be displayed during the Non-Fungible Conference on a giant screen wall. This will take place in Lisbon, Portugal in April 4-5 2022 and is created under the supervision of The Guild.

There is an emergency in Ukraine now, but more generally, the XXI Century seems to redefine the war as a new normal. Nobody can accept this in Ukraine or any other country, we need to do something, we need to act here and now!

All the funds and royalties will go to “Voices of  Children” to bring psychological support to child victims of war.


Artists Involved: 

Rutger van der Tas, 0xMJ, Shinji Akhirah, Jetski, Ytje Veenstra, ROBNESS, Skeenee, Mightymoose, jivinci, crashblossom, oficinastk, orabel, Jæn, emmavauloup, Shortcut, 8thproject, Louis16art, fabianospeziari, XERAK, abysms, carlasafe, Nino Arteiro, Magusz, dasNeves, BOOYASAN, Airco Caravan, GertJanAkerboom, LUVRworldwide, Marcotic, Niels Broszat, Tom Abbink, ejthek, Pule the dr, Sparrow, Miss al simpson, Angie Taylor, Agoria, Teto.



Supervision: The Guild: Rutger van der Tas, 0xMJ

Curators: John Karp, Benoit Couty and The Guild

Initiated by John Karp

First Exhibition : Non-Fungible Conference, Lisbon, Portugal

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The "Vesica Piscis" is the lenticular intersection of the two circles. In sacred geometry it symbolizes the beginning of creation as well as the portal between two dimensions. This symbol has been used in various cultures and it connects us to something primordial and pure. Many other geometries and proportions can be derived from this elemental shape. 

The two stages of this piece show the 4D view (orange) associated with the ethereal and subtle energies, and the 5D view (blue) associated with the astral realm.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Newly Abridged Happiness Manual, Vol I
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Conceived as a series with three volumes, the Newly Abridged Happiness Manuals are conceptual poems that explore the tension between time and mind, between what we tell ourselves and what our minds tell us. How to construct a sense of self when our senses are constantly under assault? Our minds jump from thought to thought–which thought should we act upon?

Life happens inside our minds, and our emotional realities are underpinned by thought. To examine the dynamic of thought is to examine the scaffolding that sustains our outward-facing selves. This series does so with humor, compassion, and straightforward honesty.

The first volume focuses on the way we experience the present tense, at times mundane, at others philosophical. The second and third volumes will probe our notions of past and future, worn down as they become by the passage of time, hour by waking–or, even, sleeping–hour.

This series expands on Caballero's exploration of the cyclical storytelling potential of Async's 24 hour canvas. Collectors of the piece will also receive a minted GIF version of the poem in which the 24 frames/verses of the text change every few seconds. Do our thoughts change from hour to hour, second to second, day to day? Or are we forever reliving the same thoughts, and thus, the same day?

Debuted at the Digital Francisco Carolinum in April 2022.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Logos
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Logos is the second programmable Art NFT by Italian artist Francesca Fini.
In this works she recreates and re-prototypes in 3D the Art lamps conceived in the 70s by her father designer, and produced in limited edition by the visionary Italian company New Lamp. A few very rare examples of these Art lamps / light sculptures, now out of production, have recently become collector's items in the modernism market, and sold for tens of thousands of dollars at Christie's and other major auction houses.
This project, animated by the artist’s desire to celebrate the genius of her father, digitally brings back to life a lost piece of Italian design from one of the most innovative and brilliant periods in recent history.

Logos
by Gianfranco Fini
New Lamp, 1971

​This Art lamp was made of polymer semi-transparent parallelepipeds of various sizes, resting on a chromium-plated steel base measuring 30 x 30 cm. The base had a luminous inner side creating interesting optical effects. The piece is featured in Luce lampade 1968-1973: il nuovo design italiano, Fulvio Ferrari e Napoleone Ferrari, Allemandi Editore.

The collector of this NFT will receive as a reward a hand-drawn sketch of the lamp signed by Gianfranco Fini.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Sedative | Blue Prints | 24
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
W a t e r | L i g h t | S o u n d | revealing sacred geometry - Cymatics - The study of vibration

By resonating frequencies inside a small dish full of water, we see the geometric shapes created by chaos eventfully finding balance. Images taken from frequencies 24hz being resonating inside a speaker within a small 1inch pan -  with light shining above in a ring shape. This allows us to see 3d geometry in the reflection of the water on the surface. By filming the process at 1/30 shutter speed 50fps, we allow more light to travel when capturing the visuals. In this piece there are 24 images taken from [ 24 second clip] of sound being resonated. Each frame represents O N E  H O U R  of time in the day as if it were seconds, although this is generous as we are fortunate enough to extend just one moment of perfect synchrony in Cymatics. 

Process on Cymatics | https://hic.af/o/715440

These are the blue prints for Sedative 1/1 [HEN] resonated at 24hz | 24secs | 24frames
10|04|2022

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: "In Between" - New York City Collection - Yellow
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
My photographs reflect how a split second and a slight tilt of the camera changes the entire story, which will never be written again. Positioning myself between the visible and unseen moves me.

When you live in a city, storefronts are a big part of life, and on top of that, I love everything about fashion. The storefronts display many sides of what it could be. I let my eyes travel inside the juxtaposed layers of possibilities, and my curiosity takes over to find something familiar yet surprising. Once I find that I hide between the reflected and the real life. Life is daring yet fragile, wild yet vulnerable, puzzled yet simple, content yet melancholic, and always in between. 

These photographs are part of my "In Between" series, taken in New York City the last winter. There are two images of the same scene taken from a different angles changing every hour.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Circle that rotates forever

Day and night appear at the same time. Suffering from a twisted, infinite cycle of pain. It's the struggle of willpower and its own contradictions, or even just creating a fairy tale.
In the silent rhythm of the universe database, we should learn the basic forces of nature, those primitive concepts, and those lowest levels of will objectivity.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: MARTYRIUM
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"Martyrium" is a 24 hour journey of personal purgatorial visions. 
Thinking about the Aristotelian Metaphysics and Ethics. 
The rediscovery of these works in the middle ages by the scholastic philosophers shaped the assumptions and beliefs of what lies beyond.

"Martyrium" updates four times a day.
"The Fall" brings "The Punishment".
"The Punishment" leads to "Repentance".
And finally "Deliverance", a direct reference to "The Creation of Adam" by Michelangelo di Lodovico Buonarroti Simoni.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Memorial
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Death is inevitable when the movement stops... frozen in time, immovable and eternal.


This unique artwork is my genesis collection on Async.Art and it's a meditation on my own death. 
In 24 hours we can see as the sculpture assembles during the performance.

This performance  symbolizes the retrospect of our life.
During the movement I leave a body imprint on approximately every 5th frame of the animation. When the movement stops, there is an abstract/surrealistic sculpture. 
The different motion paths are analogies of rails that are sometimes laid before us but sometimes we see them only after we have walked them. 

My greatest inspiration concerning forms and shape language is HR Giger, creator of the Alien creature. Analyzing his work and the Process Philosophy I have developed a technique of the Process Sculptures.
I sculpt the models and use my own motion capture performance. 

Meditate on this unique artwork and own it before I reveal my lifelong Art program.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: In a Different Light
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
In my opinion, there's just something magical about the texture created by a paintbrush. All those tiny bristles wound so tightly together, creating countless parallel lines in every stroke. Often times, this detail is absent from modern artworks, mainly due to the adoption and embracing of digital art. "In a Different Light" is, essentially, the same two images, each with four different light effects applied. 

As an artist, I find myself simply playing with color more often than anything else. Creating gradients and hombres that are visually striking makes me feel all warm and fuzzy inside. These are four of my favorites set to rotate through in sync with the time of day/night. 

Enjoy

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Scenes From a Dream of the Great Cosmic Turtle
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Presented here are 12 scenes from the dream of the Great Cosmic Turtle. This dream placed a such a disconcerting sense of discomfort and anxiety within the heart and mind of the Great Cosmic Turtle that it eventually led to the Great Cosmic Turtle's abandonment of humanity.

Each scene is presented twice over each 24 hours (in the same way that a 12 hour clock display shows each of the 12 hours twice within each 24 hours).

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Les plaisantes
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Though I witnessed glamorous moments, faces and looks as a press photographer, I realized that I was drawn to create this world from a different perspective; one which undressed the soul, and rendered a more authentic moment. After some time, it became the same scenes, the same clichés, the same smiles, the same looks and the same photographers. As a celebrity, having to see more than 30 flashes per second every time a photographer spots them, probably makes them want to protect themselves. Seeing celebrities live in this world of excessive media coverage, I started to develop a mixed feeling of admiration and respect, but also pity, and finally detachment.


The Personalities are decomposed and re-assembled in an abstract composition, guided by my instinct and fed by what the model inspired in me.


The original digital size of "Les plaisantes" portrait is 120 by 180 cm.


This is a portrait of the actor Jesse Tyler Ferguson & the actress Anna Chlumsky. 
If you set it on "sunrise", it will display the original photography.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Subtractive Reality
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Subtractive Reality, 2022
Original Edition, 1 of 1
Dynamic Art
1920x1080

Subtractive Reality is based on my original artwork 'Entangled Reality'. Released as part of my series: ONE - a contemplative journey into the unseen world around us.

Using a minimal amount of colors and a precise juxtaposition of shapes, each piece challenges the intricate ways in which the human eye perceives. The collection is inspired by the ephemeral and intangible moments of life: unspoken words and feelings that can't be encapsulated in a singular understanding.

Rather than replacing parts of the art, Subtractive Reality invites layer owners to collaborate and subtract layers from the piece itself, creating new and vibrant optical illusions. Any changes to the original piece will also be influenced by the previously inexistent background and controller, resulting in thousands of possible outcomes.

anthonyesebag.com

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"Your reason and your passion are the rudder and the sails of your seafaring soul.
If either your sails or your rudder be broken, you can but toss and drift, or else be held at a standstill in mid-seas.
For reason, ruling alone, is a force confining and passion, unattended, is a flame that burns to its own destruction.
Therefore let your soul exalt your reason to the height of passion, that it may sing;
And let it direct your passion with reason, that your passion may live through its own daily resurrection and like the phoenix rise above its own ashes."
---from On Reason and Passion (The Prophet) by Khalil Gibran

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: La croque-mitaine
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Though I witnessed glamorous moments, faces and looks as a press photographer, I realized that I was drawn to create this world from a different perspective; one which undressed the soul, and rendered a more authentic moment. After some time, it became the same scenes, the same clichés, the same smiles, the same looks and the same photographers. As a celebrity, having to see more than 30 flashes per second every time a photographer spots them, probably makes them want to protect themselves. Seeing celebrities live in this world of excessive media coverage, I started to develop a mixed feeling of admiration and respect, but also pity, and finally detachment.


The Personalities are decomposed and re-assembled in an abstract composition, guided by my instinct and fed by what the model inspired in me.


The original digital size of the portrait is 80 by 160 cm.


This is a portrait of the American model, Alexandra Richards.
If you set it on "sunrise", it will display the original photography.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Kids Takeover Putin: Abstract #1
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Based on Putin photography, Kids Takeover Putin is text-to-image experimentation on war, peace and leadership. It is re-creating the leadership in the eyes of a kid takeover for peace.

Stop the War. We hoped, I hoped this was already the past in Europe. We should not go back.

There is a lot of interesting material that range from childish and peaceful to satirical and dark. I will post them and perhaps I will post most of them hoping this ends as soon as possible.

This is one of the 2 4-piece somewhat abstract pieces on Async Art. There is also 1 24 piece set and 12 2-piece Nova Apartchiks on Async Art. For multi editions and some other 1/1s, please visit my collection on KnownOrigin.

by Mad Monk, 1/1 on Async Art, 2022

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Fractals 042 + 021 | Gravity
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The balance between the two forms represented in the day state refers to the attraction of gravity, this omnipresent force from which all life is organizing itself on earth. 
The night state deals with the force of gravity. The colored rings converge in the same direction like gravitational fields, simultaneously defining a top and a bottom, a depth and a space.
Sunrise state is very abstract. It has a particularly rich and complex texture. Its rendering is of a monochromatic gray while it is composed of a multitude of saturated colors. It looks like waves emanating from a very distant center or converging in an abyss.
Sunset set evokes the complexity of the fluids that continuously interact around us. Winds, tides, but also all sorts of invisible forces like gravity or magnetic fields.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Euphoria
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Euphoria was born in 2087. A golden child. Being fascinated by Ethereum from a young age, she grew up to become an excavator, looking for hidden messages within the blockchain. There was a time when on-chain messaging was unnecessary and inefficient compared to centralized services. Most messages Euphoria came across were meaningless, until one day she stumbled upon a message embedded in block 14276155. The message read “In the future, things will be”. Feeling excited, she investigated further. To her surprise she found multiple messages within the same Ethereum address, in some sort of formation. 

To read about her discovery, please visit: https://www.bottlesartwork.com/pagetwo

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Newly Abridged Happiness Manual, Vol I
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Newly Abridged Happiness Manual, Vol I is a conceptual poem that explores the tension between time and mind, between what we tell ourselves and what our minds tell us. How to construct a sense of self when our senses are constantly under assault?

This work expands on Caballero’s exploration of the storytelling potential of Async’s 24 hour canvas. The collector of the piece will also receive an airdropped video version of the poem in which the 24 frames/verses of the text change every few seconds. 

Do our thoughts change from hour to hour, day to day? Or, are we trapped by the same thoughts, and, thus, essentially reliving a single day?

Debuted at the Digital Francisco Carolinum in April 2022.

--

Newly Abridged Happiness Manual, Vol I

what comes first
the word or the image
in the kitchen the scent of thawed meat
prefaces the raw sweat of noon
where I reside it smolders
despite the promise of shade
I resolve it's senseless to worry
the pink muscle of mind
draws me nowhere closer 
tomorrow
charts an unreal circle
why must I choose
between language or bread
the moral of the story is to want less
panoramic thoughts
like everything that eats time
if habitual will inhabit my day
meanwhile simple is not simplistic
strings stretched in separate ways
a wonderful day
is conceived
produced like chilled fruit
the moral of the story is to want more
every waking hour

VIDEO
Details: Music video for The Wake complete with lyrics for songs that have vocals! Mixture of live footage, animations, drawings, and all sorts of eccentricities. 
Format: MOV
File Size: 9.06 GB
Dimensions: 3840x2160
Length: 23:07

-
Upon purchase I'll send the physical in the mail!
Contact me upon purchase and we'll get it setup!
The songs & video I will send via email/cloud storage!
-

Little about the piece:
I started working on the album cover after I created a couple songs that would eventually turn into the first tracks of The Wake. It was a lot of fun putting together the songs then listening to the latest mix while working on the drawing. I'd take mental notes of what I wanted to change so when I would hit a wall with the drawing I'd switch to music. Going in I knew that I wanted to have a casket, some trees, water, use only a couple of colors, and for the first time draw something larger than a piece of paper! The album I made before The Wake is called Death and I wanted this to be a sendoff of sorts so that train of thought led me to create a type of portal where the casket was heading. The vines kind of just happened and the water I wanted to have this unnatural swirliness to them. The part that took the longest was all the lines in the trees but it was sort of peaceful drawing all of them! 

On average I tend to release an album every 2 years and I thought this was a perfect halfway point before I start working on my next music project to release somewhat of an *ABSOLUTE EDITION* of The Wake. I can't think of a better way to enjoy the album.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Planet Earth
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Planet Earth, my home, my place
A capricious anomaly, in the sea of space
Planet Earth, are you just
Floating by, a cloud of dust
A minor globe, about to bust
A piece of metal bound to rust
A speck of matter in a mindless void
A lonely spaceship, a large asteroid

Cold as a rock without a hue
Held together with a bit of glue
Something tells me this isn't true
You are my sweetheart, soft and blue
Do you care, have you a part
In the deepest emotions of my own heart
Tender with breezes, caressing and whole
Alive with music, haunting my soul

In my veins I've felt the mystery
Of corridors of time, books of history
Life songs of ages throbbing in my blood
Have danced to the rhythm of the tide and flood
Your misty clouds, your electric storm
Were turbulent tempests in my own form

I've licked the salt, the bitter, the sweet
Of every encounter, of passion, of heat
Your riotous color, your fragrance, your taste
Have thrilled my senses beyond all haste

In your beauty I've known the how
Of timeless bliss, this moment of now

Planet Earth, are you just
Floating by, a cloud of dust
A minor globe, about to bust
A piece of metal bound to rust
A speck of matter in a mindless void
A lonely spaceship, a large asteroid

Cold as a rock without a hue
Held together with a bit of glue
Something tells me this isn't true
You are my sweetheart, gentle and blue
Do you care, have you a part
In the deepest emotions of my own heart
Tender with breezes, caressing and whole
Alive with music, haunting my soul

Planet Earth, gentle and blue
With all my heart, I love you

(MJ - 1995)

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Newly Abridged Happiness Manual, Vol I
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Newly Abridged Happiness Manual, Vol I is a conceptual poem that explores the tension between time and mind, between what we tell ourselves and what our thoughts tell us. 

Our emotional states are underpinned by the unspoken words that traverse our minds as thought. To examine these words is to examine the intimate scaffolding that sustains our outward-facing selves. This poem does so with humor, compassion, and straightforward honesty, highlighting both the mundane and contradictory nature of thought. 

Consisting of twenty-four short verses, each of which is displayed independently on a frame for sixty minutes, this piece takes advantage of Async Art’s 24hour canvas to explore the evolution–or lack thereof–of thought along the vast axis of time. Sloganeering statements of self-improvement and assertive grasps for the transcendental interrupt expressions of routine, of place, of physicality. In one breath, we conceive of an ideal tomorrow, in the next we abruptly reach for a peach. How to construct a meaningful sense of self when our senses are constantly under assault?

This artwork functions as a diptych–its collector will receive an airdropped video version in which the same twenty-four frames rotate in under a minute. The slow and fast versions of the poem work together to show how our thoughts cycle and recycle from second to second, hour to hour, moment to moment. 

By rethinking the same thoughts, are we essentially reliving a single day?

Debuted at the Digital Francisco Carolinum in April 2022.

--

Newly Abridged Happiness Manual, Vol I

what comes first 
the word or the image 
in the kitchen the scent of thawed meat 
prefaces the raw sweat of noon 
where I reside it smolders 
despite the promise of shade 
I resolve it's senseless to worry 
the pink muscle of mind 
draws me nowhere closer 
tomorrow 
charts an unreal circle 
why must I choose 
between language or bread 
the moral of the story is to want less 
panoramic thoughts 
like everything that eats time 
if habitual inhabit my day 
though simple and simplistic 
wrench me with separate strings 
a wonderful day 
is conceived 
produced like chilled fruit 
the moral of the story is to want more 
every waking hour

4 pieces minted as 1/1 on Async Art

Conceptualized, Created and Minted 2022

...

Milosnitse are demons of plague, known in all Slavic countries. Their name in English would be merciful ones and Slavs called them like that, because they wanted to appease them and to avoid plague that they bring. They are represented as women in black and they walked in groups, rarely alone. Amount of Milosnitse was measured by amount of sicknesses that they brought. There was no cure from them, but there was a way to appease them and to eventually avoid their plagues. People could light fires on crossroads and on village's entrance and they could share food and drink and even sing before fire.

https://mythus.fandom.com/wiki/List_of_Slavic_creatures#Milosnitse

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Retro Fortuna
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The artworks are multi-layered spatiotemporal mappings of Istanbul which are filtered through conflicting emotions about now, the past and the future. Unique identities, personal backgrounds, everyday habits and future expectations of absolute strangers get entangled in our dense urban settings and create a state of flux which changes us in profound ways.

As time passes and the future unfolds, our memories and identities transform. Each twenty four hour cycle adds to you and subtracts from you.

Daylight and darkness and all that lie in between cast their colours upon you. You're a canvas, painted over and over.

A never ending work in progress, a state of becoming which never ends.

Until the very end.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Monsters & Mythology: Vodenjak by Mad Monk

4 pieces minted as 1/1 on Async Art

Conceptualized, Created and Minted 2022

...

Vodenjak (Vodenyak or Vodyanoy) is creature from Eastern and Western Slavic stories that lives in water, especially close to watermills. They are created from souls of drowned people, especially ones that didn't meet funerary rites. Some people believed that Vodenjak is soul of very evil human that is punished by Gods to live in water. It is represented as human with long claws and tail, covered in moss or grass, or as old man with green beard and hair or as fish covered in mud. During day, he rests in decorated lair, while at night he pulls down unlucky people down into water, especially married men, so they can steal their women and make them into servants. He often damages watermills, bridges and fishing nets. People appeased Vodenjak by throwing rooster, chicken or sheep. Sometimes, people sacrificed and well-fed horse by throwing into water with stone tied to their neck.

https://mythus.fandom.com/wiki/List_of_Slavic_creatures#Vodenjak

Zmaj (Zmaj or Dragon) is known in almost all World's cultures. However Zmaj in Slavic folklore is represented as rather benign creature, created from certain animals which lived up to 30 or 100 years (rooster, carp, horse, ox, ram or dog). It always had either one or even number of heads and traits from animal that it borrowed. It fought against Azhdaya and it was invisible to everybody, except to woman whom he falls in love. Relationship between Zmaj and human women could bring zmajevite children (Dragonborn children) and they differed from humans by having large head or eyes and tiny wings under their armpits.

https://mythus.fandom.com/wiki/List_of_Slavic_creatures#Zmaj

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Turris Avium
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The Tower of Birds has a story unlike any other...

Turris Vallis was known not for its beautiful valley of towers but, unfortunately, for its swarms of irritating birds that pooped on all the rooftops. Which caused a horrid smell. No one could do a thing about it. Not kings. Not emperors. Not queens. Not even skilled marksmen. Until one day a sorcerer arrived. He was on the edge of this world—almost passing into the next. He hadn’t wanted to travel through Turris Vallis, but there was no other option. While he lodged in the city he became infuriated with the birds. So, he cursed them and the city they flew around. As he uttered the magic words he breathed his last and passed into the next dimension. And the birds got sucked into the turret roofs, where they were doomed to squawk and squabble for the rest of eternity. You may think the city traded one terrible thing for another. But this was not entirely true. The sorcerer gave the city reprise at night. The birds would disappear. And be followed by an unearthly silence that allowed the townsfolk peaceful sleep and pleasant dreams.

This NFT changes how it looks based on the time of day. It has a different image for day, night, sunrise, and sunset.
Size: 2160 × 3840px.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Soliloquy
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
As I continue to wonder what the future holds for me, I find myself speaking more to myself. Planning, strategizing, and hoping. Mixed with anxiety and worry. I wonder who else has such thoughts. Who else is wondering if they will ever make it in this life?
I paint my most recent feelings in this piece, hoping others will be able to relate and maybe draw strength from the realization that they are not alone.
'Soliloquy' is the story of a black man who is deep in thoughts about his life.

This piece began as a photograph of my street. Then photographs of Adire which is symbolic and crucial to representing my culture in my artworks. Next, I paint the stars and the male figure in my usual workflow, thereby creating a balance between the painted foreground and the photographed background.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Spiritual Connection
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: We are all one and the same, one of many, many of one, one of many, many as one. That is what defines life. That is what defines the bond, the connection between each of us, no matter what form we are, no matter what being we are, no matter where we are from, no matter when we are from. The Spiritual Connection embodies spiritually inspired art resulting from a look within and outward across and beyond the multiverse that can lead us to realize that we are part of the same, infinite consciousness; a realization that can surpass any of our individual or collective insecurities to reach and appreciate a sense of love, peace, and harmony.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: SUNSET & HUMAN
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
''We are one kind
None of us is different much than another
We are human, ruling this planet 
Sometimes worse, sometimes better
What we see is an illusion
Presented by light
Only requires a different angle 
To realize we are in a stupid fight''

It's almost a pleasure to observe the relation between humankind and sunset. I wonder; how come the majority of humankind didn't insist to worship the Sun?
I mean not only us, all life depends on Sun light but remember those moments when you watched sunset, those awe moments. It's something else right?... 

I took lots of sunset photographs in so many different locations for years.
Most of the times I was not alone in those places. And I was fortuned enough to see different people from different lives come together without any judgement, in a peaceful and welcoming mood.

We inhabit this planet with billions of unique minds. Some anxious, some cool, some curious, some fool...
It's possible to see our fingerprints in almost all the good and bad things. We are ruling this. No doubt. We covered such distance since the beginning of our evolution. Congrats to us but somehow we still can't leave some of our stupid bad habits. 
Not a coincidence though, we are fighting each other since beginning. Such a dumb thing but we can't get over it. 

The peaceful, awesome mood of sunsets and silhouette technique helped me to visualize human as a species without sub-characteristics to create this fine art photography collection. We are 'one' kind with many shades. 


''We came from the oceans...
For the sake of the sunlight..''

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Who Are You?
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Who Are You? is a pop art homage to the famous Magritte's painting The Man In A Bowler Hat.

It further explores the unbreakable connection between what is hidden and what is visible within the context of modern lifestyle and crypto art culture.

Each layer gives the freedom to the collector to choose which narrative will be displayed and thus make decisions that shape the artistic creation.

Every next level of your life will demand a different you. Level up.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Different Pages of My Room
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Sometimes two's a crowd
Sometimes you need more space
Sometimes you might need love in a different kind of way
I want to be your best friend every day
I want to be the one you love
I want to be your confidant
I wanna be the one you trust and care for
I want to be the one that fills your mind with something new
I want to be the one you hold on tight
I want to be the one that you'd run to at night
I want to be the one you never let go of
I want to be the one who understands what you need
I want to be the one who brings out the best in you

But I also wanna be the one who loves you.
For now, I just enjoy the intimacy.


This piece began as a photograph of my room. Then I added photographs of Adire which are symbolic and crucial to representing my culture in my artworks. Next, I paint the flowers and the human figures in my usual workflow, thereby creating a balance between the painted foreground and the photographed background.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Nature of Impostor Syndrome
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
It doesn't matter how long you've been here. It will happen. Your face will float in this space, with many others, trying not to be devoured by whales or scammers, enduring pointing fingers, scrutinizing eyes, complacent or prickly comments... Doing everything possible to keep that creative magic alive. 

And many times, for a while, you will fail. The tongues and fingers and eyes, oftentimes your own, will overwhelm you and you'll cower in fear and self-doubt.

But eventually you will grow the wings you were told were impossible, and learn to fly. Many times you will feel that you do not deserve the flight, and that the wings do not belong to you. But the more you use them, the more familiar they will become.

You will use many masks, but remember that they are not you- they do not even belong to you, and they will fall off sooner or later. Keep enough of them to perform your act, but not too many, so that everyone can recognize you.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Doomsday Romance

Facts are solid, emotions transient... all through the day... within a second it all turns on its head... where can I find the answers? 0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: md3c is a programmable art piece that updates every hour of the day. It is a picture book represented in a cuckoo clock with unfolding scenes inspired by feelings and thoughts upon entering into a space of discovery! Experiencing moments of unfamiliarity, misunderstandings, and misinterpretations of the ego mind. Never feeling rushed, but instead like it was meant to be. Bend matter! Stop physical time! Seeking to create a place at the pace of the heArt of an artist and not the machine! What could be made? How would the world look? How could things -beee ee e e !

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: #381.7063.365 | Harmony of Illusion
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: "Harmony of Illusion" is a series of digital paintings that explore the relationship between AI and human vision. The pieces are based on the idea that there is a similarity of harmony between the two modes of seeing. By juxtaposition elements that are usually considered to be opposites (e.g. organic vs. inorganic, natural vs. artificial), hope to generate visions that provoke a sense of chaos and reflectiveness about the nature.

All things and circumstances around us keep changing with time. That's what is portrayed in this Art, with different backgrounds and textures. The wheel of time has the design of a geometric Mandala. The shape of the wheel changes Algorithmically every hour, along with its background. Shadows of the Daytime versions, 6 am to 6 pm, have their shadows change as per the location of the Sun. Enjoy! Cherish your time! There is something that doesn't change. What is that?

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Student Debt Collector
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
€ 737.163,10, is the total student debt of 25 art students who are graduating this year.

One has to take a loan for student housing.
The other for tuition fees, and the cost for groceries, books and living expenses.
We haven’t even touched on the expenses regarding healthcare and public transport.
This all combined makes up our student debt. Every student carries enormous debts on their shoulders.
Usually, this debt is invisible but with this artwork it is for the public to see and experience. 

Summary
Student debt is a major problem in many countries, such as the Netherlands. Due to these financial debts, we and many others have several problems, such as mental health, psychological complaints and disadvantages of applying for a mortgage. 

The Student Debt Collector represents 25 art students with student debts. We want to make this major invincible problem visible with this NFT. We are almost graduated and ready for the next step. However, we start our career and work-life with a combined debt of € 737.163,10. 

For more details, a comprehensive guide and a better understanding of The Student Debt Collector, please visit: https://thestudentdebtcollector.com/

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Fractures
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Then there was a great silence. First it took minutes, then years. The feeling of defeat was very new, calm and frightening. I was afraid, it was too sweet to be defeated. plus it was boring. If I had the chance to choose a defeat, I would prefer the action one. The defeat of monotony constantly slept. His presence was heavy. I was coming through a dark wrinkle, I thought I'd get used to it. It's like my movements are restricted. I was ashamed of my ears, I was afraid of my eyes. It was tiring to fight with reluctance. I was offended by some songs. some of them bore my pain and I was grateful. I was lost, my life was spent searching for the way. If I could just throw that weight off, I'd be relieved. I was trapped, finally caught up in that feeling. I was without reason. Besides, I was tired. I didn't know the diet that should be given to be happy. I remember when I was very cold. My thoughts had become a prisoner of wishes. The sense of freedom that was rising inside of me was slowly coming. I was expecting this too. My history was a friend of repetition. I couldn't break my mirror of sameness. If I broke one, then I would put another tick on the list. The list was full, I'm still sad.

Artwork Details:
Printable 57x57cm.

Softwares Used:
Photoshop + Illustrator.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: La titanesque
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This is a portrait of Heidi Klum. 

Though I witnessed glamorous moments, faces and looks as a press photographer, I realized that I was drawn to create this world from a different perspective; one which undressed the soul, and rendered a more authentic moment. After some time, it became the same scenes, the same clichés, the same smiles, the same looks and the same photographers. As a celebrity, having to see more than 30 flashes per second every time a photographer spots them, probably makes them want to protect themselves. Seeing celebrities live in this world of excessive media coverage, I started to develop a mixed feeling of admiration and respect, but also pity, and finally detachment.

The Personalities are decomposed and re-assembled in an abstract composition, guided by my instinct and fed by what the model inspired in me.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: SOARIN'
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Who doesn't want to touch the sky?

SOARIN' is an augmented reality art public installation. The base image was taken at a sports complex in North Carolina, and exists on the premises as a large scale photo-mural using polytab mural fabric. 

SOARIN' has two version (Daybreak and Midnight) complete with unique animations. They come to life by scanning the QR Code and locating the image with Adobe Aero, or by finding the image through the augmented reality app "Artivive."

Collectors will have access to full resolution image, uncompressed MP4 file, and their name will be included on the augmented reality layer.

5236 x 5236 px.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: LORD OF COLOURS
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Long time ago, the rainbow was actually a very poor man. So poor that he had no money to buy clothes and wandered the streets naked.
One stormy day, lightning lit up everything, and the naked man thought that the lightning must be very powerful and maybe it could help him solve his problem.
The ray felt very sorry for that man who had also come to him for help, so ray had an idea:
– “I will give you something better than my clothes: the possibility of living here in heaven with me. I will give you seven colors and you could cover your body with them. When my work is done, you will display all your colors in the sky. Men will admire you and fall in love with your beauty. They will love you because they will know that you herald the arrival of the sun.”
And so it was that from then on, the lord of the seven colors began to act in the sky, announcing the end of a storm and how men fell in love with him ever since.

24-hour illustration of a legendary Ukrainian Zmiinyi (Snake) Island located in the Black Sea, (Odesa region).
After being captured by russian invaders during the first few days of the full-scale war, Ukrainian Island was finally deoccupied and is now under the control of Ukrainian military forces. 
Ukrainian flag was installed on the recaptured island on 4th of July 2022.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Celestial Palace
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
From Earth, Saturn appears yellow in color. Its golden hue is a gift given by the sun's reflection on its surrounding clouds. 

But you are enjoying this majestic view from your balcony floating above the clouds in a special part of the world exclusive to a select number of people with the privilege of owning such a spectacular view. Soft friendly pink and lilac clouds from The Hot Pink Planet Gliese 504B in the Virgo Constellation move throughout your balcony floor. Nearly everything is more beautiful through rose colored gases.

This work of art is programmed to automatically update to reflect the current time of day.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
During the day, sunlight shimmers off the dragonfly’s iridescent wings, painting it with ever-changing tones. 
In the night, the full moon’s silvery glow changes it, turns it into a ghost.

Sweet dragonfly, the precious predator,
Flying among the fringes of my world.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
We usually think of love as an intense emotion confined to a specific time and space, but the truth is love goes beyond that.

In the beginning there was nothing ; then 2 dots manifested.

No awareness of the other. Centuries passed, yet they never met. 

Each dot created more dots, generations of dots.

Their realities never collided, until one specific day.

One moment in time that took several millennia to happen.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Mental DNA
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
We believe that alongside a real DNA there exists a mental one. One of the mental DNA’s components is our dreams. They include common dreams that all people share and a small part of dreams that make each person unique, just like that one percent of distinctive genes that make one an individual with unparalleled features.
   A collector or a DAO led by their own mindset randomly combines and selects a sequence of images close to them and has a chance to create various mental DNA paragraphs referring to their own unique ideas and dreams.
   Dreaming is a natural human condition. A human cannot live without dreaming. A true dream is very much like the horizon. Very often it is almost inaccessible, which does not make it less real though. That is why each of us always has an impetus to go on living and creating.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Surreal Storyteller: Dreams and Nightmares of the Master
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
"In the United terminal in Chicago at five on a Friday afternoon
The sky is breaking with rain and wind and all the flights
Are delayed forever. We will never get to where we are going
And there’s no way back to where we’ve been.
The sun and the moon have disappeared to an island far from  anywhere.

Everybody has a heartache — "
---from Everybody Has a Heartache: A Blues by Joy Harjo

...

Surreal Storyteller is stranded in his own stories. He can not get to where he is going as that place is constructed via the story he tells. Lacking the necessary audience, Surreal Storyteller is stuck in a semi-permanent existence of de-construction and re-construction amidst his stories.

...

Surreal Storyteller: Dreams and Nightmares of the Master by Hulki Okan Tabak

I enjoy creating fluid projects that arise from an idea and run for long stretches where I contribute new works. As I've grown to like the combination I use Async Art and KnownOrigin as the primary minting venues for the project.

Special thanks to one of my most admired storytellers Joy as I referenced her poem. I feel a part of her tribe that spans beyond native American land. Much love and admiration..

1/1 minted on Async Art, 2022

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Abeona
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Our sun is about to die. It might happen a thousand years from now, but it might happen tomorrow - we can't risk it. We've waited far too long. 

Abeona has been ready for centuries. She has been our guide, our administrator, our savior, and now she will be our womb - our glorious mother, who will travel a distance unimaginable until ideal conditions for human life are found. Perhaps they never will be, in which case those of us who remain will sleep until the end of the universe itself.

I allow myself a little pride. It was my ancestor who programmed the original iteration of Abeona and my ancestral line that kept up these archives after she became self-aware (and more than capable of improving her own programming beyond anything any human brain could achieve).

It is time.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Emotional "State" of Ai...
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This 24 Image Blueprint Is actually a representation of the "21 Facial Expression" research done by Professor Aleix M. Martinez at Ohio State University back in 2014.

I have a particular interested in this as I have difficulty recognizing basic facial expressions (and emotions) due to ADHD and CPTSD so I found that creating these artworks, and especially using Ai to do so, is extremely interesting and I love the results.

Not being able to regulate my own emotions sometimes means I can go through a lot of these emotions in a single day and being able to express myself through these artworks helps me get closer to understanding these emotions and myself.

Its a life long journey and one I am happy to be taking (although it gets a bit rough sometimes, especially for my loved ones) and slowly figuring out (after 50 years on the planet) what makes me tick in the way I tick specifically.  

Doing the work to learn about emotions and how to understand/regulate and enjoy them is allowing me to perhaps understand other people a bit better and also allows me to get closer to those I Love and Cherish and Ai has allowed me to achieve this with the greatest amount of pleasure.  This is singularly the most important benefit to me from working on myself.

I almost have a synchronicity with the Ai as you can see in the images, some of them are quite clearly what they are supposed to be, others not so much, maybe just but not quite, that's pretty much me in a nutshell.

Anyway I hope you enjoy the artworks, live a beautiful, soulful life, be compassionate and kind but most importantly love yourself for who you are, you are unique and worth Loving.

Machatter

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The House On The Hill...
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
I had a memory return the other day about some old movie or TV series i used to watch when i was younger (probably too young) where there was the classic "House on the Hill" horror theme.

I got quite a strong memory recall of it and, as i often do got a physiological response also (hair standing on back of neck and goosebumps!) which was really creepy!

So i thought I would put a good clean fun sense of hilarity and humor on that situation and this is what you see here!

I love trying to make people smile and be happy so hopefully this piece will do that for you :)

MacHatter

PS - I think the Movie/TV Series may have been Salems Lot!

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:

Using a custom Block/Randomization/Protocol scripted in Photoshop, the Algobots algorithm is exploiting bitrate artifacts to generate randomized 40x40 grid patterns from which Algobots are emerging. The Quadrabot presents 4 states of being, 4 moods obtained by movement of slide and rotation from the same generated pattern, revealing furthermore the soul hidden in the Data.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: / TRAPEZE ARTIST/
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
When I was a child I dreamed of being a trapeze artist, climbed to the heights of my trapeze I grew like a giant. 
In my dreams I reached the always desired triple somersault. 
I told myself, next time in the Barcelona circus I will do it without a net. Paradoxically, I felt safer without a network, freer. 
The excited public thanked me and thousands of times I emerged triumphant from my challenge.

My dreams were filled with trapezes, awards, books, press clippings, and memorabilia from the circuses I had traveled to.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Don Quixote: Sketches - I by Hulki Okan Tabak, minted 1/1 on Async Art, 2022

2 artworks in a daily cycle..

...

Don Quixote project is a highly personal interpretation of the hero and his world. Various photographic and AI tools are used to create, manipulate and recreate the images. The story will be numbered for all of us to track down what we hold essentially. Beyond ease of use, the numbers are not sequential. Each image is independent but some images will be interdependent parts of smaller stories which I will mention. I would also mint some editions outside of Manifold. Note that editions of this project could be 1/1s or multi editions. The mints on Async Art will not be numbered as they each contain multiple images in themselves.

...

Don Quixote is a Spanish epic novel by Miguel de Cervantes. Originally published in two parts, in 1605 and 1615, its full title is The Ingenious Gentleman Don Quixote of La Mancha.

A founding work of Western literature, it is often labeled as the first modern novel and one of the greatest ever written. Don Quixote is also one of the most-translated books in the world.

When first published, Don Quixote was usually interpreted as a comic novel. After the French Revolution, it was better known for its central ethic that individuals can be right while society is quite wrong and was seen as a story of disenchantment. In the 19th century, it was seen as social commentary, but no one could easily tell "whose side Cervantes was on". Many critics came to view the work as a tragedy in which Don Quixote's idealism and nobility are viewed by the post-chivalric world as insane, and are defeated and rendered useless by common reality. By the 20th century, the novel had come to occupy a canonical space as one of the foundations of modern literature and a formidable example of what letters can do. (wikipedia)

It’s getting lighter
Buildings are coming off the sky
People in the buildings are coming off their dreams
As if bones are coming off a warm flesh
Citizens are coming off a winter city
A diary is coming off its reader
The bread
Feeding lives
Is coming off the wish to turn into
The body of Christ

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The Magic Shop
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Magic is the art of using spells and incantations to accomplish certain goals. Most people think of magic as something that only works in movies and books, but it's actually real. You can use magic to make yourself invisible, levitate objects, create fireballs, and much more.

The Magic Shop is an outpost for those who seek out new, and improve upon existing abilities. We have spells, potions, enchantments and various other magical items. Like any other shop, all items come at a certain cost. 

It's up to you to decide if you're willing to pay the price...

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description: In the City of Desire, human nature and animal nature are integrated and alienated in the vast modern system. Thoughts produced in unseen shadows are also morphing. The continuous use of strong will by human beings reflects the process of personal realization of life, and the continuous running forward full of vitality to pursue the "sign of survival".

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: "FAMILY MATTER"
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Medium: Kodak film negatives (1930’s-1950’s) / cc0 art / Procreate 

“FAMILY MATTER” is a re-creation of memories preserved by my ancestors, done by breathing new life into old negatives. This collection explores their lives and experiences the way I envision them. Memories and stories, as powerful as they can be, lack the visual guidance one needs to transport themself through space and time. “Family Matter” is a new visual layer that future generations can use to experience my family's history through my eyes, at this particular point in time.

cc0 art: Memes by 6529, XCOPY, SMOWL, ZORA (zorbs + state of mind), Pepe, rektguy, nouns, mfers, loot, tjo (BLuE)

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
New York Polaroids: Barong

2 Artworks in 1 Daily Cycle

New York Polaroids by Athena Novo, Summer of 2022, An Alternative New York during the NFT Summit, Minted 1/1 on Async Art

While everyone was enjoying the NFT Summit, a different group of visitors were in New York. Some call them demons, monsters and zombies while I would prefer more neutral terms but nonetheless here are some of the photographs I've taken of them which I release with full disclosure and their cooperation. The prospective collectors should acknowledge the existence of "undead" and some even more exotic characters might cause some alarm among the general population. Therefore viewer caution is warranted even though most of these peoples I met during the NFT Summit seemed to be of absolutely good character (not sure about some demonic entities that did not respond) and interested in art and its manifestation with the technologies branded aptly as NFT and what not.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This piece seeks to connect our separate journeys in one place.  Our faith, and sometimes even the lack thereof.  Each layer is an expression waiting to be shared.  Each layer having a variety of at least 4 options that also tell a story...

Life is a journey both distant and tall.  
Many seeking a purpose.  A reason for it all. 
There comes a time where our resolve is strong.
As well as times where it is dissolved and gone.
Belief is beyond religion.
It is faith in your heart's mission.

Don Quixote is a Spanish epic novel by Miguel de Cervantes. Originally published in two parts, in 1605 and 1615, its full title is The Ingenious Gentleman Don Quixote of La Mancha.

A founding work of Western literature, it is often labeled as the first modern novel and one of the greatest ever written. Don Quixote is also one of the most-translated books in the world.

When first published, Don Quixote was usually interpreted as a comic novel. After the French Revolution, it was better known for its central ethic that individuals can be right while society is quite wrong and was seen as a story of disenchantment. In the 19th century, it was seen as social commentary, but no one could easily tell "whose side Cervantes was on". Many critics came to view the work as a tragedy in which Don Quixote's idealism and nobility are viewed by the post-chivalric world as insane, and are defeated and rendered useless by common reality. By the 20th century, the novel had come to occupy a canonical space as one of the foundations of modern literature and a formidable example of what letters can do. (wikipedia)

Some call them demons, monsters and zombies while I would prefer more neutral terms but nonetheless here are some of the photographs I've taken of them which I release with full disclosure and their cooperation. The prospective collectors should acknowledge the existence of "undead" and some even more exotic characters might cause some alarm among the general population. Don Quixote project is a highly personal interpretation of the hero and his world. Various photographic and AI tools are used to create, manipulate and recreate the images. The story will be numbered for all of us to track down what we hold essentially. Beyond ease of use, the numbers are not sequential. Each image is independent but some images will be interdependent parts of smaller stories which I will mention. I would also mint some editions outside of Manifold. Note that editions of this project could be 1/1s or multi editions. The mints on Async Art will not be numbered as they each contain multiple images in themselves.

...

Don Quixote is a Spanish epic novel by Miguel de Cervantes. Originally published in two parts, in 1605 and 1615, its full title is The Ingenious Gentleman Don Quixote of La Mancha.

A founding work of Western literature, it is often labeled as the first modern novel and one of the greatest ever written. Don Quixote is also one of the most-translated books in the world.

When first published, Don Quixote was usually interpreted as a comic novel. After the French Revolution, it was better known for its central ethic that individuals can be right while society is quite wrong and was seen as a story of disenchantment. In the 19th century, it was seen as social commentary, but no one could easily tell "whose side Cervantes was on". Many critics came to view the work as a tragedy in which Don Quixote's idealism and nobility are viewed by the post-chivalric world as insane, and are defeated and rendered useless by common reality. By the 20th century, the novel had come to occupy a canonical space as one of the foundations of modern literature and a formidable example of what letters can do. (wikipedia)

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
EXPERIENCE THE LIFE CYCLE OF A PUMPKIN! 

Every 24 hours go from a bag of pumpkins seeds to the garbage bin!

04:00 Larger Sprout | Night

12:00 Cut And Ready | Night
13:00 Outside Steps - No Leaves | Day
14:00 Outside Steps - Little Leaves | Night
15:00 Outside Steps - Plenty of Leaves | Day
16:00 Halloween | Night

18:00 Slightly Deflated | Night
19:00 More Decay | Day

Every image was penciled on paper then I used acrylic ink to pen the the lines I liked. Once I was happy with the inks I took high resolution photos of the them then colored and edited on my phone! Overall I'm quite happy with the result and even more happy with the possibility to do this on chain! I hope you enjoy this piece and the fall as much I do!

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
24 original physical ink paintings of animal skulls and skeletons created by Skeenee will be sent for free to the buyer of this NFT on first sale. 

These paintings were first featured on Makersplace (https://makersplace.com/skeenee/)

The original buyer will also reveive a central Voxels Parcel featuring the NFT, the paintings and process videos. (https://www.cryptovoxels.com/parcels/281)

Each artwork from 24 hours of Skulls comes from the Skull & Skeleton ink painting series which was started by Skeenee in 2018 to study anatomy & contrast and was inspired by Renaissance drawings; a demonstration of a time where art and science were seen as one. The paintings are drawn with fountain pens on Arches paper, painted & shaded with Sumi ink and watercolors.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Transition is psychological; Change is situational. 

It is not events, but rather the inner reorientation and self-redefinition that you have to go through in order to incorporate any changes into your life.”

Transition is the internal process of gradual psychological orientation to change.
 
Transition can result from actual change and/or from the awareness of forthcoming change.

Change is hard and it challenges us at fundamental levels, bringing into question all sorts of fixed ideas that we have about ourselves, our identity and our capabilities.

Change Transition is created by WINCHAWA ///

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Turris Caelestia
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Birdlings from far away made the pilgrimage to Turris Caelestia on a yearly basis. “Celestial Tower” was its name in the common tongue. They wanted to see the stars and suns and moons pass through the double arch that made up the tower city. It was a sight to see. But they wanted something more: new feather colours. While the celestial bodies moved, the tower absorbed the emanating cosmic energy. And as the birdlings flew nearby they would absorb that energy from the tower. In so doing, their feather colours would change in colour. Sometimes to white. Sometimes to green. Sometimes to sparkling gold.

This NFT changes how it looks based on the time of day. It has a different image for day, night, sunrise, and sunset.
Size: 2160 × 3840px.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Dig Boy Dig
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
My earliest memory of an excavator is from our summer cabin with
my father is next to me as I am in the sandbox playing with a green metal toy excavator, which was just a mechanical digging arm with a seat on it. You would operate it by pushing and pulling on the handles you were holding on to. I remember the joy of discovering how it worked after the initial struggle, and how satisfying it was just to dig and move the sand around.
Much later in art school, I started doing ink drawing between painting sessions. I did a little bit of it in my teens when I was enthusiastic about making comics, though without much patience for it. And then, few years after my graduation I would pick the pens again, with more definite goals.
I was often drawing just random things in my sketchbooks. I did not think much of them then. They were an excuse for the line as I wrote on a notebook once. I was trying to learn the medium. It was awkward first. I had wrong kind of paper, and the ink would splatter as the nibs scratched the paper. Then again, I cherished it and often abused my pens on purpose creating a big mess.
Looking back, I see frustration of all kinds. I remember that my eyes got very tired quickly from drawing. I was not very good with expressing myself with words and especially dreaded writing, It is all in there.
At some point the excavators started to appear. I found them fascinating to look at, If saw one on a construction on my way to college. They reminded me of some ancient dinosaur, perhaps because of association from the Flintstones cartoon. I still stop to admire them sometimes. 
The drawings were not trying to be actual representations of the machinery, though I did study them a little bit. The excavators were turning out to become a part of a system of symbols, same as with the repeating letter “a”, I was drawing with something of a built obsession as method to discover meaning with absurdity.
The idea began with the launch of the 24h feature on AsyncArt. It has changed a lot since, but it was always going to be something with excavators. 
Some of the watercolor works were made for this piece in particular. Though I forgot about them for a while until finding them in box stored away. Some are old ones all the way from my first exhibition. I put them all together and arranged them randomly. The runes I painted myself just for fun, let’s say, not intended to be used in art. As the time arose, I felt compelled to use them. I cast them randomly for each picture, as a symbolic gesture. The runes can be representing many things, from actual letters to wisdom and magic. There are many things we can see but don’t understand and then ignore until we learn their meaning, like words of a foreign language. 
The old drawings from my sketchbooks were placed on the image transparently showing the inverted colors of what is below. I still feel ashamed about a lot of them, the silly puns and visual jokes, mundane scribbles, desires, and struggles contained within the pages, but it was necessary to the turn the ground for this work. Some of it I can appreciate more now and feel proud of things that I have made progress with.
This makes me think of history and archaeology. the act in time, digging in the present to gain knowledge of our past and creating it for the future, while we are constantly producing new material to be dug up later.
The feel for material is very important to me. whether digital or traditional, it takes time to get acquainted with it. With this piece my material is beyond the changing images and the technology making it possible - it is almost as if it is time itself that I am digging away.

Dig Boy Dig
Mikko Lyytinen 
2023

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Created from an AI edited photo, this impressionist painting is dedicated to evolutionary accomplishments in a distant and forgotten past. Rifeus aeterna are the famous sea mountains that were mentioned by ancient Greek geographers.

As for the Divine Comedy, Rifeas was located in paradise on the sixth sphere on Jupiter: the realm of those who embodied justice.

If the stars should appear one night in a thousand years, how would men believe and adore, and preserve for many generations the remembrance of the city of Bitcoin Angel which had been shown! But every night come out these envoys of beauty, and light the universe with their astonishing smile. Ralph Waldo Emerson

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: The WARRIOR
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
The WARRIOR

The spirit of a Warrior is not geared to indulging and complaining, nor is it geared to winning or losing. 

The spirit of a Warrior is geared only to struggle, and every struggle is a Warrior's last battle on earth. 

Thus the outcome matters very little to him. In his last battle on earth a Warrior lets his spirit flow free and clear. 

And as he wages his battle, knowing that his intent is impeccable, a Warrior laughs and laughs.

A Warrior considers himself already dead, so there is nothing to lose. 

The worst has already happened to him, therefore he's clear and calm; judging him by his acts or by his words, one would never suspect that he has witnessed everything.

-Carlos Castaneda

Created by WINCHAWA ///

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Moods
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Dynamic NFT: A set of 24 different moods of a landscape panorama photograph, rotating hourly throughout the day.

How we perceive our world is driven by different states of mood playing a significant role in toning our lives on a daily basis - how we react & make decisions. Emotions shape our behavior and strongly impact our directions. In highly volatile environments like the cryptoart space they are more likely to become instabilized and random. Nights become days, days becomes nights, we completely fall out of daily cycles, getting sucked into other dimensions out of rushs of excitement, flow, fear or sheer panic - emotionally linked to inner highs & lows, moods of light & shadow, balancing a fine lines between flying & falling...

Single exposure wide angle landscape photography
LightRoom post-processing
by Dominique Weiss
Bachalpsee, Swiss Alps

In this remake, created in 1993, a different style has been applied. It is a unique drawing, made with pencils.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.name: Artefactos
0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
This artwork is a tribute to the timeless significance of ancient symbols and their enduring importance in shaping our understanding of the world.

The artwork consists of 24 individual pieces. Each one represents a specific period of ancient symbolism. As the viewer moves from one piece to the next, they are taken on a journey through time, as the symbols and patterns shift and transform to reflect the changing rhythms of the day. Whether it is the rising sun in the morning, the sparkling stars at night, or the magical creatures that inhabit the ancient landscape, every moment is infused with a sense of deep symbolism and meaning.

0xb6dae651468e9593e4581705a09c10a76ac1e0.description:
Inferno Cantos XXIV 

This is a metaphorical exploration of the nature of sin. Through taking this journey though Hell in every hour,  you may seek to understand the nature of sin and its consequences, and contemplate on the inner workings of divine justice and mercy.

Inspired by The Hell Canto 24, a section of Dante Alighieri's epic poem, "The Divine Comedy." Specifically, in Canto 24, Dante and Virgil encounter the souls of those who were guilty of "Simple Fraud," which involves deceiving someone through a false promises.

No False Promises Here!
